job.abstract: Leverage your expert skills and enterprise experience with MSBI, Power BI, Tableau, SQL Server + Azure data tools (Data Factory, Data Bricks etc.)
job.content:
As some with significant professional work experience in Business Intelligence (BI) and Analytics and an expert with Microsoft BI (MSBI) - SSIS / SSRS / SSAS, Power BI, SQL Server, and ideally experience in Azure data tools - Data Factory, Databricks etc - you understand the value of data to help solve business problems.
You will also have a passion for data visualisation whether it's developing models, prototypes, reports or dashboards.

You’re happy to roll up your sleeves and see projects through from end-to-end including mapping business processes, conduct requirements analysis and documentation. Most importantly you understand that your role is all about helping our clients source, transform and interpret data into actionable metrics to optimise their business.

Our team of broadly experienced Consultants, work on a diverse portfolio of client, projects, and innovation initiatives - some of which will make you the envy of your peers.
  

Applicants MUST have Australian Citizenship, as the successful person will need to gain and maintain at least baseline security clearance.


Location: Adelaide, SA (hybrid)
Type: Permanant, full time
Start: ASAP


Required skills and experience:
  • Previous experience in a similar role as a Microsoft BI / Analytics Specialist
  • Advanced skills in SQL Server
  • Significant, commercial, hands-on experience across the Microsoft BI stack (SSIS, SSRS, SSAS)
  • An expert in Power BI
  • Experience working in a complex enterprise data warehouse environment
  • Solid Agile environment experience
  • Knowledge and experience of DWH, BI, and analytics best practice
  • Ability to develop requirements into actionable business analytics strategies, roadmaps, and BI solutions
  • Able to quickly build strong relationships with decision-makers, and become their trusted advisor
  • Knowledge of Azure data tools; Databricks, Data Factory, Data Lake etc. Python and R would be beneficial, but are not essential
  
Working at DWS offers you:
  • Ongoing professional and career development
  • Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses
  • An active social club that hosts regular, subsidised events
  • Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, Apple products and much more

Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCLTech. With offices across Australia, we have over 800 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation.

job.title: Senior Azure Data Engineer - Melbourne
job.abstract: Senior Azure Data Engineer, Melbourne, Permanent, ETL, SQL, Data Lake, Data Factory, DAX etc
job.content:
My Melbourne based client is looking for multiple Senior Azure Data Engineers for permanent roles.

Responsibilities:
  • Develop ELT pipelines in and out of data warehouse using Azure Data Factory and Databricks.
  • Integrate on-premises infrastructure with public cloud AZURE infrastructure.
  • Translate requirements for BI, Reporting and Analytics to database modelling and designs.
  • Partner with the Data Architects, Product Managers and Scrum Masters to deliver data integrations and BI solutions required for various projects.
  • Create, prepare, implement, and maintain reporting dashboards using Power BI
Skills and experience:
  • Previous experience in Data Warehouse / Data Lake implementations
  • Hands-on experience in Azure Data Platform
  • Excellent communication skills
In more detail, your experience and skills include:
  • Must have a mimimum 5+ experience working as an Azure Data Consultant, and 7 to 8+ years in Data Warehousing, ETL/ELT, BI, and Analytics projects.
  • Must have experience at least one (2) end to end implementation of Azure Cloud Data Warehouse and two (4) end to end data warehouse implementations.
  • Expertise in data modelling, ELT using ADF, implementing complex views, stored procedures and standard DWH and ETL/ELT concepts.
  • Extensive design and implementation experience in Azure cloud data platform and modern data warehousing. Including Security, Azure Logging and Monitoring, Azure Databricks, Synapse, Azure Blob Storage, Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory, Azure SQL Database, Azure Analysis Services, Power BI 
  • Deep understanding of relational and NoSQL data stores, methods, and approaches (star and snowflake, dimensional modelling).
  • Experience with data security and data access controls and design.
  • Proficiency in RDBMS, complex SQL, PL/SQL, performance tuning and troubleshooting.
  • 4+ years as full stack MS Power BI modelling (M code), Dax, data storytelling, report publishing, security, and knowledge of how people make decisions with data.
  • Provide resolution to an extensive range of complex data pipeline-related problems proactively and as issues surface.
  • Must have experience with Agile development methodologies.
Must be Australian Citizen or Permanent Resident

job.title: Senior BI Data and Reporting Analyst - Azure
job.abstract: Provide valuable insights and help us make data-driven decisions. Sydney CBD location, right next to Wynyard Station. Full time perm role.
job.content:
WHO WE ARE?

Scape’s vision is to be the Earth’s best living company (so you can see straight off the bat we are a conservative bunch!). We are a leading provider of student accommodation in Australia. We currently have the capacity to provide a home to 15,000 students (and are growing) and we don't simply provide a bed and roof; we also provide a unique, amazing experience and a safe environment to help students make the most of their studies.

 

THE ROLE

As the Senior BI Data and Reporting Analyst, you will work closely with internal teams to ensure the workforce is supported by developing and delivering our data analytics and reporting capabilities. Working closely with multiple stakeholders, you will play a key role in translating business requests into reports and dashboards in PowerBI.

 

THE IDEAL CANDIDATE

You will be a highly motivated and passionate data professional who will develop, maintain & support Scape’s Reporting and Power BI capability, operating as a consultant within the Technology team. Your Power BI capability will focus on converting various business units reporting requirements into user friendly, storytelling reports & dashboards.

You will have:

  • Demonstrated experience in the delivery of Business Intelligence and reporting systems.
  • Management of Data warehouse methodology Data Vault 2.0 and Dimension Modelling
  • A demonstrated in-depth knowledge of database infrastructure and cloud data solutions, preferably Azure suite (SQL, Analysis Services, Power BI, Dataverse, Gen II data lake, Synapse, Data Factory)
  • Ability to scope and define data sets needed for specific use cases and identify data gaps.
  • Modelling experience for analytical/OLAP systems - preferably Cloud Native Database(s)
  • Demonstrated experience in administration and support of databases & proficient at writing SQL queries
  • Experience building models in spreadsheets. Comfortable writing formulas and VBA in Excel

 

PERKS OF WORKING WITH SCAPE

At Scape, we are all about creating and sharing good vibes. Below are just some of the scape-tastic perks of joining our team:

  • A day to celebrate your birthday, however, you want
  • A recharge day (known affectionately as a Bueller Day!)
  • ‘Escapes’ – stay at any of our buildings in any state for up to 5 nights free of charge
  • Referral bonuses
  • EAP, Sonder & Duress support

 

THE FINE PRINT

At Scape we believe that we are most successful and effective when we work together as a team.

This is a great time to be joining a growing business, that is willing and able to make a difference for our residents (predominately students), stakeholders and the community as a whole. If this role sounds like the challenge you have been looking for, then apply now!

job.title: Senior Azure Data Engineer
job.abstract: Define innovative solutions for building, deploying, & supporting data cloud services within Azure environment.  Support DMAIC initiatives.
job.content:
About the Role

We are seeking a Senior Azure Data Engineer for a full time permanent contract working in a flexible / hybrid nature.

Reporting to the Senior Manager Applications Development, you will support the DMAIC project, and partner with a broad spectrum of stakeholders to support the delivery of innovative and optimised performance reporting.

You will have an opportunity to define innovative solutions for building, deploying, and supporting data cloud services within Azure environment and as such a high level Azure Data & Analytics PaaS, Azure DevOps, Azure Pipeline, CI/CD and ETL experience is required.

Location: based in Redfern, Sydney or Blackburn, Melbourne or Brisbane, Queensland (hybrid WFH).



Key responsibilities:

  • Understand existing business processes and practices, identify opportunities, and implement solutions leveraging Azure data and analytics PaaS deployment standards and processes
  • Define technical strategy and solutions designs for ETL and Azure DevOps pipeline services
  • Develop, Maintain & Support Data solution leveraging Azure Analytics, Data, Integration PaaS services
  • Work collaboratively with other Developers, Data Architect, Business & Enterprise Data Architects, and other cross functional project team members to achieve project goals.
  • Facilitate the development of ETL and Data engineering best practice (e.g., documentation standard), guidelines e.g. code reuse, automation, deployment strategies and help to promote the viability/usefulness of the solutions.

About You

Qualifications:

  • Tertiary qualifications in the relevant technologies or proven relevant work experience.
  • Proven experience in orchestrating ETL and data engineering solutions on cloud using on premise and/or cloud data sources on Azure Cloud platform
  • Strong experience on Azure Data & Analytics PaaS, Azure DevOps, Azure Pipeline and CI/CD.
  • Good understanding SQL and database concepts

Why work for us

  • Eligible employees can access NFP salary packaging ($15,900 tax free)
  • Flexible working conditions
  • Internationally renowned not-for-profit organisation
  • Rare opportunity to work with passionate, like-minded people who enjoy being a part of an organization that makes a difference within the Australian community
  • An inclusive culture of dedicated, passionate and professional team members
  • Opportunity for career development
  • Paid parental leave
  • Employee Assistance Program - Independent confidential counselling service

HOW TO APPLY

If you're excited by this unique opportunity, the above sounds like you, and you have a heart for working for an organisation that truly does transform lives, we would love to speak to you. We are looking for compassionate people who share our mission and values. If you have the passion and drive to commit yourself to a challenging and rewarding role; we invite you to apply via the link and submit a current CV and a cover letter which details your alignment with the essential requirements of the role.

job.abstract: An Azure Data Engineer role is currently available with a Queensland State Government Department.
job.content:
A Data Engineer role is currently available with a Queensland State Government Department. Located in Brisbane CBD, the Data Engineer will be helping to build, maintain and optimize the data infrastructure in the department's recent migration from on-prem to Cloud.

Key responsibilities:

  • Develop ETL/ELT pipelines using Azure Data Factory and Databricks.
  • Develop Azure Data Factory objectives - ADF Pipeline, configuration, triggers, parameters, variables, Integration's services runtime.
  • Finetune the data pipeline performance with PySpark.
  • Contribute strong understanding and technical skills across Azure.
  • Drive the development and implementation of data engineering road-map.
  • Ensure that high quality documentation is developed of the process for ease of knowledge transfer.
  • Develop and maintain data models to support business objectives.
  • Monitor and troubleshoot data pipeline performance issues.

The ideal candidate for this role will possess the following:

  • Experience working with large datasets and complex data pipelines.
  • Excellent communication and problem-solving skills.
  • 3+ years of experience in data engineering.

Experience with the following technologies:

  • Azure Data Factory
  • Azure DataBricks
  • Azure Synapse Analytics (dedicated SQL Pool)
  • Azure Data Lake Gen2

Knowledge of the following languages:

  • Python
  • PySpark
  • Spark SQL

If you are interested please hit "APPLY" or email your resume to Sian Asnicar at sian.asnicar@randstad.com.au

At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

job.title: Senior Data Engineer - Azure
job.abstract: With our continued business growth we have a newly created position for a Senior Data Engineer to join our Technical Service Team!
job.content:
What we can offer you

At Specsavers we promise to make you feel good, cared for and smart. Being Great Place to Work accredited for the last three years, this is a great opportunity to join us as we continue our path to not just be great but be the BEST place to work!

We are well known for valuing our people and providing a supportive, driven and inclusive culture. Beyond that, we also have a range of different benefits within the support office, that include:

  • Quarterly Bonus Scheme 
  • Two free pairs of glasses
  • On site free parking
  • Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Paid Parental leave
  • Health & Wellbeing programs
  • Fully funded Social Club – provides a wide range of activities throughout the year.

 

The Role & Team

To support the way our Data team is transforming Specsavers into a data-driven business and to support with our continued business growth we have a newly created position for a Senior Data Engineer to join our Technical Service Team. The team’s vision is to establish a data culture within the business and to deliver high quality data products to deliver organisation wide insights and quality data products to help accelerate robust decision making, drive consistency and enable self-service for the business. 

Reporting into our Lead Data Engineer, you will look at our overall technical capability for ingesting, managing and exploiting data (via modelling and modelled data), while ensuring future capability expansion, cost management and scalability. 

At Specsavers, we believe in adopting a hybrid approach to support our people and the future of work. When not working from an alternative location, you will be based at our support office in Port Melbourne. 

 

What we are looking for

  • Strong technical ability and understanding of how databases work, as well as the use of data development software (ETL packages) and programming languages (SQL, Python and Pyspark) to develop tools to extract, transform and load data, as well as to document the creation of these tools.
  • Proficient capability to understand business processes in detail, to apply knowledge and acquire more, to understand and create requirements, apply them to a tool design and execute its build.
  • Excellent communication skills as you will need to discuss technical principles and business processes in simple language to people at all levels. 
  • Hands on experience with:
    • Azure Data Lake 
    • Azure Data Factory 
    • Azure Databricks (inc. SQL and Python) 
    • Azure SQL Server 
    • Azure DevOps/Git 
  • Enthusiasm for learning, trying new things, sharing knowledge and developing skills in others
  • The ability to invent and innovate in the determination of creative solutions to all problems, and to take on work for which there is no set of rules or industry-standard answer 

 

About Us

At Specsavers we believe a diverse, inclusive and flexible culture enables our people to bring their whole selves to work and be proud of doing so. When it comes to flexibility, we understand that one size doesn't fit all. Our flexible working at Specsavers enables us to work in ways that support our lifestyle to help us balance our career with the other important things in life

Creating a great place to work for our people is pinnacle to us and along with our Behaviours is at the core of everything we do, ensuring our people feel good, cared for and smart. We like to think it’s a fun and positive place to work – why not have a look for yourself https://join.specsavers.com/au/department/support-office/ 
 
Applicants for the role are required to have current working rights as per, relevant government legislation.

Bluefin Resources are working with a prestigious government enterprise to recruit an Azure Data Engineer on an initial 4 month contract plus extensions.

Role

We are looking for a Data Engineer that specializes in Data Warehousing using Azure resources and Microsoft Business Intelligence tools, within the Analytics Unit, Information Technology Directorate, to start immediately for an initial 4 months with the possibility of extension.

Background and job description

The Data Engineer plays a critical role in designing, developing and implementing the solution, monitoring, security, and privacy of data using the full stack of data services.

The ideal candidate is a self-motivated, highly detail-oriented team-player with a positive drive to strategize and implement BI solutions that enable the business to derive valuable insights.

You will join a tight knit group of key contributors who are actively working together to achieve aggressive goals and meet timelines to drive the business forward.

Key accountabilities include

  1. Understand the Business Context and Requirements
  2. Collaborate with other team members to achieve business objectives
  3. Conduct feasibility analysis by verifying requirements, ingesting and profiling data.
  4. Complete design, data models, loading approaches and source to target mapping documents
  5. Develop ELT for Azure Synapse Analytics (using Azure Data Factory, SSIS, PolyBase, Stream Analytics)
  6. Create and manage entities, business rules and strategies in master data management
  7. Develop, manage and deploy SQL, MDX/DAX, PowerShell, C# and Python source code using Azure DevOps
  8. Interpret trends and patterns, prepare data for prescriptive and predictive modeling.
  9. Develop Star schema, Facts & Dimensions, Analysis services cubes and Reports in Microsoft BI tools including Power BI and Azure Analysis Services
  10. Develop and conduct unit testing
  11. Conduct initial Root Cause Analysis and defect triage

Selection Criteria

  1. Demonstrable experience working in Data Warehouse or Business Intelligence environments.
  2. Excellent experience working with Microsoft SQL databases and Azure Synapse Analytics
  3. Working experience in SQL Server Integration services and SSAS
  4. Working knowledge of Azure Data Factory, Stream Analytics
  5. Comprehensive SQL, PowerBI and DAX knowledge and experience
  6. Working knowledge of Python or C#
  7. Experience in working with large, complex Data Warehouses using the Microsoft BI Stack within an Azure or cloud-based environment

On Offer - An initial 4 month contract with likely ongoing extensions that offers great working flexibility with a mix of working from home to accessional visits to the Sydney office.

You will work with a great and well-established team and be part of something meaningful and rewarding where you will make a real difference!

job.title: Business Development Manager
job.abstract: A fantastic opportunity to help build, grow, and shape the future of our successful IT Consulting business. Utilise your current network and contacts!
job.content:
About Us:
Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCLTech. With offices across Australia, we have over 700 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane, and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer-driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation.

Start: ASAP
Type: Permanent, full time
Where: Melbourne CBD + WFH (flexible hybrid)
Salary: $150-180K base + uncapped commission


About the role: 
As an expert in hunting all new IT Consultancy opportunities, you’ll be a creative and forward-thinking addition to the DWS team. With a self-starter yet collaborative working style, you’ll roll up your sleeves and generate leads, actively seeking and responding to tenders, and managing the end-to-end bid process.
We won't sugar coat it; this is a big role; it's demanding and challenging. However, in return for your hard work you will get the opportunity to help shape our very well-established Melbourne head-office of the wider Australia & NZ business.


About you:
You’re a real 'go-getter' that has an impressive network of major enterprise scale customer contacts. Someone who isn’t afraid to put themselves out there and generate the big new leads through your contact networks, LinkedIn, or picking up the phone to make a connection. You’re all about being social and building long-term client relationships. Most importantly, you know your area of expertise well and have a record of success. You appreciate technology and understand the use of Cloud, Data, Business Consulting, Applications, Solutions Development, and Integration.
    
Your Skills and Experience
  • Previous experience working within a similar all new business development role in a professional services / consulting organisation
  • Currently working with major Tier 1, enterprise scale and/or government clients
  • A strong understanding of technology (AWS/Azure, Data, Software Development, Testing, Automation etc.)  
  • An established enterprise scale client network in Melbourne 
  • The ability to work in a consultative and collaborative way
  • Proven experience building a brand-new sales pipeline in various industry sectors
  • Great communication and interpersonal skills
  • A strong understanding of the sales cycle
  • The ability to apply sales methodologies to a variety of solutions and clients
  
We’ll make you feel rewarded:
While we offer a generous compensation package ($150K+ package with uncapped commissions), working at DWS is more than just about the salary.
We’re all about professional development and taking your career to new levels. You'll have access to a range of very attractive products and services available to you including discounts on health insurance, gym memberships, Apple products, and much more.
Most importantly, we know how to have fun; our team members work hard but they also let their hair down with regular events hosted by our social club.
  

Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now!
www.dws.com.au

No agencies please – our in-house talent acquisition team have this covered.
#LI-CH1

job.title: Data Governance Analyst
job.abstract: Excellent opportunity for an experienced Data Governance Analyst to join a market leader in an exciting period of growth!
job.content:
About the Opportunity

As part of the Data Governance & Privacy team, this role will play a critical part in implementing a robust data governance framework across Endeavour Drinks Group.

With an increasing focus across the group on the use of data to empower decision making and uplift revenue, this role performs a critical function to ensure better understanding, quality, and governance of data.

Drive the delivery of data governance across Endeavour and work with the data governance & privacy team to develop and execute a strategic road map to ensure our data is safe and trusted.

A day in the life of a Data Governance Analyst @ Endeavour ...

  • Create and conduct governance processes to measure data management and data quality maturity across various domains
  • Create, update & support policies, standards, and processes related to data management, quality, access, and security are followed in all environments. Create repeatable data management processes within Data Governance & Data Ingestion space
  • Work with stakeholders to understand, prioritise, and document business and technical needs, and to ensure alignment with DG strategy
  • Support the implementation of a new data lineage, metadata & reference data management framework and technology solution in partnership with IT. Utilise this solution to identify, initiate and champion improvements in data quality, sustainability and security.
  • Support the requirement to ensure Endeavour data assets are classified, certified and prioritised to enable our community of users to trust the data they use in their decision making processes.
  • Work to uplift the group-wide Endeavour data culture and capabilities, alongside other members of the data and Analytics team,
  • Contribute to the management of a portfolio of data governance initiatives for Endeavour. This includes the development of concepts, business cases, project planning, and delivery.
  • Improvement in Endeavour data governance framework capability maturity assessment.
  • Stay abreast of regulatory change and how this may impact on data governance and assist in appropriate responses across Endeavour
  • Data governance adoption and embedding (governance forums attendance, deliverables, outcomes).
  • Strength of critical relationships with the group data governance team and Endeavour Stakeholders.
  • Project initiatives delivered on time, within budget, to agreed scope, with positive stakeholder feedback

What you'll need to succeed

  • 5+ years of experience in a data governance analyst and/or project management role in a data or risk related role within a large organisation or consulting firm.
  • Experience in implementing frameworks, policies, processes, and transformational agendas in large organisations.
  • Hands on experience using data governance tools including; Collibra or Ataccama is an added advantage.
  • Hands-on experience managing enterprise cloud data platform including; GCP or Azure (bigquery, data loss prevention, data catalogue & cloud IAM) an added advantage
  • Demonstrated experience working in an Agile project delivery model environment.
  • Eagerness to work in a fun, dynamic, and fast-paced environment.
  • Exposure to data governance, data information security practices, and cloud databases.

What's in it for you?

  • Excellent remuneration package and flexible working in every sense. We value our people
  • Everyday Rewards plus card - access exclusive employee discounts across Woolworths, BigW and Endeavour Group brands (BWS, Dan Murphy's etc) and 50% off food at ALH venues.
  • Our innovative ways of working include headspace mornings once a month (no meetings company-wide), opportunity to partner alongside bright minds and genuine investment in leading technologies
  • Paid learning & development opportunities
  • Career progression to help you realise your potential. As our business grows so do the opportunities for our people
  • Access to our Endeavour Group Employee Share Scheme!
  • Wine education: Bronze, Silver & Gold certifications
  • Work with an industry-leading team and be a part of one of the most exciting retail transformations in Australia

Grow with Endeavour Group

Endeavour Group comprises a diverse range of drinks and hospitality businesses including BWS, Dan Murphy's, ALH Hotels and Pinnacle Drinks. We are focused on growing and transforming our businesses to meet the changing needs of customers and we're driven by a culture that puts our customers and team first.

As an inclusive, team-first company, our people are at the core of everything we do. We care deeply about creating a workplace where our team members feel valued, respected and empowered. We are committed to providing equal opportunity regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, disability or sexual orientation. At Endeavour Group we value flexibility, and encourage our team members to work in ways that meet their work/life commitments and support their wellbeing.

We work hard to create a safe and inclusive environment for all, and most importantly, we're all about creating a more sociable future - for our customers and for each other.

We'd love to hear from You

If you meet a number of the requirements, but not all, we encourage you to submit your application.

You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn [link removed]or via www.wowcareers.com.au #LI #work180

Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

job.title: Senior Data Engineer
job.abstract: Be a driving force in the design and development of our new cloud data platform using modern Azure technologies. At Icon, You Can. Flex on location.
job.content:
Icon Group is Australia’s largest dedicated cancer care provider and has expanded globally into Singapore, Mainland China, Hong Kong and New Zealand. We are built on a strong but simple vision – to deliver the best care possible, to as many people as possible, as close to home as possible. 
 
With more than 3,000 employees company-wide, we bring together all aspects of quality cancer care, including medical oncology, radiation oncology, haematology, pharmacy and chemotherapy compounding to deliver a true end-to-end seamless service for cancer patients internationally. 
 
Here’s what our people said what it takes to succeed and love life at Icon
  • You’ll truly want to work together towards our ambitious vision and goals
  • You’ll embrace and enjoy pace, progress, and change – we rarely sit still for long
  • You’ll need a serious work ethic and a thirst for job satisfaction that sees you putting up your hand to  grab opportunities
A few of our benefits 
  • Discounts and cashback on hundreds of brands through our internal ignite app
  • Flexible work arrangements, including remote working, compressed work weeks, varying start-finish times and so much more!
  • Access to novated lease options via our partner RemServ
  • Access to paid parental leave
  • Access to our Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
  • Professional development
The Opportunity
  
As a Senior Data Engineer on a permanent full-time basis, you’ll join our growing Data & Analytics team to design and develop our new Azure Data Platform and be a driving force as we embark on an exciting journey to be smarter with data.
  
We think it’s cool that our HQ is in South Brisbane, but we’re open to consider candidates located elsewhere, and we offer great, flexible work arrangements.
  
Working directly with the business, you’ll build our new Azure Data Platform and help to establish a self-service capability by maturing our cloud platform to support operational reporting as well as ad-hoc experimentation and analytics. You’ll be developing the Azure Data Platform as a primary focus but also be comfortable designing and developing data products that leverage it (integration solutions, reports, etc), while sharing knowledge and strengthening the capabilities of the team. The position will interface directly with the business and as such you’ll need to be comfortable in a business-facing role.

Our people make us who we are and here you’ll play a key part in contributing to our services by:   
  • Designing and delivering our new Azure Data Platform to enable the Icon Group business to leverage our data assets
  • Supporting the onboarding of new data sources into the platform by building highly optimised, resilient, scalable data pipelines
  • Working in close partnership with the business to design and develop data models
  • Developing data products which put the right information in front of the right people at the right time
  • Working with delivery teams to provision data to support use cases
About You
  • Bachelors’ degree with a relevant focus
  • Significant experience developing data ingestion solutions in the Azure ecosystem – Data Factory, Data Bricks, Synapse, Data Lake
  • Experience designing and developing data models across a range of functional areas
  • Experience in data profiling, facilitating business-led data cleansing, and Data Quality frameworks
  • Experience with CI/CD process and tools and sound knowledge of software engineering principles
  • Self-motivated individual able to work autonomously and as part of a team
  • Ability to build strong working relationships and a demonstrated willingness to be a team player
  • Comfortable and confident facilitating data-focused workshops with the business
Excited to join us and help change people’s lives for the better? 
 
Apply Now because At Icon, You Can. 
  
Visit https://icongroup.global/en/careers/our-people/stories/ to read the stories of our incredible people. 
 
Icon Group celebrates diversity and is committed to creating an inclusive workplace for all employees. We encourage applications from all diverse backgrounds.

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: IM SYSTEMS is seeking a Data Engineer to support their ongoing Melbourne based projects.
job.content:
IM SYSTEMS is seeking a Data Engineer to support their ongoing Melbourne based projects.  

IM Systems (IMS) specialises in the full enterprise data lifecycle – covering collection, management, transformation, and usage of Data and Information.  

We are looking for a Data Engineer to work with our team of expert professionals. With a number of exciting engagements commencing, this position will work within our expanding Data Engineering practice. This is a full time, Melbourne based position with a mix of on-site and remote working. In this position you will have the opportunity to learn and grow from a team of expert professionals highly skilled in the data industry.

Data Engineer 

  • Working closely with our experienced Data Engineers/Cloud Architects on a number of data related activities
  • Designing ingestion processes and implementing ingestion frameworks
  • Supporting senior consultants with the provision of our advisory services 
  • Building enterprise data platforms such as Data Lakes/Data Warehouses using Azure or Microsoft SQL server
  • Support the design and building of data structures and pipelines to client specifications  

 The successful candidate will have the following skills and attributes:  

  •  Some experience in Data Engineering - understanding of data integration 
  • Ability to contribute to building and engineering data pipelines (Microsoft Azure or AWS) 
  • Understanding of ELT and ETL processes for Data Warehouse / Data Lake using the Azure tech stack or other tools
  • Familiarity with one or more of Azure, AWS, Google, or on-premises database platforms
  • Aspirations to learn within the data domain 
  • Self-motivated and ability to work with limited guidance on set tasks and accountabilities 
  • Ability to manage competing activities and tasks  
  • Some knowledge of data warehouse / data hub implementations

 COMPANY PROFILE 

  • We offer flexible work arrangements. 
  • Our culture values people as individuals, and we invest in our people to get the best out of them. 
  • We love innovation, excellence and thinking outside the square. 
  • We are focused, agile and nimble; offering our clients a breath of a fresh air over the larger management consultancies. 

MANDATORY SKILLS and ATTRIBUTES 

To be a member of the IMS team, you must have the following: 

  • General understanding of the data management landscape – including data governance, data capture, data hub / warehouse / reporting platforms, data modelling, master data management, data analysis, metadata management. 
  • Good verbal and written communication skills. 
  • Good presentation skills. 
  • Ability to establish professional rapport with customers
  • Self-motivated, with a positive attitude towards keeping abreast of new learnings and technologies. 
  • Experience in working in a team environment 

If you are a confident individual with the ability to absorb information and learn and grow, we are keen to talk to you. 


Prior applicants matching the criteria should re-apply to be considered

job.abstract: An exciting contract role for a Senior Azure Cloud / Data Engineer has arisen, to work on a Data and Analytics platform program in Brisbane.
job.content:
About the Role

We are looking for a Senior Cloud Engineer to work on an exciting Data and Analytics program.

You will be responsible for undertaking the development and maintenance of a high quality, reliable, secure cloud platform. Additionally, you will play a key role in advancing the DevSecOps maturity of the business in consultation with providers of cloud platforms (Microsoft Azure), vendors of on-premise/cloud applications, development and testing service providers.

The organisation is working on solutions that are primarily based on a serverless architecture which leverages Microsoft Azure technologies, such as: Power Platform, Dynamics 365, Integration Services (including API Management), identity & access management and security management.

The Senior Cloud Engineer operates within an Agile and Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe) working environment working closely with Product Managers, Product Owners, Scrum Masters, Solution Architects, project teams and IT Applications and Operations teams in the corporate IT unit as well as federated IT areas and third party providers.


Working in partnership with the delivery and operational teams, you will:

  • Provide input and guidance into application and product architecture and solution design discussions, contributing to the development of reliable, secure, and cost-efficient (whole of life) solutions
  • On-board and streamline CI/CD processes for parts of the system that are currently not Continuously Integrated.
  • Provide technical advice to project teams on Azure infrastructure architecture, design and connectivity.
  • Implement automation and orchestration and regularly review/optimize CI/CD processes and tools (across Azure) to reduce manual tasks, improve release cadence, reliability, repeatability and quality.
  • Monitor CI/CD practices across corporate IT and federated IT areas identifying opportunities to informally share knowledge, formally set/update standards or policies and leverage innovation between teams .
  • Apply infrastructure knowledge to lead practices/topics such as Load Balancing, API Gateways, DBMSs, DNS configuration, Azure virtual networking, RBAC design, implementation, monitoring etc.
  • Work with technical stakeholders to plan and migrate existing on-premise Microsoft products to cloud based equivalents (Azure).
  • Monitor, manage, capacity and undertake planning & configuration of production and non-production Azure environments

The tech involved:

    • Enterprise-grade DevOps
    • CI/CD Experience with a variety of deployment automation and configuration management tools
      • Azure DevOps
    • Infrastructure as code
    • Public Sector cloud administration
    • Azure specific technologies
      • Active Directory and RBAC
      • Virtual Networking
      • SQL Managed Instance
  • Data Factory
    • Synapse Link
    • Purview
    • Power BI
    • Synapse Analytics
    • Azure Security Controls including
      • Security Centre
      • Bastion
      • Threat Modelling
      • Key Vault
      • Firewalls
      • Network Security Groups
      • Two-factor authentication management
  • Data security & encryption
  • Cloud System Administration
    • Windows & Linux based systems administration
    • Scripting experience in a cloud-based environment
  • Azure specific technologies
    • Azure Functions & Logic Apps
    • Azure API Apps, Service & Management Tooling
    • Azure Monitoring & Azure Log Analytics (to trigger automation)
    • Dynamics 365 and Dataverse
  • Multi Cloud - Integrations between On Prem, Azure and AWS

The following certifications would be highly regarded:

  • Microsoft Azure DevOps Solutions Certifications (AZ 400, AZ 301, AZ 70-487)
  • Certified Cloud Security Professional
  • Azure Security Engineer - Associate

For more information, contact Sian on sian.asnicar@randstad.com.au or apply now

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Deliver organisation wide insights and help accelerate robust decision making, drive consistency and enable self-service for our business
job.content:
What we can offer you

At Specsavers we promise to make you feel good, cared for and smart. Being Great Place to Work accredited for the last three years, this is a great opportunity to join us as we continue our path to not just be great but be the BEST place to work!

We are well known for valuing our people and providing a supportive, driven and inclusive culture. Beyond that, we also have a range of different benefits within the support office, that include:

  • Quarterly Bonus Scheme
  • Two free pairs of glasses
  • On site free parking
  • Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Paid Parental leave
  • Health & Wellbeing programs
  • Fully funded Social Club – provides a wide range of activities throughout the year.

 

The Role & Team

To support our continued business growth our Technology department is rapidly growing, and we have newly created opportunities for driven and passionate Data Engineers to join our Technical Services team, who pride themselves on cultivating a culture of growth and opportunity with a focus on career development and progression. Reporting into our Lead Data Engineer, you will work with the broader local data team who work collaboratively with our business teams to identify and understand challenges and opportunities and deliver organisation wide insights to help accelerate robust decision making, drive consistency and enable self-service for the business. 

In your role, you will migrate & transform data, creating views that can be utilised across our business. You will facilitate the use of data within the data team as well as allowing the benefits of data to be liberated across the organisation and within our digital transformation. 

At Specsavers, we believe in adopting a hybrid approach to support our people and the future of work. When not working from an alternative location, you will be based at our support office in Port Melbourne. 

 

What we are looking for

  • An inquisitive nature with a passion for learning and growth 
  • Tertiary qualifications in Computing, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, Statistics or a relevant area of study related to computer/data sciences
  • Expertise in scripting with SQL, Python or Pyspark and sound knowledge of CI/CD
  • Good technical ability and understanding of how big data platforms work, as well as the use of data development software (ETL packages) and programming languages (usually SQL and Python) to develop tools to extract, transform and load data, as well as to document the creation of these tools. 
  • Excellent communication skills as you will need to discuss technical principles and business processes in simple language to people at all levels. 
  • Good understanding of spark processing clusters and use of ganglia to monitor performance and troubleshoot issues. 
  • Experience with the below or similar tools and technology:  
    • Azure Data Lake 
    • Azure Data Factory 
    • Azure Databricks (inc. SQL and Python) 
    • Azure SQL Server  
    • Power BI Premium
    • Azure DevOps/Git 

 

About Us

At Specsavers we believe a diverse, inclusive and flexible culture enables our people to bring their whole selves to work and be proud of doing so. When it comes to flexibility, we understand that one size doesn't fit all. Our flexible working at Specsavers enables us to work in ways that support our lifestyle to help us balance our career with the other important things in life

Creating a great place to work for our people is pinnacle to us and along with our Behaviours is at the core of everything we do, ensuring our people feel good, cared for and smart. We like to think it’s a fun and positive place to work – why not have a look for yourself https://join.specsavers.com/au/department/support-office/ 
 
Applicants for the role are required to have current working rights as per, relevant government legislation.

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Come join us, discover a world of opportunity at a time you can be a part of a global network and have a meaningful impact in the healthcare industry.
job.content:
Healthcare Logic 

 

Data Engineer

ABOUT US

Healthcare Logic is one of Queensland’s fastest growing technology start-ups, and we are aiming for global market leadership within the next three-five years.  We build software to help hospitals work better.  Come join us and discover a world of opportunity at a time you can be a part of a global network and have a meaningful impact in the healthcare industry.

We are currently transacting in five jurisdictions.  Our flagship product is SystemView: a new-to-the-world analytics platform using high-frequency data automation and a proprietary UI to give clinical and executive leaders in hospitals previously unobtainable insights and actionable data.  We currently have a global headcount of c.90 and growing!

To continue building out our data engineering team, we are looking for committed and motivated individuals to join us at an exciting time of rapid expansion.  The successful candidate will have technical experience combining both a good working knowledge of database architecture, design, and approaches to integration (with focused knowledge of SQL), and significant devops experience as well as familiarity with version control software such as Git and Redgate.

 

ABOUT THE ROLE

You will be joining a multi-talented and diverse team of data engineers with the below responsibilities:

  • Assist in designing and implementing ETL pipelines across a range of technologies and working with clients to integrate pipelines with their source systems
  • Assist in development and optimisation of a next-generation analytics platform that utilises numerous data sources
  • Assist in extracting and transforming data to support new analyses supported by high-frequency, highly granular data flows
  • Help and develop reusable code and libraries for future use
  • Maintain an in-depth understanding of technologies and stay abreast of current industry trends and emerging technologies
  • Passionate to learn new technology and willing to go beyond your comfort zone

ESSENTIAL SKILLS:

These skills and experience will help get you onto the shortlist:

  • A degree in Computer Science or similar, or ability to demonstrate equivalent knowledge in database development
  • Graduate to 1 – 2 years' experience with exposure to data in the context of application development, data warehousing, migration, or data analysis
  • A high-level of motivation and demonstrable ability to solve complex problems and deliver solutions under tight timelines
  • The ability to help develop a suite of databases that will support a cutting-edge web application
  • Good understanding and some experience with SQL Server Integration Services or other ETL tools
  • Exposure to SQL Server 2016 
  • Exposure to Healthcare data preferred but not essential
  • Exposure with Azure services desired
  • Exposure writing automated tests for data pipelines
  • Good understanding and exposure with one or more database engines, including MySQL, Postgres, MS SQL, etc...
  • Be a critical thinker with strong analytical and problem-solving skills
  • Be passionate about delivering high quality work
  • Prior experience with application or web development working in fast-paced agile and exposure to modern technology, frameworks, and tools such as Scrum, Test Driven Development, React, Redgate, NodeJS, CI/CD and Docker are also of interest

 

Job benefits and perks

  • Join a team at the cutting edge of Healthcare analytics to improve patient outcomes worldwide
  • Solve interesting real-world problems in a dynamic environment
  • Attractive salary 
  • Work within a global team and collaborate internationally
  • Option of in-office days on the Gold Coast and remote working options available
  • We have a modern office space with awesome ocean views in Southport on the Gold Coast
  • Annual all expenses paid trip to the Gold Coast for anyone recruited outside south-east QLD
  • Join us now for the opportunity to grow and expand with the Company

If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged, and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

Why Your Role Matters:

As a Senior Data Engineer with UNSW Planning and Performance, you will assist in the planning, coordination and delivery of the Azure data platform infrastructure and end to end development of the Azure Data Lake.

As a Senior Data Engineer, you will work closely with the Senior Manager, Data Platforms to support the delivery of complex projects, system enhancements and business process improvements whilst working closely with colleagues and UNSW stakeholders to ensure quality service delivery.

As a Senior Data Engineer, you will provide subject matter expertise and advice as well as manage and participate in system integration and performance testing to ensure system integrity. You will have the opportunity to provide leadership in projects and proactively identify areas of business improvement through analysis methodologies.

The Senior Data Engineer reports to the Senior Manager, Data Platforms, and has one direct report.

 

Who You Are:

Candidates should be able to demonstrate experience in the use of PySpark or Python in addition to possessing and demonstrating:

  • Relevant tertiary qualifications or an equivalent level of knowledge gained through any other combination of education, training, and experience.
  • Strong technical and computing skills (specifically including Office 365, MS Excel, and databases), with excellent attention to detail as well as strong technical ability in the use of SQL, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, Python, Pyspark and presentation skills in data visualisation and presentation tools (e.g., Power BI). Experience in Delta Lake development would be desirable.
  • Demonstrated experience coordinating and delivering on strategic activities in a complex environment, ideally within higher education.
  • High level project management, analysis, research, planning and advisory skills and experience, combined with creative problem-solving skills.
  • Proven ability to establish highly effective and collaborative working relationships and initiate change using high level interpersonal, influencing, and written and verbal communication skills.
  • Advanced project management skills with the ability to manage multiple concurrent complex projects (end to end), and provide high-level advice and review and re-engineer complex systems and processes.
  • Demonstrated high level critical thinking and analytical skills.

Further details on this role can be found in a copy of the Position Description linked below or via JOBS@UNSW.

 

Benefits and Culture:

Some of the great benefits of working with UNSW are detailed in the link below. These include but not limited to:

•              Flexible Working Options (work from home, flexible hours etc)

•              Career development opportunities

•              17% Superannuation contributions and additional leave loading payments

•              Additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period

•              Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness)

 

For further details on the benefits, please visit

https://www.jobs.unsw.edu.au/lifestyle-benefits

 

How to Apply:

Make It Matter… Apply Now by clicking ‘Apply’ below and submit your application

(Please note applicants must have full working rights in Australia)

 

Submit your application online before Tuesday 28th February 2023 at 11:55pm

 

Get in Touch:

Chris Haywood, UNSW Talent Coordinator

chris.haywood@unsw.edu.au

Please note applications sent directly to the contact above cannot be accepted.

 

UNSW is committed to evolving a culture that embraces equity and supports a diverse and inclusive community where everyone can participate fairly, in a safe and respectful environment. We welcome candidates from all backgrounds and encourage applications from people of diverse gender, sexual orientation, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander background, people with disability and those with caring and family responsibilities. UNSW provides workplace adjustments for people with disability, and access to flexible work options for eligible staff.

 

The University reserves the right not to proceed with any appointment.

job.title: IT Systems & Data Specialist
job.abstract: We're looking for an IT and data all-rounder to really make a difference to our team.
job.content:
Are you an all-rounder who wants variety in their role?

  • Permanent full-time role with growing business
  • Great team, Mitcham location (amd able to work from home)
  • This is a stand-alone role that can really make a difference to our team.

 

WHO ARE WE?

We’re Australia’s leader in environmental monitoring and provider of emission monitoring systems.  We care about the environment and by joining us you’ll make a difference.

We’re diverse – we have a fabulous team from all parts of the globe and varying backgrounds working in our locations in VIC, WA, NSW and QLD.

 

WHAT YOU’LL DO

You’ll be the backbone to our organisation, providing IT systems and data solutions to meet and improve the needs of the business.  We’re after a curious innovative and resourceful technology expert to help us make the most valuable impact.

You’ll be responsible for:

Digital / IT System Management: 

  • Source, deploy and administrate software platforms and digital solutions that make a difference. 
  • Maintaining continuity of IT services and manage/monitor cyber-security. 
  • Infrastructure optimisation. 
  • Provide general IT support to our team including onboarding/offboarding users. 
  • Developing/improving digital templates/forms/database/tools formats for all operations. 
  • Implementing changes to the business and providing training, documentation and monitoring tools.

 Data management/analysis: 

  • Database development and management.
  • Data expertise – getting the most out of our data, and connecting the dots for informed decision-making. 

 

WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR

Someone with energy and passion, who wants some variety in their role.  You’ll need to bring:

  • A continuous improvement mindset – we want to keep evolving.
  • Sound understanding of computer, network, and data security principles.
  • Ability to effectively communicate with well-developed analytical and problem-solving skills.
  • Experience in a similar autonomous/stand alone IT role will be beneficial.

Technical capability:

  • Demonstrated experience administering and working with Virtual Windows Server environments, including Azure Active Directory and Microsoft O365.
  • Reporting/data management – PowerBI.
  • Microsoft Power Automate.
  • SQL knowledge. 
  • Modbus protocols / data communication expertise. 
  • VBA (primarily for Excel application).

 

OUR VALUES

Our values are Responsibility, Integrity, Care, Excellence and Enjoyment, Integrity and Responsibility.  If these values resonate with you then we’d love to hear from you. Join us and help us achieve great things as a team.

This is a full-time position with an immediate start available.

 

Sound like you?

Then we’d love to hear from you by submitting a copy of your cv and a cover letter addressing the above criteria. 

Applications close March 17 however we will be reviewing applications as they are received as we're keen to move forward.

  • You must be an Australian citizen or have Australian working rights to apply for this role.
  • Submissions from recruitment agencies will not be accepted. 
  • If you have any queries please email hr@ektimo.com.au

job.title: Data Analyst - Retail Analytics
job.abstract: Supporting the growth of Endeavour by providing meaningful insights to support decisions and outcomes for customers and stakeholders
job.content:
About the Opportunity

Retail Analytics spans the whole business: we support merchandise and supply teams, understand customer behaviour and support our market-share strategies.
Our remit is to ensure we're supporting the growth of Endeavour by providing meaningful insights to support decisions and outcomes for customers and stakeholders across our retail and online environments.

The Data Analyst is responsible for supporting our merchandising and strategy teams which will see you supporting end-to-end analytical projects and delivering to stakeholders with a key focus on strong insights and actions for business use.

We're looking for someone who isn't afraid of the unknown: is ready to learn, can ask the right questions, get deep into data, explain findings to stakeholders and work as part of a well-rounded team of analysts.

A day in the life of a Data Analyst - Retail Analytics

  • Providing ongoing and ad hoc reporting, analysis and insights in a timely manner
  • Focus on the insights (aka ‘so what') from ongoing and ad hoc analysis, defining the narrative and identifying actions and opportunities
  • Establish strong relationships with business stakeholders to become their trusted advisor and partner
  • Work within team norms, standards and procedures to provide consistency across the business
  • Support and drive the development of great team dynamics
  • Learn and be proactive with ideas and recommendations and help drive the business outcomes
  • Document your pathways: champion the role of solid data governance, create data lineage assets and create meaningful documentation for your stakeholders and peers
  • Thrive and grow within our team norms, standards and procedures to provide consistency across the business and with peers
  • Keep learning: stay up up to date with knowledge of current trends up to date to ensure our solutions remain in line with industry best practice

As our successful candidate you will form part of the Retail Analytics team within the broader Endeavour Advanced Analytics team. You will have had relevant experience in a similar role where you have supported key stakeholders to deliver insights and support decisions, as well as having worked across data visualisation and insights.

What You'll Need to Succeed

  • Tertiary qualification or equivalent in a relevant field (Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Analytics)
  • Have a minimum of 2 years hands on analytics experience
  • Strong SQL skills
  • Ability to handle large and complex data sets using different applications and an understanding of databases
  • Experience in technical operations working with Cloud technologies (GCP, Azure, DBT)
  • Data visualisation and storytelling experience (Tableau, Data Studio)
  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills
  • Ability to work with large and complex data sets using different applications
  • Hold a strong focus on delivery and the right attitude and approach towards any challenges
  • Analytically inquisitive - identifies opportunities to find root causes

What's in it for you?

  • Excellent remuneration package and flexible working in every sense. We value our people
  • The opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia
  • Training and Education - we pride ourselves in helping you realise your potential and give you the opportunity to be innovative leveraging great partnerships we have with Google, Microsoft and others
  • Career progression to help you realise your potential. As our business grows so do the opportunities for our people
  • Innovative environment working with the latest and greatest tools and technology on the market. Upskill in Cloud technologies. Work with an industry-leading team and be a part of one of the most exciting retail transformations in Australia
  • Everyday Rewards plus card - access exclusive employee discounts across Woolworths, BigW and Endeavour Group brands (BWS, Dan Murphy's etc) and 50% off food at ALH venues.
  • Our innovative ways of working include headspace mornings once a month (no meetings company-wide)

Grow with Endeavour Group

Bring your spark. Tap into our spirit. That's the power of Endeavour.

If you want to experience the diverse spirit of drinks and hospitality businesses, here you can tap into Australia's leading brands including Dan Murphy's, BWS, ALH, Pinnacle Drinks, Endeavour X and more.

If you have a passion for connecting people with products they love, here you can join an industry that's deeply embedded in the way Australians socialise, unwind and celebrate.

If you want access to a breadth of career opportunities, here you can enjoy a path that travels between diverse roles and businesses within the Group.

If you're already asking ‘what's next for me' and our industry, here you'll thrive.

If you want to bring your full self to doing fulfilling work, here you'll find a culture that's welcoming, inclusive and responsible.

If you are looking for flexibility, here we encourage our team members to work in ways that meets their work / life commitments and supports their wellbeing.

Come grow with Endeavour where we are passionate about our purpose of creating a more sociable future together, and leaving a positive imprint on our team members and the communities we serve.

If you meet a number of the requirements, but not all, we encourage you to submit your application.

You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn [link removed] or via www.wowcareers.com.au/endeavour/ [link removed] #EGL #EDG #NSWJOBSCONNECT

Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

My client promotes a hardworking, open-minded, and passionate culture, crafting phenomenal results and delivering real value for their customers.   • Significant experience designing/architecting complex systems

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Looking for someone with great SQL skills and experience with Azure
job.content:
The Data Engineer will design, build, and integrate data from multiple sources to prepare a trusted data infrastructure that supports our data and analytics capabilities. This position develops the processes for data acquisition, transformation, migration, verification, modelling, and mining. This position also implements the data systems that drive machine learning and artificial intelligence.

Ideally we're after someone with current/recent use of SQL at a high skill level and experience SSIS and Azure. 

Role is available in -  Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane and Adelaide.
 
What you'll be doing:
  • Collaborate with the data and analytics team to develop and maintain a data pipeline and infrastructure using a range of different storage technologies that enables optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from multiple data sources.
  • Develop and maintain scalable data platforms through various integration patterns, including APIs and quality frameworks that support continual increases in data volume and complexity.
  • Assemble large, complex data sets that meet both functional and non-functional business requirements.
  • Support the development of processes and standards for data mining, data modelling and data protection.
  • Prepare raw data for manipulation and analysis by the Data Scientist.
  • Build analytic tools that identify patterns and trends to deliver insights that can inform effective business decisions.
  • Build analytical tools that support the Data Scientist in making recommendations to build and optimise innovative products and services.
  • Design and implement continuous process improvements for automating manual processes and optimising data delivery.
  • Assess and report on the unique data needs of key stakeholders and troubleshoot any data[1]related technical issues through to resolution.
  • Work with the broader data and analytics team to improve data models that support business intelligence tools, improve data accessibility and foster data-driven decision making.
  • Implement systems and processes to monitor and improve data quality, ensuring production data is always accurate and available for key stakeholders and business processes that depend on it.
  • Continually research and recommend ways to improve data reliability, quality, and use.
  • Collaborate with the Data Scientist and project teams to develop new ideas, data products and solutions that optimise and automate business processes including the design, build and deployment of artificial intelligence solutions.
  • Work across the Agile environment to continually deliver value through analytical projects, artificial intelligence solutions and automation.
  • Monitor data assets, data products, artificial intelligence and automated solutions for ongoing effectiveness and maintenance requirements.
  • Implement and maintain data-related disaster recovery procedures.
 
What you need to bring:
  • Bachelor’s Degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics, Actuary, or a similar related field.
  • Minimum 4 years of experience as a Data Engineer designing, building, and optimising data pipelines, architecture, and data sets.
  • Extensive experience in building processes supporting data transformation, data structures and the manipulation, processing, and extraction of value from datasets.
  • Extensive experience using R, SQL, Python, Scala, and Java.
  • Extensive experience in machine learning, data mining, mathematics and statistical modelling and analysis.
  • Extensive experience in pattern recognition and predictive modelling.
  • Experience with data pipeline and workflow management tools, and Cloud data platforms.
  • Experience working with a Map Reduce, Hadoop or an MPP system of any size/scale.
  • Knowledge of data platform concepts such as data lakes, data warehousing, big data processing, real time processing architecture, scheduling, and monitoring of ETL/ELT workflows.
  • Knowledge of relational databases such as SQL Server and Oracle as well as the use of NoSQL databases.
  • Knowledge of Agile Software Development methodologies.
  • Knowledge of website scripts such as XML, JavaScript and JSON.
  • Strong organising and prioritising skills with the ability to work across multiple projects simultaneously.
  • Strong process orientation with solid documentation skills.
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, particularly relating to unstructured datasets.
 
You can apply directly on here or email don@inviewconsulting.com.au

West Technology is proud to be partnering with a large Australian business that is at the forefront of an industry that is currently being disrupted by new technologies and environmental impact. 
This business is leading the industry within this space and has invested significantly in the latest enterprise level technologies to ensure it’s position as the industry leader.
As an employer, this business values its’ people and offers programs to upskill and develop their workforce with a strong preference to promote from within.
  
About Your New Role 
 
Working within the Data & Analytics function, the Data Engineer will have direct experience working with all aspects of company data with an emphasis on data warehouse management, data extraction, cleansing and sound governance & data hygiene.
  
The key tasks include:

  • Participate in the design and ongoing management of company databases
  • Oversee compliance and data governance including security requirements
  • Maintain an up-to-date knowledge of current industry trends, advancements in technologies and data management concepts.
About You!

Sound Interesting? Contact Dean Mumford on 0450 901035 to find out if this exciting job opportunity is for you.

Why Collar?
Here at Collar, our focus is to “Recruit a better way” and we are doing just that.
Australian-owned and established in 2021 we have grown our business and have not only been voted the best place to work but a one-of-a-kind company making a difference. Here at Collar, we provide 24/7 helplines, welcome gift packs, training, and expert knowledge from experienced consultants.

Who we're looking for: 
Someone who can help lead specialised Data Transformation projects under the supervision of the IT & Data Governance Team, and work closely with key stakeholders, the Chief Data Strategist and subject matter experts.

The work being undertaken includes Data Services, including Data Modelling, Data Architecture and Reporting, particularly in transforming analytics to the Azure cloud. Gather requirements, create conceptual, logical, prototype and physical data models, and support the development and maintenance of the underlying architecture.
 
The data models will be developed in Azure Analysis Services through Azure Synapse Analytics and Data Factory, and a business reporting platform will be created through Power BI. All processes will need to be documented. 
 
These services will be provided to business teams to facilitate ongoing reporting and analysis by subject matter experts. It increases efficiencies for staff who need to access data. The broader framework will support data strategy, and provide a consultation prototype for the Chief Data Strategist as they move to implement changes in data governance, access and reporting.

What you will need:
  • Strong knowledge of SQL database and Microsoft Azure platform
  • Data warehouse and data modelling experience e.g., Star schema
  • Solid experience in developing complex ETLs based on SSIS
  • Experience in working with Azure Data Lake
  • Experience in designing and implementing MS SSAS solutions i.e., tabular
  • Experience in BI tools
  • Strong understanding of Azure DevOps or other version control systems
  • Excellent communication skills
  • Tertiary qualification is desirable (e.g., TOGAF)
Sound like you? please email adam.webber@collar.group for more information or to setup a confidential chat.

The Smith Family is a children's education charity that helps young Australians experiencing disadvantage to create better futures for themselves through harnessing the power of education.

We are looking for a hands-on Data Engineer/Developer to join the TSF Technology team. As the Data Engineer, you will be responsible for developing, and maintaining data pipelines extracting from multiple sources and loading to the enterprise Datawarehouse as well as providing Analytics and Reporting solutions to meet the business' analytics and reporting needs.

About our role

  • Create and support data pipelines that extract data from multiple sources and load it into a central data warehouse.
  • Work with stakeholders to understand business requirements and design data models and reports to meet those requirements.
  • Optimize and improve existing data pipelines to ensure high performance and reliability.
  • Develop and maintain data quality checks to ensure the accuracy and completeness of data.
  • Continuously monitor and maintain data pipelines to ensure they are running smoothly and identify areas for improvement.
  • Create visualisations with tools like Power BI to provide insights to business areas.
  • Collaborate with business and technology stakeholders in ensuring our solutions are fit for purpose and improve utilization.
  • Maintain high quality code, best practice code development and version control processes.

About you

  • Strong MS SQL, SSIS and Data warehousing background
  • 1-2 years of MS Azure Cloud experience working with Azure Synapse, AAS, SQL MI, Data Factory, Data Flows, and related Microsoft Azure technologies
  • Understanding of Data Warehousing concepts data and modelling techniques
  • Experience building visualisations and paginated reports in Power BI
  • Strong analytical data skills and proven ability to resolve complex data problems using technology solutions
  • Good verbal and written communication skills with technical and non-technical audiences
  • Predictive Data Analytics - ability to model data and create reports that can answer specific business questions
  • Coding experience with Python, Scala

About our culture

The Smith Family has employees at the centre of its values and operations. We nurture a supportive and inclusive culture that enables people to achieve personal and professional goals, through collaboration and innovation. With a proven work-life balance, wellbeing and health are our top priorities. Enjoy many other benefits, such as tax concessions and flexible working arrangements.

For any other information, please contact Minu Ganesh, Data Platform Manager at Minu.Ganesh@thesmithfamily.com.au

Due to the nature of this role, the successful candidate must be prepared to undertake a National Police Check and a Working with Children's Check. We are an equal opportunity employer and are committed to principles of cultural diversity. Applications from people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander descent are encouraged.

The Smith Family is obligated to comply with Federal, State and Territory Government Rules and Health Orders. For roles that fall under Health Orders, to be eligible applicants will either need to provide proof of Vaccination or a Medical exemption.

job.title: Lead Engineer - Insights - Hawthorn East
job.abstract: We are embarking on the delivery of key data initiatives, building them using market leading cloud technologies
job.content:
We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

About the team

As the way we shop continues to evolve, our Digital team keeps us at the cutting edge. Driven by our innovative, inclusive and forward-thinking culture, we're constantly looking at ways to reinvent the shopping experience for our customers and build the next generation of digital retailing.

The Insights Team within the broader Coles Technology Team focuses on building data collection and analytics capabilities to uncover customer, product, and operational insights. Providing data driven support to our users and enabling Coles to be a data driven organisation.

About the role

We are embarking on engineering, enablement, operations, and delivery of key data initiatives, building them using market leading cloud technologies including Azure DevOps, Azure Data Factory, and Databricks.

The Technical Lead designs engineering solutions and ensures all parts of the technical design are correctly incorporated to provide technical support and technical quality control throughout all stages of the project.

You will mentor and guide teams to achieving great outcomes and maturing their capabilities, as well as overseeing all aspects of project deliverables including architecture and design to ensure all parts technical design are strategically aligned.

In addition, you will gather technical requirements and provide effort estimates and delivery timelines, as well as develop and deliver projects within the agreed timeframes and budgets. The role will also provide weekly status reports to management and other stakeholders.

You'll also:

  • Resolve technical issues and ensure all parts of the technical design are correctly incorporated
  • Provide technical support and technical quality control throughout all stages of the projects
  • Oversee all aspects of project deliverables including architecture and design to ensure quality and strategic alignment
  • Gather technical requirement and provide effort estimate and delivery timelines
  • Design, develop, and deliver projects with high quality within the agreed timeframes and budgets

About you and your skills

We are looking for a dedicated and experienced Technical Lead with experience in managing the end-to-end project delivery and leading data solutions within both on-premises and cloud-based environment.

You will have previous experience in a similar role, offering ongoing support to functional and technical stakeholders working in a large, complex and data driven organisation.

You'll also need:

  • Understanding of business intelligence & analytics applications within corporate environments
  • Previous experience of leading small to medium sized teams.
  • Good understanding of retail domain
  • Deep understanding of data warehousing architectures and software engineering principles
  • Experience in on-prem databases such as Oracle, SQL and Cloud databases such as Snowflake
  • Previously worked in at least one of these cloud technologies: Azure or AWS
  • Proficiency in data pipelining, distributed data processing, software engineering components and data modelling concepts
  • Exposure to CI/CD pipelines using a tech stack of Git and Azure
  • Exposure to Data Factory and Databrick highly regarded but not essential

Take your next step into something bigger, apply now

With us it's not about the discounts (although you do get those), it's about joining a team where your wellbeing and professional development is invested in and celebrating your contributions is the norm. And because everyone leads unique lives, we offer flexible work including work from home, additional leave and parental leave entitlements.

We're continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that's just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We're happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. Find out more in the ‘Our Recruitment Process' section [link removed] of our careers site.

Safer together

We're committed to providing a safe environment for our team members and our customers. As part of that commitment, you will need to be vaccinated against COVID-19 before joining the team at Coles, unless you're medically exempt. You'll also need to disclose your COVID-19 vaccination status as part of your application (and possibly provide further evidence of your vaccination status). Thanks for applying, and for your understanding.
