This is a fantastic opportunity for someone who is passionate about big data technologies, enjoys solving problems, and takes pride in delivering high-quality solutions. To propel your data career to the next level you will work closely with senior stakeholders across the business and take a lead role in Data Architecture.

job.title: Engineer (Open Banking) - ANZPlus
job.abstract: ANZPlus BETA has landed! We're looking for Engineers to deliver MLP and impact millions of customers with products build in Golang, GCP/AWS.
job.content:
Company description:

ANZ Banking Group Limited



Job description:

What is ANZPlus?

At ANZPlus, our purpose is to provide the tools, supports and insights our customers need to improve their financial well-being. We've already released our first product - the ANZ Plus app. Our new app makes it easier for our customers to both manage and save their money.

You won't need to worry about outdated enterprise tech here. At ANZPlus, we are 100% cloud-based, write most of our code in Go and deploy to production daily.

We're an Engineering lead business, so our technology leaders have all progressed their careers through the engineering pathway, to create a best practise, engineering culture of ongoing improvement and provides the perfect environment for you to develop and learn new and in demand skills.

What is the Open Banking Team?

Open Banking is a Consumer Data Standard that gives consumers the ability to and control over sharing their data between multiple organisations. At ANZPlus, we are working on two Open Banking related capabilities: Data Out and Data In.

For Data In, we provide standardised APIs that allow other organisations to access ANZ customer data given the correct consent is provided.

For Data Out, we ingest data from other holders of financial data with our customers consent to support experiences in the ANZ Plus App.

The Open Banking team is divided into cross-functional squads focussing on Data Out and Data In respectively.

Our Technology Stack

• Go
• Temporal for workflow management
• ForgeRock for consent management

• GCP

  • GKE

  • Cloud Run

  • Spanner & CloudSQL

  • PubSub

  • BigQuery

• GitHub Actions

What will your typical day look like?

You will work in a small squad responsible for building and improving our data out compliance for open banking; this involves the end-to-end delivery of features, including planning, design, and implementation.

We believe in empowering our engineers to solve problems autonomously and build well-engineered solutions, and as a greenfield program of work, our codebase is brand new - no legacy or spaghetti code.

We have automated testing, deployments and monitoring in place, which makes it easy to release changes and keep our systems running optimally.

With a flexible approach to working, and keeping meetings to a minimum, you can focus on solving complex problems with your squad mates. Planning and communication is asynchronous using Slack, GitHub as well as face-to-face both virtually and in person.

What are we looking for?

  • Passion for technology - you keep abreast of the latest developments and care deeply about creating well-engineered solutions

  • Proficiency in one or more backend programming languages, such as Go, Java, C#, Node.js or Python

  • Some experience with Docker and/or Kubernetes

  • Some experience with cloud-based development using either AWS, GCP or Azure

  • Analytical thinking: be able to break down complex, messy problems into clear, well-articulated ideas and plans

  • Communication: good written communication skills for writing issues, documentation and asynchronous design discussions.

So, why join us?

At ANZ, everything we do boils down to ‘why' - our purpose - to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We're just as focused on seeing our people thrive as well as our customers. We'll give you every opportunity to develop your career. We are responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter the most, energising our people, eliminating waste and reducing bureaucracy.

A happy workplace is a thriving one. So, in order to attract and keep the best talent, and say thanks for the hard work, we make sure all our employees are rewarded. We work flexibly at ANZ and encourage you to talk to us about how this role can be flexible for you and any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you are a candidate with a disability, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.

Job Posting End Date

, 11.59pm, (Melbourne Australia)

job.title: ICT Infrastructure Manager
job.abstract: The RNA Showgrounds has an exciting opportunity within our ICT Department
job.content:
Here at the Royal National Agricultural and Industrial Association of Queensland (RNA) we are experiencing a period of exceptional growth post COVID that is transforming our iconic establishment into a state of the art precinct. Home to the Royal Queensland Show (Ekka), as well as an array of cultural events - our transformation has seen the Brisbane Showgrounds becoming the hub of a new mixed-use precinct with the centrepiece being the Five Star Royal International Convention Centre (Royal ICC).

 

Reporting to the ICT Systems Manager, the ICT Infrastructure Manager will be responsible for the corporate ICT environment of the RNA. Working with a small diverse and motivated ICT team with a can do attitude this role has the broad responsibility for setting strategy and hands on management of the RNA Microsoft Server and office desktop environment, Microsoft 365 Applications and Azure Cloud environment. This is an excellent opportunity to identify and execute continuing improvement projects in this dynamic events driven environment.

 

What we offer…

The RNA is a traditional organisation with a progressive mindset towards employee benefits, we offer 5 weeks of annual leave a year, 5 days of Wellness Leave a year, Free Parking on site, team building lunches and award-winning food sampling throughout the year.

 

What you will be responsible for…

  • Manage the RNA’s Azure based and physical infrastructure equipment and systems including servers, PC’s, peripherals to maximize uptime, protection of data and compliance with policy and best practice.
  • Administer and manage server environment running Microsoft Hyper-V Cluster
  • On premise Windows Server environment (Software & Hardware)
  • Management and operation of data backup
  • Microsoft 365 environment management and support
  • Azure infrastructure management
  • Workstation environment (Software & Hardware)
  • Creation and deletion of user accounts and access configuration
  • Management of ICT supply contracts
  • Develop and maintain RNA ICT policies

 

What you will need…

  • Minimum 3-5 year’s experience in an ICT Infrastructure role.
  • Ability to lead by example and to work effectively within a busy team environment
  • Knowledge and experience using Microsoft Operating Systems and Office products and a variety of PC applications.
  • Effective verbal communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to liaise with people at all levels in an accurate and positive manner. 
  • Customer service focus and genuine desire to assist team members. 
  • Ability to organise and plan work to achieve deadlines and outcomes. 
  • Demonstration of initiative to assist within the team and be proactive in completing tasks.

 

How to Apply:

To be considered for this role, press the “Apply now” button on Seek and please ensure you include a one-page Cover Letter addressing the above selection criteria and your current Resume in your application.

 

Applications close: COB Tuesday 7th March 2023

Please note that depending on the volume of applications received we may not be able to respond to all. However, all applications submitted will be thoroughly reviewed to assess suitability for the position.

 

Please note we may interview candidates before the closing date.

job.abstract: Data Engineer required to assist in replacing Customer Information Systems. Tech stack: Oracle, AWS/Azure, ETL and Power BI.
job.content:
Our client, a large Energy Retailer, is undertaking a digital transformation towards becoming a utility of the future by implementing a fully digital system where their systems and data, and therefore their people, are better connected.
Their Digital Division provides and supports information and communications technology products, services and solutions for the business and its subsidiary companies.


The Data Engineer will be embedded in the Retail Customer Information System (RCIS) Replacement project to design, build and transition the retail data ecosystem as it transitions from current to new state. The Project Data Engineer will work in conjunction with Operational and dependant project teams to design and build systems that collect, manage, and convert raw data into usable information for data migration , data sciences and business analytics.
This role will report into the customer migration workstream lead and will work closely with the Digital and Retail businesses and the customer migration delivery partner. Collaboration with solution and enterprise architects, SecOps, Cyber, Digital platform teams will be essential to ensure successful delivery of systems.

In this role the Data Engineer will:
* Develop detailed designs
* Ensure PII security policies are implemented and auditable.
* Ensure the consistency of data across the various project and operational deliverables.
* Provide leadership and oversight on data cleansing activities


Essential Skills:
* Proven working experience as a data engineer
* Understanding of Data Migration ETL Process
* Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques
* Analyse Legacy Data Models to determine attribute usage/business purpose
* Knowledge of Oracle and Microsoft SQL Server (PL-SQL and T-SQL) and Python
* Build AWS and/or Azure infrastructure to support data migration activities
* Build and design interim and target state data repositories
* Knowledge and experience designing and deploying big data technologies such as DataBricks
* Mapping of current state data models to target state
* Demonstrated experience in supporting data cleansing activities
* Proven experience in ensuring data integrity in a phased data migration approach

job.title: Data Engineering Lead
job.abstract: Join a growing healthcare company with 3,000+ employees. Take lead in delivering our Azure Data Platform using modern technologies. At Icon, You Can.
job.content:
Icon Group is Australia’s largest dedicated cancer care provider and has expanded globally into Singapore, Mainland China, Hong Kong and New Zealand. We are built on a strong but simple vision – to deliver the best care possible, to as many people as possible, as close to home as possible. 
 
With more than 3,000 employees company-wide, we bring together all aspects of quality cancer care, including medical oncology, radiation oncology, haematology, pharmacy and chemotherapy compounding to deliver a true end-to-end seamless service for cancer patients internationally.
 
As we continue to grow, what we do matters to more and more people every day. Each role at Icon holds a strong contribution to the care provided. And when you choose a career with Icon, you help change people’s lives for the better.
  
Here’s what our people said what it takes to succeed and love life at Icon Group
  • You’ll truly want to work together towards our ambitious vision and goals
  • You’ll embrace and enjoy pace, progress, and change – we rarely sit still for long
  • You’ll need a serious work ethic and a thirst for job satisfaction that sees you putting up your hand to grab opportunities
A few of our benefits 
  • Discounts and cashback on hundreds of brands through our internal ignite app
  • Flexible work arrangements, including remote working, compressed work weeks, varying start-finish times and so much more!
  • Access to novated lease options via our partner RemServ
  • Access to paid parental leave
  • Access to our Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
  • Professional development
The opportunity

Due to business growth we’re looking to grow our Data & Analytics team. As a Data Engineering Lead on a permanent full-time basis based in our South Brisbane head office, you’ll join a truly connected and talented team who are passionate about delivering positive outcomes so that we’re providing the best possible patient care. 
  
Working directly with the business, you’ll build and maintain our Azure Data Platform and a range of data products to support decision-making across the business. You’ll help to establish and drive a self-service capability by maturing our cloud platform to support operational reporting as well as ad-hoc experimentation and analytics. And you’ll take the lead in developing both the Azure Data Platform and the data products that leverage it, while sharing knowledge and strengthening the capabilities of the team.
  
Key responsibilities
  • Lead the design and delivery of our Azure Data Platform to enable the Icon Group business to leverage our data assets
  • Support the on-boarding of new data sets into the platform
  • Architect and develop a range of data products which put the right information in front of the right people at the right time
  • Work with DevOps and Platform Engineers to build, automate, standardise, and streamline the rapid deployment of consistent, high-quality solutions
  • Work in close partnership with the business to design and develop data models
  • Build highly optimised, resilient, scalable data pipelines
  • Research innovative techniques and contribute to the development of leading practices around data
  • Work with product delivery teams to provision data to support use cases
About you
  • Bachelors degree with a relevant focus
  • Significant experience developing data ingestion solutions in the Azure ecosystem – Data Factory, Data Bricks, Synapse, Data Lake
  • Experience designing and developing data models across a range of functional areas
  • Experience in data profiling, facilitating business-led data cleansing, and Data Quality frameworks
  • Experience with CI/CD process and tools and sound knowledge of software engineering principles
  • Self-motivated individual able to effectively prioritise
  • Ability to build strong working relationships and a demonstrated willingness to be a team player
  • Comfortable and confident leading and facilitating data-focused workshops with the business
Excited to join us and help change people’s lives for the better? 
 
Apply Now because At Icon, You Can. 
  
Visit https://icongroup.global/en/careers/our-people/stories/ to read the stories of our incredible people. 
 
Icon Group celebrates diversity and is committed to creating an inclusive workplace for all employees. We encourage applications from all diverse backgrounds.

job.abstract:
Data Operation Engineer - data engineering, modelling & data management practices. 
- ERD tools like LucidChart, EA Sparx, ERWin, ER Studio
job.content:
This Federal Government Agency is looking for a Data Operations Engineer to be responsible for the integrity of the production data utilized by the Agency employees by designing, creating and administering steps required to resolve or escalate issues that may prevent successful completion of scheduled production processes and data transfer, ensuring changes to the production environment have been reviewed and authorised.

Role Responsibilities and Duties

  • Investigate and understand data anomalies.
  • Design web-based tools for business process management and automation.
  • Support the data requirements of the different business areas and processes including data management, governance, quality, architecture, enterprise modelling, security and integration.
  • Supports daily operational tasks.
  • Analyses impact of proposed solutions to the business requirements, data integrity and quality.
  • Monitors and ensures operating integrity.
  • Provides recommendations on systems and business process enhancements.
  • Provides operational support and recommendations during testing efforts.

Qualifications/Experience

  • Ability to scope and define data sets needed for specific use cases and identifying data gaps.
  • Ability to translate scientific insights into product decisions and work streams.
  • Flexibility to handle directional changes and moving priorities to ensure project success.
  • Knowledge and application of DMBOK data management frameworks and principals.
  • Familiarity with star schemas and data vault modelling.
  • Experience using enterprise data modelling tools (LucidChart, EA Sparx, ERWin, ER Studio, etc).
  • Capability to create Conceptual, Logical and Physical data models for a range of technological solutions, databases and pipelines at an enterprise level in accordance with prescribed data modelling standards.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, with Attribute Based Access Control and deployments for Power BI.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, using Github, CI/CD and attribute-based Access Control and deployments for Power BI
  • A demonstrated in-depth knowledge of data base infrastructure and cloud data solutions, preferably Azure suite (D365, SQL, Analysis Services, Power BI, Purview, Dataverse, Gen II data lake, Synapse, Data Factory).

Note: Candidate must be an Australian Citizen to apply.

Please apply now through the job board quoting JL580006

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Play a significant role in setting up data infrastructure, data pipelines and implementation across Cleanaway - an iconic ASX100 brand
job.content:
• Major project - Design, and implement data pipelines
  • 12 Month FTC- Full-time position – St Kilda Road, VIC
  • Supportive team environment; WFH/Office balance
  • High growth business, ASX 100 listed

  • Who we are

    When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens up a world of possibilities. Cleanaway is the largest waste management company in Australia providing sustainable waste management solutions to a range of customers including councils, small businesses, large corporate entities and government agencies to provide sustainable waste management solutions.

    The position

    Cleanaway is an essential service with environmental causes and sustainability in mind. In order to be efficient and to succeed in its good to great journey, major data sources need to be harnessed. The data landscape is vast, incorporating huge amounts of data in all different shapes and sizes: Everything form Telemetry, IoT, trucks GPS and weight-bearing loads, production lines to HR systems, ERP, sales and more; Tens of source systems and complex data challenges.

    As a Data Engineer with at least 3 years of experience under your belt as a Data Engineer/DevOps/DataOps, you will build storage, transformation and analytical solutions for the Data & Analytics team. You will be working with an experienced team to support data engineers, data scientists & data analysts in implementing data pipelines and high-quality productionisation of complex models. You will be the backbone of the Data & Analytics team and will play a significant role in delivering and implementing solutions across the company.

    You will be joining an already diverse team of talented and energetic individuals.

    Core Responsibilities:

    • Develop data analytics and reporting solutions that drive decision making and improve performance across all departments of the business.
    • Designing, implementing, optimising and managing the data infrastructure framework on Azure with an emphasis on security and reliability. Including data migration from on-prem environment.
    • Developing, implementing and managing application and user access for the Data & Analytics framework in accordance with Cleanaway Data Governance policies and IT.
    • Managing data infrastructure in a CI/CD (Continuous Integration/Continuous Development) pipeline with appropriate controls and documentation.
    • Liaise with solutions architects, data analysts, DataOps, business analysts, data scientists and other developers to ensure all deliveries are supported by the correct architectural implementation.
    • Work closely with Data Analysts, DataOps and Data Scientists to develop the Data & Analytics framework – Data Lake, Enterprise Data Warehouse solution and more
    • Comply with the procedures and processes used within the Data & Analytics team, ensuring all work undertaken is executed consistently and professionally.
    • Support building ETL pipelines supporting batch and streaming data

    Required Skills

    • Excellent communication skills
    • Experience with Python/Pyspark to build end-to-end data pipelines!
    • Understanding DBA concepts; Prior experience working in/with DevOps or Data Engineers teams; Comfortable with DevOps/SRE thinking.
    • Knowledge and experience in designing, implementing, deploying and configuring Azure resources using Azure DevOps tools and scripting languages - as required.
    • DataLake & EDW methodologies; Data analysis, data modelling, data integration, data warehousing and database design; Azure Stack
    • Understanding of GIT, post/pre-scripting and CI/CD workflow under TDD using Azure DevOps
    • Support multiple environments (Dev, UAT, Prod) and a strong understanding of SDLC concepts.
    • Knowledge of traditional ETL/ELT process and tools (Informatica, Talend, SSIS, Alteryx..)
    • Degree qualified in a relevant commercial, analytical or mathematical discipline or equivalent experience
    • Experience participating in scrum-based agile teams

    Desirable Skills:

    • Experience in multiple database technologies such as: Distributed Processing (such as Spark, Hadoop, EMR) Traditional RDBMS (such as MS SQL Server, Oracle, MySQL, PostgreSQL) MPP (such as AWS Redshift, Teradata, Snowflake, Greenplum) NoSQL (such as CosmosDB, MongoDB, DynamoDB, Cassandra, Neo4J, Titan); Strong understanding of CDC/CT/Deltas mechanisms.
    • PowerBI exposure
    • Experience with Databricks
    • Understanding of the services industry, preferably with applicable experience

    Benefits

    • High growth business ASX 100 listed
    • A leader in sustainability and renewable resources
    • Collaborative and supportive team environment
    • Competitive pay and benefits
    • Opportunity to work on integrations

    How to apply

    Cleanaway encourages and values diversity and inclusion. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people are encouraged to apply. If this sounds like the opportunity you’ve been waiting for, please forward your resume and cover letter by clicking “Apply”.

    www.cleanaway.com.au [link removed]

job.title: Senior Data Architect
job.abstract: Be a key contributor to the group technology function in BOQ Group (BOQ, ME Bank and VMA) making a valuable difference to the business.
job.content:
About the Role

The Senior Data Architect will be responsible for the delivery of data strategy across the Data Architecture team. They are responsible for managing the delivery of Data Architecture strategy and artefacts including but not limited to data models, development and supporting data architecture patterns, assist in designing and delivery of data capabilities for data platform and responsible to provide data architecture services to key programs and initiatives. The position enables architecture team to achieve the following:

  • Designing fit for purpose data solutions that enables our business and delight our customers
  • Developing, publishing, and maintaining the information architecture – current, interim and target state architecture aligned to execution roadmaps and data strategy.
  • Translate high-level business requirements into data models (Dimensional and Datavault 2.0) and appropriate metadata
  • Provide clear, continuous, and consistent data architecture support to the in-flight initiatives and to the data platforms team.
  • Strong experience with data warehouse-based solutions – design, patterns, services, and processes. Good understanding of data ingestion, storage of data, pipeline design, ETL / ELT methodology, integration patterns, data conformance / standardization and data consumption (Analytics, APIs, events, services, datamarts, data science, AI and ML use cases etc.)
  • Good understanding of at least one cloud service providers, leading cloud practices, architecture approach, services, technology, strategy, and process. Assist in execution of cloud first strategy and in designing cloud hosted solutions (preferably Azure with Databricks)
  • Defines technical direction and roadmap for cloud migrations and managing the implementation and technical solutions. Architect cloud native, hybrid, or multi-cloud solutions to meet business needs.
  • Define and maintain data architecture principles, standards, patterns, guidelines, and processes
  • Ensure proposed architecture solutions are in alignment with data architecture principles and target state strategy
  • Work with business and technology teams to understand data consumers’ needs and develop solutions to meet them
  • Evaluate and recommend emerging technologies for data management and analytics
  • Engage with relevant stakeholders in maturing the team and the data architecture practice
  • Demonstrate a relentless improvement and a continuous learning mindset
  • Provide mentoring and coaching to the team
  • Maintain strong, enduring relationships with a variety of senior level stakeholders across business areas as well as Group Technology

About you

  • Minimum 10 - 14 years of delivery and data architecture experience - growing capabilities in a large sized data team within a data architecture domain in a multi-platform, multi-technology environment
  • Experience in cloud-based data platforms – demonstrate experience with cloud based data platform implementations
  • Technical Competency - demonstrable experience with all phases of the SDLC using either Agile or Waterfall methodologies
  • Bachelor's Degree in Technology - education with data related coursework or another equivalent field; an advanced degree in any of these, or related fields is preferred.
  • Leadership and management experience is preferred
  • A sound working knowledge of existing, new, and emerging data trends - and the benefits derived from these
  • Business acumen with ability to understand and anticipate business needs to provide appropriate data architecture guidance
  • Collaboration, communication, presentation, problem solving, interpersonal, consulting, influencing and stakeholder engagement skills to build relationships at all levels.
  • A broad, enterprise-wide view of the business - and varying degrees of appreciation for strategy, organisational capabilities and enabling technologies
  • Banking experience is preferred with good knowledge of one or more of these domains – Core Banking, Mortgages, Lending, Payments, Digital, Business Banking, Regulatory reporting

About Us

BOQ is one of Australia’s leading regional banks and provides a genuine alternative for Australian financial services customers and employees. Our purpose is to create prosperity for our customers, shareholders and people through empathy, integrity and by making a difference. Our ambition is to be known as the bold challenger bank; with multi-brands that are digitally enabled with a personal touch.

BOQ is passionate about providing opportunities for you to develop your career as we continuously adapt and deliver in a transformational and collaborative environment with a strong focus on community.

BOQ’s Inclusion vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.

In 2021 BOQ Group was awarded a Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) Employer of Choice for Gender Equality citation.

Our Benefits

• Flexible working arrangements
• Discounted financial products
• Salary sacrificing options
• Paid parental leave with no minimum
• Paid volunteer days
• Purchase annual leave
• BUPA Corporate Plan
• Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
• A ‘zero tolerance’ to Domestic and Family Violence (DFV) with active support for employees experiencing DFV
• Accessible work support through various practices, systems, office adjustments
• Gym, shopping, technology and travel offers
• 5 employee diversity network groups focusing on; First Nations Reconciliation Council, EPIC (LGBTIQA+), Multicultural, Gender and Early Career.

How to Apply

To apply for this role please follow the links or apply via our Careers Page.

The Bank of Queensland is committed to diversity and an inclusive workforce. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People are encouraged to apply.

If you are successful for a role with the Bank of Queensland, it is a condition of employment that background screening is completed to ensure that the Bank complies with its obligations under the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter Terrorism Financing Act. These checks may include, but are not limited to: identity, verification, reference checks, criminal background checks, immigration checks, verification of academic qualifications, bankruptcy checks.

job.title: Senior Data Engineer
job.abstract: Come and join us as a Senior Data Engineer in our Digital and Technology team, and be part of the future of mining.
job.content:
Grow your career with Thiess

As a global business, we are proud to offer diverse and rewarding career opportunities. We are committed to Thiess being a company which supports great people to succeed, develop their careers, and feel supported to reach their highest potential. We offer a safe and inclusive work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives and where the capability of our people is key to our success.

About The Role

This is a newly created role where you will responsible for developing the Thiess Data Platform to support the growing analytical requirements of the business, employing a mature approach to ingesting, modelling, and sharing data, catering for requirements varying from Data Science to Business Analytics. You will design, develop and support data engineering solutions that are robust, observable and performant, supporting data sources across business applications, machine data, provider API’s and loT platforms.

Additionally, the role will:

  • Lead the design and implementation of data engineering products through engaging with technical and business SMEs to understand requirements, and architect appropriate solutions.
  • Design and build data structures supporting requirements ranging from high volume machine data, dimensional modelling, through to supporting machine learning projects
  • Provide high level expertise in the use of SQL, both in developing data engineering solutions, and supporting less-technical teams to effectively interact with Thiess data platforms.
  • Optimise data solutions deployed to Thiess’ cloud data platforms to improve performance and reduce cost

About You

You will have completed relevant tertiary qualifications in Computing/Computer Science or have the appropriate Technical Background and have 5+ years in Data Engineering roles, including with large, heavy-industry based organisations.

You will have substantial knowledge, experience and demonstrated achievements in architecting big-data processing systems using contemporary cloud-based technology, and working with Data Scientists to develop data solutions that drive complex algorithmic and machine learning processes. You will have expertise in the Azure data stack, with a focus on Azure Data Factory, and data lake environments build on Data Lake Store and DataBricks. You will also have extensive experience working with SQL Server data sources, and an ability to deal with a variety of data ingestion requirements across relational, streaming, and semi-structed (JSON, XML) formats.

This is a unique opportunity to build trust and influence across a our global community, representing the Thiess’ culture.

Please note that this role will be a permanent position and applications for this role will close at midnight on Monday 20 February 2023.

What Thiess Can Do for You

  • Help to grow your career, offering diverse and varied opportunities for advancement
  • Flexible working arrangements
  • Recently renovated corporate head office located in South Bank, Brisbane
  • World-class health & wellbeing programs
  • On-site gymnasium
  • Salary sacrifice options
  • A range of corporate discounts, including health insurance (Medibank), travel & retail products
  • Referral bonus program

About Us

We partner with our clients to deliver excellence in open-cut and underground mining in Australia, Asia, Africa and the Americas. For more than 80 years, we’ve operated in diverse commodities, geologies, environments and cultures. Our team uses that insight to optimise solutions for each project and create lasting value for our clients and the communities in which we live and work.

Visit our website to learn more – http://www.thiess.com [link removed]

We’re committed to safe, healthy and respectful workplaces - places where everyone matters - always.

We welcome and celebrate the differences and similarities among people, including gender, identity, ethnicity, race, heritage, sexual orientation, disability, age, culture, religion, language, appearance, parental status and education.

Please note, you will be required to complete a pre-employment medical assessment to meet Thiess' employment criteria which may also include a drug and alcohol screen.

Please get in touch with us if you require assistance applying for this position due to a disability, injury or health condition here [link removed], no other requests will be acknowledged.

How to Apply

This role is an opportunity to take the next step in your career. With our culture of recognition, development, and a stimulating and satisfying work environment, there is no better time to join Thiess.

Please click the “apply” button to apply for this role.

Permanent full-time position
Located in the South Bank precinct, Brisbane

job.content:
This large state Gov organisation is looking for a skilled Data Engineer to join their team for a large-scale project. The successful candidate will design, build, and transition the retail data ecosystem from the current to the new state. They will be working with operational and dependent project teams to collect, manage, and convert raw data into usable information for migration, sciences, and analytics. Your work is critical to ensure a seamless transition.

Responsibilities:

  • Create comprehensive designs with specific details.
  • Implement and ensure the auditability of policies that protect personally identifiable information (PII).
  • Maintain data consistency across all project and operational deliverable.
  • Lead and oversee activities related to cleaning up and improving data quality.

Required Skills:

  • Experience working in an iterative agile delivery team is highly valued, and an agile mindset and understanding of agile delivery approaches are important for this program
  • Understanding of the ETL process for data migration
  • Previous experience in contributing to architecture and design forums
  • Technical expertise in data models, database design and development, data mining, and segmentation techniques
  • Strong experience in incident, problem, and change management
  • Analyse legacy data models to determine attribute usage and business purpose
  • Knowledge of Oracle and Microsoft SQL Server (PL-SQL and T-SQL), as well as Python
  • Build AWS and/or Azure infrastructure to support data migration activities
  • Build and design interim and target state data repositories
  • Knowledge and experience in designing and deploying big data technologies such as DataBricks

issued under GGS0060 Temporary and Contracted Workers Preferred Supplier Panel

The Data Engineer will be embedded in the RCIS Replacement project to design, build and transition the retail data ecosystem as it transitions from current to new state

The Project Data Engineer will work in conjunction with Operational and dependant project teams to design and build systems that collect, manage, and convert raw data into usable information for data migration , data sciences and business analytics.

This role will report into the customer migration workstream lead and will work closely with the Digital and Retail businesses and the customer migration delivery partner.

Collaboration with solution and enterprise architects, SecOps, Cyber, Digital platform teams will be essential to ensure successful delivery of systems.

    1. Requirements

In this role the Data Engineer will:

job.title: Senior Data Architect
job.abstract: Be a key contributor to the group technology function in BOQ Group (BOQ, ME Bank and VMA) making a valuable difference to the business.
job.content:
About the Role

The Senior Data Architect will be responsible for the delivery of data strategy across the Data Architecture team. They are responsible for managing the delivery of Data Architecture strategy and artefacts including but not limited to data models, development and supporting data architecture patterns, assist in designing and delivery of data capabilities for data platform and responsible to provide data architecture services to key programs and initiatives. The position enables architecture team to achieve the following:

  • Designing fit for purpose data solutions that enables our business and delight our customers
  • Developing, publishing, and maintaining the information architecture – current, interim and target state architecture aligned to execution roadmaps and data strategy.
  • Translate high-level business requirements into data models (Dimensional and Datavault 2.0) and appropriate metadata
  • Provide clear, continuous, and consistent data architecture support to the in-flight initiatives and to the data platforms team.
  • Strong experience with data warehouse-based solutions – design, patterns, services, and processes. Good understanding of data ingestion, storage of data, pipeline design, ETL / ELT methodology, integration patterns, data conformance / standardization and data consumption (Analytics, APIs, events, services, datamarts, data science, AI and ML use cases etc.)
  • Good understanding of at least one cloud service providers, leading cloud practices, architecture approach, services, technology, strategy, and process. Assist in execution of cloud first strategy and in designing cloud hosted solutions (preferably Azure with Databricks)
  • Defines technical direction and roadmap for cloud migrations and managing the implementation and technical solutions. Architect cloud native, hybrid, or multi-cloud solutions to meet business needs.
  • Define and maintain data architecture principles, standards, patterns, guidelines, and processes
  • Ensure proposed architecture solutions are in alignment with data architecture principles and target state strategy
  • Work with business and technology teams to understand data consumers’ needs and develop solutions to meet them
  • Evaluate and recommend emerging technologies for data management and analytics
  • Engage with relevant stakeholders in maturing the team and the data architecture practice
  • Demonstrate a relentless improvement and a continuous learning mindset
  • Provide mentoring and coaching to the team
  • Maintain strong, enduring relationships with a variety of senior level stakeholders across business areas as well as Group Technology

About you

  • Minimum 10 - 14 years of delivery and data architecture experience - growing capabilities in a large sized data team within a data architecture domain in a multi-platform, multi-technology environment
  • Experience in cloud-based data platforms – demonstrate experience with cloud based data platform implementations
  • Technical Competency - demonstrable experience with all phases of the SDLC using either Agile or Waterfall methodologies
  • Bachelor's Degree in Technology - education with data related coursework or another equivalent field; an advanced degree in any of these, or related fields is preferred.
  • Leadership and management experience is preferred
  • A sound working knowledge of existing, new, and emerging data trends - and the benefits derived from these
  • Business acumen with ability to understand and anticipate business needs to provide appropriate data architecture guidance
  • Collaboration, communication, presentation, problem solving, interpersonal, consulting, influencing and stakeholder engagement skills to build relationships at all levels.
  • A broad, enterprise-wide view of the business - and varying degrees of appreciation for strategy, organisational capabilities and enabling technologies
  • Banking experience is preferred with good knowledge of one or more of these domains – Core Banking, Mortgages, Lending, Payments, Digital, Business Banking, Regulatory reporting

About Us

BOQ is one of Australia’s leading regional banks and provides a genuine alternative for Australian financial services customers and employees. Our purpose is to create prosperity for our customers, shareholders and people through empathy, integrity and by making a difference. Our ambition is to be known as the bold challenger bank; with multi-brands that are digitally enabled with a personal touch.

BOQ is passionate about providing opportunities for you to develop your career as we continuously adapt and deliver in a transformational and collaborative environment with a strong focus on community.

BOQ’s Inclusion vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.

In 2021 BOQ Group was awarded a Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) Employer of Choice for Gender Equality citation.

Our Benefits

• Flexible working arrangements
• Discounted financial products
• Salary sacrificing options
• Paid parental leave with no minimum
• Paid volunteer days
• Purchase annual leave
• BUPA Corporate Plan
• Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
• A ‘zero tolerance’ to Domestic and Family Violence (DFV) with active support for employees experiencing DFV
• Accessible work support through various practices, systems, office adjustments
• Gym, shopping, technology and travel offers
• 5 employee diversity network groups focusing on; First Nations Reconciliation Council, EPIC (LGBTIQA+), Multicultural, Gender and Early Career.

How to Apply

To apply for this role please follow the links or apply via our Careers Page.

The Bank of Queensland is committed to diversity and an inclusive workforce. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People are encouraged to apply.

If you are successful for a role with the Bank of Queensland, it is a condition of employment that background screening is completed to ensure that the Bank complies with its obligations under the Anti-Money Laundering and Counter Terrorism Financing Act. These checks may include, but are not limited to: identity, verification, reference checks, criminal background checks, immigration checks, verification of academic qualifications, bankruptcy checks.

job.content:
We are looking to engage a skilled and enthusiastic Data Engineer to join our Federal Government client!

Our client is currently undergoing a major uplift in data capability for the Agency, planned and delivered through our change program, there are vast opportunities to be a key contributor to drive, design and deliver policies, frameworks and infrastructure to suit the agency's data operation needs.

This is your chance to make a difference for our Federal Government client in this 24 month contract with an additional 12 months of extensions offered.

Australian Citizens with the ability to obtain a Baseline security clearance will be considered for this role.


The experience and skills for this role are:
  • Ability to scope and define data sets needed for specific use cases and identifying data gaps.
  • Ability to translate scientific insights into product decisions and work streams.
  • Flexibility to handle directional changes and moving priorities to ensure project success.
  • Knowledge and application of DMBOK data management frameworks and principals.
  • Familiarity with star schemas and data vault modelling.
  • Experience using enterprise data modelling tools (LucidChart, EA Sparx, ERWin, ER Studio, etc).
  • Capability to create Conceptual, Logical and Physical data models for a range of technological solutions, databases and pipelines at an enterprise level in accordance with prescribed data modelling standards.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, with Attribute Based Access Control and deployments for Power BI.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, using Github, CI/CD and attribute-based Access Control and deployments for Power BI
  • A demonstrated in-depth knowledge of data base infrastructure and cloud data solutions, preferably Azure suite (D365, SQL, Analysis Services, Power BI, Purview, Dataverse, Gen II data lake, Synapse, Data Factory).


 To be considered for this opportunity, APPLY to this advertisement.

job.abstract: UnitingCare is seeking an experienced Technical Domain Manager - Hosting and Domain on a full time, permanent basis.
job.content:
Make a meaningful difference with us:

We’re looking for someone who wants to make the world a little better through small moments that leave big impacts. To be part of something bigger, achieving positive change by working with thousands of Australians to help them live life in all its fullness.
 

We want people who are great as individuals, and even better in a team. As a Technical Domain Manager – Hosting and Domain to join their Digital and Technology (D&T) team on a full time, permanent basis. 
 

The Technical Domain Manager - Hosting and Domain within the Digital Backbone and Service Management Technical Services team, has been created to establish and lead D&T’s Hosting and Domain Technical Service Offering, providing underpinning reliable and scalable End User Services for UnitingCare. 
 

You will work collaboratively with leaders to invite the “voice of the Customer” into continuous improvement of the Hosting and Domain Technical Service Offering and work closely with the broader D&T team to collaborate effectively to ensure smooth and stable technical services and solutions that deliver the desired and timely customer outcomes. 

 

Please note, this is a full time, permanent opportunity where hybrid working is supported. 

 

Your part in our UnitingCare team:

  • Lead technical governance over Hosting & Domain services primarily delivered by the Managed Service Agreement (MSA) partner as well as other internal and external service providers. 
  • Formalisation and stabilisation of the existing and evolving Hosting and Domain Technical Service Offering (H&D TSO), ensuring the H&D capabilities continue to improve to support improved service delivery and speed of resolution by establishing repeatable, reliable and quantifiable services. 
  • Day-to-day operational stability and continuous improvement of UCQ’s current and future Hosting and Domain Technical Service Offering (H&D TSO), including both Standard and Virtual environments. 
  • Manage the delivery of UnitingCare’s H&D TSO, in alignment with industry best practices and frameworks. 
  • Actively monitor the quality and quantity of work produced by the H&D TSO MSA partner and service providers, with the aim of continuous improvement. 
  • Work with peers, such as the other Technical Domain Managers and other D&T stakeholders, such as Delivery Managers, Small Initiatives Lead and Digital Platform teams, to promote and communicate opportunities both inside and outside of the team. 

 

What makes a difference for us?

  • Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Information Technology or Management, Data Analytics or related discipline or equivalent proven and successful industry skills and experience. 
  • Extensive technical experience across a wide-reaching range of client facing technologies including: Active Directory (AD) and Azure AD (AAD), Cloud (Azure), Windows Server and Database Technologies, VMware Virtualisation, Enterprise Storage, ITIL.
  • Proven successful expertise in developing, evolving and managing technology operations, infrastructure services and/or technical project management and delivery within a multi layered vendor and internal capability across a complex enterprise technical environment preferably working in a large geographically diverse organisation. 
  • Prior experience managing End User Computing technologies, Citrix, Exchange Online, Microsoft 365, Mobile Device Management, Network Data & Voice Management will be highly regarded.
  • Proven successful experience converting IT strategies into tailored operational delivery roadmaps to underpin investment, operational stability and ongoing sustainability. 

 

What makes a difference for you?

The opportunity to be part of the second-largest Queensland employer who has been leading by example as a proud not-for-profit, for more than 100 years.

  • Flexible work arrangements to support work-life balance.
  • Access to salary packaging, meal and entertainment benefits - up to $15,900 per year tax free as well as up to $2,650 of your pre-tax income to pay for meal and entertainment benefits.
  • A recognition and rewards platform, providing employee discounts at hundreds of retailers, including everyday expenses, holidays, health insurance, a wellbeing program and employee assistance program.
  • Career development opportunities to challenge yourself, grow and make a meaningful difference.
     

Diversity & Inclusion

Our approach is simple –everybody is welcome here. At UnitingCare, diversity is at the core of our who we are, our mission and our values. We are committed to providing equal opportunities to all employees no matter their sex, race, culture, sexual orientation, disability or gender identity. 
 

Vaccination

All employees are required to comply with statutory and Government requirements and UnitingCare's COVID-19 vaccination requirements policy. The successful applicant must be able to provide a Covid-19 Certificate before commencing employment.
 

UnitingCare as part of our commitment to reconciliation and building long term employment opportunities for First Nations peoples, would strongly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander applicants for this position. You can learn more about UnitingCare's Reconciliation Action Plan here.

job.title: IT System Administrator
job.abstract: Join an exciting company that is going through aggressive growth and seeking a passionate IT System Administrator based in Haymarket.
job.content:
We are one of Australia's fastest growing companies. We design, build and maintain world-class digital infrastructure, encompassing fibre networks, communication platforms, residential internet and voice services.

We believe our people are vital to our success. We strive to create an environment that appeals to the very best people in the industry, providing them with an exciting, market leading and satisfying workplace, and rewarding their performance.


Join an exciting company that is going through aggressive growth and seeking a passionate IT System Administrator. This position reports to the Infrastructure Manager and is available in Haymarket.
 

About the Role:

As a member of our Group IT team, the Systems Administrator is responsible and accountable for the operation, support, architecture and documentation of our Business IT environment with an acute focus on cyber security, automation and ensuring our employees are getting the best out of our Business IT systems.

They will work closely with the Infrastructure Manager and have direct input into Business IT related projects and will help shape the future of our IT environment through ongoing programmes of design, implementation, maintenance and upgrade.

Responsibilities include but not limited to:

  • Build technology solution designs to meet business requirements including scope, deliverables, financials, and internal communication
  • Coordinate the implementation of solution designs across the business
  • Ensure on-time and on-point delivery of anticipated requirements and business outcomes from projects and solution designs
  • Coordinate with key stakeholders on impactful changes and incidents
  • Ensuring the setting and enforcement of ICT Security policies
  • Ensure security of data, network access and backup systems, including Disaster Recovery, Business Continuity Planning etc
  • Act in alignment with business needs and system functionality to contribute to organizational policy
  • Identify problematic areas and implement strategic improvements across the environment
  • Document the detailed design and implementation plan to improve or upgrade the Business IT environment
  • Documenting and Managing our Standard Operating Environment and changes to it
  • Running regular checks on network and data security and identifying opportunities for improvement
  • Assisting with the design of training programmes to educate employees across the group
  • Conducting regular system audits
  • Oversee and manage on-premises and cloud business computing environments across the group
  • Create, and Update Documentation of ICT systems as improvements are identified
  • Assist in the management of the day-to-day ICT support systems, including the overall triage and reporting of the ticketing system, ensuring fast resolution for internal customers

About you:

The ideal person for this role will have/be:

  • Problem Solver with strong attention to detail
  • Excellent oral and written communication skills
  • Self-starter who can manage priorities and their time effectively
  • Ability to work with a range of different stakeholders both internally and externally
  • Adaptable and able to work in a dynamic changing environment
  • Team player able to work effectively as part of a team and shares knowledge and skills toward achieving a common goal
  • Innovative approach, seeks ways to improve on past experiences by providing creative solutions
  • Takes initiative for ongoing personal development identifying and continually developing skills and talents
  • Integrity – performs with honesty, transparency and trust
  • Always presents professionally, reflecting a positive attitude and approach to their work
  • Demonstrates flexibility when the needs of the business changes and management directives change to ensure the best outcome is achieved to meet daily operational targets

Essential Experience:

  • Minimum 3 years experience in a Systems Administration role, working with Windows, Mac, Azure and Office365
  • Experience in virtual server infrastructure, DR scenarios and backup.
  • Previous experience with MDM and Autopilot administration and deployment
  • Familiarity with the Fortinet suite of devices, software & services.
  • Excellent knowledge of technical management, information analysis and of computer hardware/software systems
  • Working understanding of Linux systems desirable but not essential
  • Highly experienced in IT Security concepts and application
  • Aptitude for problem solving
  • Aptitude for documentation and ability to relay information clearly and efficiently.
  • Hands-on experience with computer networks, network administration and network installation
  • Batchelor in Computer Science, Information Systems or similar fields such as MCSA, Azure Administrator (or equivalent experience)
  • Skilled in Microsoft 365, Azure, Autopilot + Intune architecture design
  • Skilled in support of Windows Active Directory and Windows Server
  • Skilled in Office365 hybrid cloud environments
  • Skilled in basic routing, networking and firewalling concepts
  • Skills in SharePoint and Microsoft Flow highly desirable

About us:

Uniti Group is an exciting, dynamic and fast-growing telecommunications company.

At Uniti Group we are absolutely committed to attracting, developing, and retaining the best people by offering a flexible, diverse, and inclusive workplace where hard work and dedication is rewarded  

If this role sounds like you, we would like to hear from you! You must have the right to live and work in in Australia to apply for this role. For current opportunities, please visit our Careers Portal at https://unitigrouplimited.elmotalent.com.au/careers/careers/jobs

Questions about the role to be emailed directly to our HR team at recruitment@unitigrouplimited.com

No recruiters please, we manage our recruitment in-house.

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Challenge yourself, develop your technical skills and have plenty of fun in the process!
job.content:
Servian, is an award winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital app dev, Machine Learning and cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has for us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career which will have a greater impact.

We are currently looking for talented Data Specialists who are based out of Perth, to help our clients deliver data driven solutions. Our Perth office has gone from strength to strength in the past 12 months, growing from a team of one to a team of 31! We are a collection of passionate problem solvers and technologists, who love learning new things and having plenty of fun along the way.

You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, being involved in implementing strategies and delivering on cloud solutions in Google Cloud, Azure and AWS.

Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields.  You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, working with our clients to understand their needs and to help shape the engagements that allow Servian to provide services that will meet those needs. 

If you have a passion for learning new technologies, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process!

 

What experience are we looking for?

  • Data Integration - bringing data together from various sources into a quality source of information. You bring expertise in working with ETL and ELT software, best-practices patterns, and supporting technologies to build data warehouses in part or whole.
  • Database Technologies - to serve as engines for transactional and analytical data workloads. You can articulate the pros and cons of the myriad of database technologies and find the best fit for any given use case.
  • Data Modelling - to construct efficient and meaningful representations of data. You are able to design data structures that take into account access patterns, simplicity of human understanding, and maintainability of data.
  • Reporting and Business Intelligence - A primary consumer of data assets in the enterprise
  • Data Governance and Quality - Building integrity and trust in data
  • Information Security - Confidentiality, integrity and availability of data
  • DataOps - Automation practices and tools which accelerate delivery of data assets
  • Non-warehouse Data Architectures - Data lakes, NoSQL data stores, data virtualization

 

Who are you?

  • Curious and eager to learn - You are a curious individual who is eager to develop their skills and progress their career at every opportunity in a consulting environment.
  • Team player - You thrive as a part of high performing teams and love sharing your knowledge with your peers and clients. We win together.
  • Proactive - You seize opportunities when you see them. Every day at Servian presents broad opportunities for personal, professional and business growth.
  • Passionate - You are excited by tech. Our team constantly innovate and implement new technologies and methodologies for themselves, our vendors and our clients.

 

Wellbeing & Benefits:

  • Access to a wide range of internal training sessions, across both technical and consulting skills.
  • Sponsored certifications across all our partner technology vendors. 
  • We provide employees with Life Insurance, Income Protection Insurance and access to an Employee Assistance Program. 
  • Generous Parental leave.
  • We are proud to have a sociable workplace that values diversity and celebrates achievement with multiple company-wide, social, and family events throughout the year. Due to Covid-19, all social events are currently virtual.

 

Why join Servian?

  • Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies.
  • A chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team.
  • Consultant-led events including Social clubs, Tech clubs (IoT, Chatbots, etc.), Gaming events, MeetUps, Tech Guilds and Cloud Vendor Hackathons.
  • Proactive career development through structured learning and development, multiple avenues for growth and an innovative reward and recognition structure.
  • Inclusion and diversity - The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow.
  • Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, and a progressive parental leave policy.

 

Inclusion & Diversity

  • Servian recognises individual differences and welcomes people from a variety of life and work experiences. The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and to fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow. 
  • A natural curiosity, a respect for differences and a growth mindset are valued at Servian.

 

If you’re looking for the opportunity to step up into a challenging position and are excited by the thought of getting your hands dirty with the latest tech stacks/methodologies, then look no further...

APPLY NOW!

job.content:
Permanent opportunity for an experienced Data Architect.

Your new company
Hays Technology is currently working with a large energy client in WA. We are looking to appoint an experienced Data Architect into a permanent opportunity. This role is likely to commence in April 2023.

Your new role
You will be joining a established team who has new projects coming up hence why they need a Data Architect to be directly involved in a semi-greenfield project. The focus of the role will be working with other members of the existing team to design, establish and operationalise the new data warehouse platform. This will be done by using OracleDB and Microsoft Azure as the main data warehouses.

Key responsibilities include:

  • Development of Data Architecture for organisation.
  • Development of data related policies, guidelines, standards and other artifacts.
  • Development of data management related processes and procedures.
  • Leading design / configuration of data warehouse and / or data lakes.
  • Leading design / configuration of reporting and analytics "end user layer".
  • Development, or identification, of data standards for adoption within the organisation.


What you'll need to succeed

  • Previous experience as a Data Architect specially working with OracleDB.
  • Strong data warehousing design and development experience, preferably with Azure Data Warehouse or Azure Synapse.
  • Experience developing data architectures in large complex organisations.
  • Extensive data modelling skills are absolutely key to success in this role.
  • Demonstrated ability to work both independently and part of a team.
  • Excellent communication and interpersonal skills


What you'll get in return

  • Permanent Opportunity.
  • Attractive salary.
  • 11% superannuation.
  • Perth CBD.
  • Friendly environment with flexible working arrangements.
  • Opportunity to be part of a dynamic team.

job.content:
THE ROLE

This role supports the collection and management of data assets that transform into information for business decision support, artificial intelligence solutions and analytics.

This is a unique opportunity to join a great team. Reporting to the Asset Data and Information Manager you'll be responsible for:

  • Maintain and develop data interfaces for Generation Data Warehouse
  • Plan, create and maintain data architecture
  • Utilise data to create and maintain BI reporting
  • Develop User Interfaces (UI) to facilitate data maintenance
  • Maintain source control utilising CI/CD pipelines
  • Develop and lead strategic projects

IS THIS YOU?


You'll need to have exceptional communication skills with the ability to easily build rapport with others and have a minimum of 5 years Tertiary qualifications in Information Technology/Computer Science.

You can show, through the work you've done that you have:

  • Microsoft SQL Server and Integration Services
  • BI reporting tools e.g. Tableau, Power BI
  • Strong documentation capability
  • Modern programming languages e.g. Python, C# (desirable)
  • M365 suite including Power Automate and Power Apps

Origin - Where good change happens

At Origin, we're powered by people who believe in creating collective change. We're creating more diverse and inclusive workplaces for everyone because the more perspectives we have, in a place where everyone can belong, the better we can tackle our challenges together. We are united, yet unique.

We are committed to fostering a diverse, gender equitable workforce, where all applications are evaluated on merit and potential. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, people living with disabilities, culturally diverse people, any stage in life, people with intersex variations and people within LGBTQ+ communities, including trans, and gender diverse.

Origin's Energy Supply and Operations business plays a key role in providing reliable, affordable and sustainable energy to power Australian homes and businesses. We're the largest owner of natural gas-fired power stations in Australia, and generate more than 7,400 MW of power through our flexible generation portfolio. We're also a major supporter in the growth of renewable supply and storage, supporting a cleaner energy future.

We're looking for passionate and forward-thinking people to help, who are committed to a zero-harm safety culture, managing risk and driving culture change.

Origin. Good energy

At Origin, our focus is on getting energy right for our customers, communities, and planet. Because we know it's up to us to shape the future of energy. Today, we serve more than 4.2 million customers, are one of the most significant energy producers in the country and listed in the ASX Top 50 companies.

job.content:
Data Engineer - Cloud

Join one of Australia's largest retail organisations who make an impact on the lives of millions of people each day. They are looking for a data engineer with Spark, Python, SQL, Pyspark, Snowflake and Azure experience.

What You'll Be Doing

The Insights team within the broader Technology team focuses on building data collection and analytics capabilities to uncover customer, products and operational insights, providing data driven support to our users, and enabling the organisation to be data driven.

We are embarking on engineering, enablement, operations and delivery of key data initiatives, building them using market leading cloud technologies, including; MS Azure, Databricks, Snowflake and Spark.

The cloud transformation journey we are in, focuses on democratising and streamlining sharing of data across team and will enable teams to operate more efficiently, provide better insights, and scale with the exponential growth of data.

You will be pivotal in making this happen by:

  • Design and develop cloud-based applications
  • Manage cloud environments in accordance with company security guidelines
  • Deploy and debug cloud initiatives as needed in accordance with best practices throughout the development lifecycle

Good things you'll need

  • At least 4 years relevant software development experience.
  • Degree in Computer Science, IT, or similar field
  • Solid experience in ETL/ELT processes and pipelines.
  • Experience with databases, data views, and data exploration using advanced SQL
  • Understanding of database schema design and dimensional data modelling
  • Demonstrated experience with at least one programming language (Scala, Python, Java etc)
  • Experience with designing and developing reusable ETL framework models
  • Exposure to DevOps, CI/CD processes and best practices
  • Experience in data quality assurance processes
  • Exposure to cloud technologies.

job.title: EL 1 Director Data Engineer, Data Analytics
job.abstract: We are looking for a Data Engineer specialist to fill a key vacancy in our SADA team.
job.content:
About the Director Data Engineer, Data Analytics, SADA in the ANAO

This is your opportunity to undertake work that you can’t do anywhere else. The Director Data Engineer is a unique position within the Australian Public Service. You will work side-by-side with experienced leaders and play a pivotal role in ensuring accountability and transparency in the Australian Government sector.


About the role

The Systems Assurance and Data Analytics Group (SADA) provides support and services to the ANAO’s financial statements and performance audit groups, and Corporate Management Group. SADA comprises of approximately 35 staff who work in teams specialising in either IT systems and controls assurance or in data analytics. Within SADA, the Data Analytics Team consists of approximately 10 staff, with backgrounds encompassing professions such as research, data analytics, engineering, economics, information technology, finance and accounting.


The opportunity

The ANAO undertakes a variety of data analytics work. An increasing portion of our work involves the design, build, and sustainment of data analysis products that produce information for audit teams from large volumes of data.

The ANAO has recently established a digital audit function within the Data Analytics Team to take carriage of this work. The Digital Audit Section will make use of major IT investment projects currently underway, involving the Section, to implement centralised data storage, automated deployments using Azure DevOps, a data exchange portal for receiving large volumes of data from audited entities, and a self-service analytics platform in which audit teams can easily access a variety of analytic products.

The digital audit practice is managed by the Senior Director, Digital Audit. The Director (Data Engineer), Digital Audit is a leader that supports the Senior Director to define and deliver the functions of the Digital Audit Section. Your day-to-day work would likely involve tasks along the lines of the below:

  • Lead and manage a team of data engineers/data analysts to design and deliver data analytics products to end users, including reviewing Python scripts that assess data for risks, applying a calculation model, or performing ETL functions. Develop a plan to migrate that functionality into an automated pipeline hosted in Azure that scales to larger volumes of data with less human intervention;
  • With the Senior Director, meet with audit teams to co-design new data analytics solution to make audit work more efficient;
  • Work with the ANAO’s IT Services team to plan and deploy new resources into the data analytics cloud, and ensure data is appropriately managed;
  • Work with staff in the ANAO’s corporate area to discuss how technologies such as Power Automate (or similar tools) could streamline the production of management reporting;
  • Provide guidance and support to other Data Analytics team staff regarding the use of data engineering-related technologies in the Microsoft Azure platform;
  • Provide feedback to more junior staff regarding their technical work, and reviewing their technical work for correctness, so they can improve their skills and undertake more complex work in future;
  • Raise awareness across the organisation of data technology related issues for different types of audits and projects;
  • Manage client relationships including maintaining a high level of engagement and communication with audit or business teams;
  • Assist in the formulation of business and operational plans for the SADA Group; and
  • Mentor, coach, guide and support the professional development of junior staff.
  • The data engineering practice is a newly established, growth function. The role would suit an individual who is seeking opportunities for growth, and who is looking for the challenge of helping to build a new capability with the ANAO.


Desirable skills

Given the nature of the work within the team, the following skills and experience would be highly regarded:

  • Tertiary qualifications relevant to data analytics, data engineering, information technology, or similar disciplines; and
  • Experience working with a wide range of data-formats or data sources from various IT/business information systems

This role may be offered on an ongoing basis in Canberra. If you are found suitable but do not receive a job offer, we’ll add you to a list of people we can contact about similar jobs that become available. This is called a merit pool.


About you

The successful candidate should have the following:

  • A demonstrated ability to leverage technical, stakeholder engagement and project management skills to review, validate, transform and present data to business users;
  • Experience in working with diverse data sources, and solving challenging ETL problems;
  • Excellent problem-solving skills, including the ability to independently research and assess potential solutions to complex issues, and liaise with other teams to implement them;
  • Sound project management skills, including a demonstrated capability to lead data-related projects, manage competing priorities, and resolve changing or evolving situations;
  • Demonstrated capability to communicate complex issues clearly and effectively to various audiences including non-technical audiences; and
  • Demonstrated effective leadership of high performing teams that have diverse and complementary technical skills.

Experience with technologies used in the ANAO Environment (which are primarily Python, SQL, and data-related components of the Microsoft Azure/M365 stack such as PowerBI, Azure Data Factory, Synapse, etc) would be highly regarded. However, the technology tools used by the ANAO are continuously evolving. As such, an innovation mindset, an openness to try and experiment, and a demonstrated ability to quickly adapt and learn new skills is considered essential.

The Data Analytics team and the ANAO are strongly committed to a workplace culture in which staff act with respect and integrity to deliver excellent work in a spirit of open, supportive collaboration. As a leader in the team you will be expected to demonstrate effective leadership in support of this culture.

 

Benefits

The ANAO is proud to offer a modern, activity-based work environment and a strong focus on ongoing training and development to grow and invest in your career.

You will be offered quality in-house training and on-the-job mentoring as well as support for you to undertake your professional studies.

We also offer generous salaries with additional 15.4% superannuation, flex time for APS level staff, an Employee Assistance Program for staff and their families and a range of different leave options.


Interested?

For more information about the roles and how to apply, please refer to our ANAO Careers webpage, and submitting your application via our online recruitment system by: 11:30pm (AEST) on Sunday 19 March 2023

bullets: Opportunity for growth and challenge in building a new capability in the ANAO
Strong commitment to career development
Modern and flexible workplace
