job.title: Senior Observability Engineer
job.abstract: This is a new team within Optus with lots of opportunity to grow and develop your skills.
job.content:
About the role

Optus is building a new Team who will be focused on Observability and AIOPS. We're looking to hire an experienced Engineer who will help establish and continue to evolved this key part of our business.

This is an Observability position for a highly skilled individual. You will play a key role in Onboarding of a large-scale Metrics based Monitoring solution for various critical traditional compute environments, private cloud Observability initiatives in the enterprise. Focus is on systems and application monitoring (log, metrics events), covering existing and open-source monitoring tooling, as well as public cloud monitoring services.

You will be responsible for leading the building and operation of Optus IT Elasticsearch and Dynatrace platforms and plays an active role in gathering of both business and technical requirements, design and development of new business dashboards and configurations that deliver meaningful insights to key stakeholders.

Snr Observability Engineer provides technical leadership and solution guidance to graduates and contract observability personnel

About you
  • Tertiary qualification in Information Technology or related.
  • Advanced cerrtification, knowledge and experience in a recognized ITSM framework e.g. ITIL
  • Knowledge and experience in Elasticsearch framework
  • 10+ years of experience with IT and integration engineering
  • 3+ years of experience in Dynatrace with Davis engine, synthetic URL monitoring
  • Hands on experience in one or more data technologies (e.g Elasticsearch or Splunk)
  • Hands on experience in Linux / UNIX Cloud VM
  • Hands on experience in scripting Python, UNIX Shell, Perl
  • Extensive experience in working with time series data, as well as critical application metrics e.g. java JMX, thread pools, GC, etc
  • Understanding of data modelling techniques
  • Hands on experience in data visualization using Kibana, Grafana, Prometheus, Splunk
  • Hands on experience with querying languages (KQL, SQL, NoSQL, Lucene).
  • Extensive experience in APM (application performance monitoring)
  • Experience in web and application server setup and administration on RHEL, including Apache web server, JBoss AS and Websphere AS
  • Experience with an APM tool such as Dynatrace (APM and Synthetics), New Relic, AppDynamics, or Datadog.
  • Experience with cloud monitoring in AWS or Azure
  • Experience with recommending baseline monitoring thresholds, recommending performance monitoring KPIs and SLAs
  • Hands on experience with Machine Learning Models
  • Possess the ability to exercise independent and effective judgment
  • Strong analytical skills, meticulous, energetic, innovative, able to work well in a team and under pressure
  • A good team player and able to work effectively at all levels of an organization with the ability to influence others to move towards consensus.

So, Why Optus?

Our vision is to be Australia's most loved everyday brand with lasting customer relationships. By creating unique customer connections, being digital everywhere and delivered by our amazing people.

Every role at Optus helps us to achieve our vision. We believe in the value of an inclusive and diverse workforce for our people to build stronger connections within our teams, with our customers and fuel innovation.

We're a highly collaborative workplace, and offer a range of perks such as:

  • Ongoing training, mentoring and development opportunities
  • Hybrid ways of working
  • Competitive salary (expand upon STI, Comms etc.)
  • Vibrant campus life, variety of facilities including restaurants, cafes, gymnasium, GP, and post office

It starts with Yes!

To find out more about our culture at Optus, go behind the scenes with our people by searching #OptusLife on LinkedIn.

Please no recruitment agencies, we'll be managing this role in-house. Any resumes submitted outside of our process will be deemed the sole property of Optus.

As a provider of essential services across Australia, Optus has a critical role in the community through keeping our customers connected to the people they love and the things that matter. We have a COVID-19 Vaccination Policy and also require vaccination to enter our workplaces. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this policy or how it impacts you, including any concerns you might have about meeting this requirement.



Optus is a place where we let you do you. Whether you'll be working in our corporate offices or in a retail store, we're a highly collaborative workplace, and offer a range of perks such as:

  • A competitive salary
  • Discounts on products and services
  • Ongoing training, mentoring and development opportunities
  • Up to five days of Volunteer Leave per year
  • Blended Ways of Working

Curious about our culture? Go behind the scenes with our people by searching #OptusLife on LinkedIn.

job.title: Senior GIS Engineer
job.abstract: Within a small team, lead the development and maintenance of TCA's geographic information services.
job.content:
TCA’s mission is to provide assurance to governments, industry sectors and end-users in the use of telematics and related intelligent technologies. Through the National Telematics Framework, the data collected from the transport industry is managed and analysed, with insights reported back to Government to better inform decision making.

We are currently seeking a technically driven individual to join our small Data Insights Team. Highly skilled, the Senior GIS Engineer will be responsible for:

  • technical leadership for the development and maintenance of TCAs spatio-temporal insights capability
  • management of the testing and change management processes to ensure GIS capability
  • providing hands-on geospatial administration services
  • assisting in publication of technical reports
  • mentoring

To be considered for this role, you will need:

  • minimum 5 years GIS engineering/ development experience
  • tertiary qualification in Geospatial engineering or IT
  • experience with ArcGiS Enterprise in an Azure cloud environment
  • experience with spatio-temporal systems development using ArcGIS Pro

Experience in the transport industry would be considered an advantage, as would experience with Hadoop, Spark, DataBricks, Delta lake, JSON, MSSQL, Scala, Python and Tableau.

The full position description is available on the TCA website, at https://tca.gov.au/about/careers/

The role is based in the Melbourne CBD, however TCA supports flexible working arrangements. 

The successful applicant will be required to undertake a Police Name Check.

job.abstract: Flexible working in the NFP industry on offer for a Data Architect who has Azure cloud exp and can develop data-led insights to stakeholders
job.content:
The Role
This role is focused on reinventing and transforming the technology landscape of the Data & Digital Transformation team to best meet the needs of their operations teams. The Data Architect ensures that strategic goals are optimised by evolving effective Enterprise Data Management using enterprise data standards for data warehousing, data lake, data management and other corporate databases. The Data Architect works across the business, and closely with other members of the Technology Services Group, building the direction
and vision for strategic data architecture that supports business outcomes.  

The Candidate
The ideal candidate will have good knowledge of one or more data warehousing applications that may include Oracle, PL/SQL and Azure Data Platform technologies. They must be willing to get their hands dirty and have experience hosting data management platforms and data architecture. They can work in a collaborative environment and have good knowledge of Machine learning, data mining and AI principles to resolve data driven problems.

Core duties
  • Working experience with both on-premises, public cloud and SAS hosted data management platforms and data architecture including but not limited to cloud service providers such as Azure and AWS.
  • Knowledge and understanding of both batch and fast-moving data paradigms.
  • Good knowledge of one or more data warehousing applications that may include Oracle, PL/SQL, Microsoft SQL and Azure Data Platform technologies.
  • Experience with data manipulation and scripting languages such as SQL, Python and Java knowledge of Machine Learning, data mining and AI principles applied to data patterns recognition resolving data driven problems.
  • Good working experience in establishing MDM (Master Data Management) patterns across the Enterprise data estate.


Benefits
  • Option of 9 day work fortnight
  • Work overseas for 2 months of the year
  • Drive real-world impact
  • NFP bonus on top of salary
  • WFH flexibility – 2 days in office
Apply
If you feel you are fit for this role, click the apply button, alternatively, please send in your CV to ccrummey@sharpandcarter.com.au. If you would like to discuss the role further, please don’t hesitate to call Chris Crummey on 0424808442.

job.title: Senior Cloud Engineer - AZURE
job.abstract: Swing from Mindtree vines to enhance your AZURE cloud skills and be a cloud evangelist with customers, partners and external social communities
job.content:
LTIMindtree is a global technology consulting and digital solutions company that enables enterprises across industries to reimagine business models, accelerate innovation, and maximize growth by harnessing digital technologies. As a digital transformation partner to more than 750 clients, LTIMindtree brings extensive domain and technology expertise to help drive superior competitive differentiation, customer experiences, and business outcomes in a converging world. Powered by nearly 90,000 talented and entrepreneurial professionals across more than 30 countries, LTIMindtree — a Larsen & Toubro Group company — combines the industry-acclaimed strengths of erstwhile Larsen and Toubro Infotech and Mindtree in solving the most complex business challenges and delivering transformation at scale. For more information, please visit www.ltimindtree.com.

 

 

Senior Cloud Engineer > Azure

Being a global technology services and digital transformation company, Mindtree has earned the AI and Machine Learning prime partner status of Microsoft Azure. This is a true validation of our deep knowledge, extensive experience and proven success in enabling customer adoption of AI and implementing Azure solutions for machine learning life cycle and AI-powered apps. Only partners that meet stringent criteria around customer success and staff skilling, as well as pass a third-party audit of their AI and machine learning technical practices, are able to earn the AI and Machine Learning prime partner status on Microsoft Azure's advanced specialization.

This new role will provide thought leadership for technical architecture, design, development and deployment as well as guide customers towards accelerated adoption of the Azure cloud data platform.

Working within various Australian government departments you will require: Baseline Security Clearance.

 

Roles & Responsibilities:

  • Experience in Data warehousing and BI domain with ability collect requirements and translating them into Design & Technical specifications
  • Experience in handling the structured and unstructured data
  • Architect/engineer end-to-end data migration solutions
  • Support IaaS and data migrations and PaaS implementation
  • Deliver clear vision for system architecture topology, component design, networking and security of proposed solutions through modelling and using tools like Visio
  • Implement end-to-end DevOps automated processes and pipelines via Azure DevOps, Implement CI/CD, Infrastructure as Code (IaC) .
  • Analyze customers’ data estate, including common workloads, use patterns and business priorities and needs and arrive at solution architecture, design and implementation approach.
  • Apply modern data platform architectures and data engineering best practices to build, implement, and optimize analytical data solutions including data lake, data warehouse, data lakehouse etc. with streaming and batch data processing and visualizations.
  • Identify opportunities for improvements and enhancements based on stakeholder feedback and help incorporate them into the overall technical strategy.
  • Anticipate, identify, and remove technical blockers through regular technical reviews and check ins to accelerate solution implementations.
  • Ensure that solution exhibits high levels of performance, security, scalability, maintainability, and evolvability upon deployment. Apply governance to identify, communicate, and minimize business and technical risks.

 

Technical Skills:

  • Strong communication and experience in managing various stakeholder relationships to get consensus on complex technical solutions.
  • Knowledge of Microsoft Well Architected Framework and Cloud Adoption Framework.
  • Strong Database development/management skills, with RDBMS (e.g. SQL Server, Oracle) as well as NoSQL database systems (e.g. MongoDb).
  • Knowledge and skills in other public cloud platforms like AWS and GCP.
  • Experience in open-source analytical data technologies such as Spark, Hadoop, HDFS, Hive, Kafka etc.
  • Programming skills in SQL, PySpark, Python, .Net, JavaScript etc.
  • Deep understanding of agile development methodologies like Scrum and Kanban.
  • Understanding of large program and project management processes and best practices.

 

Desired:

  • Hands-on experience in any of the following Technologies: Azure App Services, Azure Functions, Kubernetes/AKS/OpenShift, Azure storage, Service Bus, Azure SQL Database, Redis Cache, Azure Search, Azure Monitor, Application Insights, Traffic Manager, Key Vault, Cosmos DB, Azure DevOps, API Management, ARM templates, and general cloud governance and security mechanisms are required

 

LTI Mindtree Minds Enjoy:

  • Flexible working arrangements - work here there or anywhere!
  • Working on the most innovative project works!
  • Personal development to enhance your career!
  • Rewarding curiosity and collaboration!

 

LTI Mindtree minds are distinguished by their superior talent and mental agility marked by extreme ownership of transformative technologies in the digital age!

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Seeking an experienced and forward-thinking Data Engineer who enjoys taking the lead in designing and optimising data systems
job.content:
ABOUT US

Chisholm is Victoria’s premier public vocational education and training provider, with campuses located across Melbourne and the south east.

Each year, we welcome some 41,000 students from over 43 culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds. More than 1,400 passionate and dedicated Chisholm employees work together to deliver quality training and education in Melbourne’s south east manufacturing heartland and key residential growth corridor. 

A Victorian Government-owned TAFE, we aim to lead the way in education and training to inspire success and transform lives.

Our purpose is to excel in education and training and be respected and valued for enhancing the social and economic futures of individuals, industry and communities. 

Our drive for commercial success is underpinned by our core values of Collaboration, Accountability Integrity and Respect.

In the past 20 years, we have grown significantly to become a multi-sector institute, delivering a broad range of education and training programs and services in higher education, vocational education and training (VET) and school sectors across ten campuses in Victoria, online, in the workplace and overseas with partner educational and government organisations.

We offer more than 400 courses, from Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE)/Victorian Certificate of Applied Learning (VCAL)/ Vocational Education and Training Delivered to Secondary Students (VETDSS), through to nationally accredited qualifications such as certificates, diplomas, advanced diplomas, degrees, graduate certificates, graduate diplomas and short courses.

ABOUT THE ROLE

This role is responsible for designing and building data models to enhance analytics and performance reporting as well as optimising data flow and collection for cross-functional teams. You must be an experienced forward thinking data pipeline builder and data wrangler who enjoys taking the lead in designing and optimising data systems and building them from the ground up.

The position will develop and test architectures that enable data extraction and transformation for predictive or prescriptive modelling. Under the guidance of the Financial Systems and Data Governance Manager, the role will lead and contribute on data initiatives ensuring optimal data delivery architecture is consistent and fit for purpose.

The Data Engineer will be self-directed and be comfortable supporting the data needs of the business, systems and products. This role requires strong decision-making skills and the ability to communicate confidently and efficiently.

Key accountabilities will include:
  • Building, testing and maintaining data pipeline architecture using cloud technologies.
  • Contributing and supporting design of reporting solutions including BI dashboards and scheduled reports.
  • Communicating and coordinating effectively with the Data and Analytics team and other business areas to ensure models and results are well understood and incorporated into their business processes.
  • Identifying and implementing data quality control processes that prompt correction in the source systems where required.
  • Driving awareness and providing expertise on use of analytics tools and concepts, providing training and effectively communicating with multiple stakeholders.
  • Developing and implementing testing plans for newly developed solutions, maintaining data definition and technical documentation as well as maintaining user access, permissions and updating procedure documentation.

ABOUT YOU

You will be degree qualified in Data Engineering, Information Technology and Systems, Computer Science or related discipline with extensive experience of at least 5 years and have the following skills and experience:

  • Extensive experience and understanding in dimensional data warehouse design and implementation.
  • In-depth understanding of large-scale data sets, including both structured and unstructured data.
  • Ability to analyse and break-down complex data problems.
  • Experience in data warehousing and ETL tools – Snowflake, Azure, Alteryx, SSIS, Matillion.
  • Strong SQL skills – Stored procedures, views, functions, index, performance tuning.
  • Remaining up to date with industry standards and technological advancements that will improve the quality of your outputs.
  • High level written and communication skills as you will need to discuss technical principles and business processes in simple language to people at all levels.
  • Strong interpersonal skills including the ability to negotiate, influence and motivate.
  • Effective self-management skills including the ability to prioritise, problem solve, meet deadlines
  • Ability to work effectively as part of a team as well as independently and autonomously.
  • High attention to detail whilst remaining adaptable to dynamic changes in the business.

BELONGING AND INCLUSION 

Chisholm is resolutely diverse. We celebrate our people’s unique contributions to achieving our ambition to transform lives through relevant and responsive high-quality education. Chisholm’s culture of Belonging & Inclusion strives to promote a self-regulating culture that enhances the experiences of our employees, students and communities.   

We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply. 

We are committed to a fair and equitable merit-based recruitment process for all our candidates. If you have specific accessibility or support requirements please contact our People, Culture & Safety Team at Pcsops@chisholm.edu.au   

Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Applicants 

We welcome and strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.  If you have specific support requirements please contact our People, Culture & Safety Team at Pcsops@chisholm.edu.au    

HOW TO APPLY

Applications for this position close 9am Monday 6 March 2023.

Applications should include:

  • a covering letter
  • curriculum vitae
  • contact details of three (3) referees

Appointment to this position is subject to satisfactory completion of Safety Screening requirements including but not limited to:

  • Valid Employee Working With Children Check
  • National Police Check
  • International Police Check (if applicable)
  • Verification of unrestricted work rights in Australia, eg citizenship, passport or birth certificate
  • Certified copies of qualifications and transcripts

Employees of Chisholm/Chisholm Online/Caroline Chisholm Education Foundation (Chisholm) are required to comply with any applicable directions of the Chief Health Officer, as well as any policy implemented by Chisholm.  In relation to mandatory vaccinations against COVID-19, it is a condition of any offer of employment that candidates agree to comply with any applicable direction or policy regarding mandatory vaccinations.

If you have any questions regarding the position or require further information please contact Manoj, Lead Finance Systems and Business Intelligence, Financial Services on 03 9212 5180.

Chisholm Institute reserves the right to withdraw an advertised position at any stage.

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Seeking all Data Engineer's with Cloud and Python experience
job.content:
One of Australia's best-loved brands is scaling, and they are looking for great Data Engineers to join the team!
  
Working with the delivery team, you will be building, deploying and then maintaining highly scalable data pipelines on a variety of projects and products.
  
Along with a passion for data, we are looking for people who have experience building quality data products deployed into the cloud, and have experience with cloud DWH and CI/CD deployment and development processes.
  
What You’re Bringing:
  • A university degree in IT (or related)
  • 5 + years of experience in Data or Machine Learning engineering
  • ANY cloud experience in AWS or GCP or Azure - we need some solid exposure to the cloud.
  • A background in Software Engineering - you will be working with a very large code base
  • Experience with Spark or PySpark
  • Experience with Python and SQL
  • Exposure to DevOps - you'll be deploying your pipelines and will need to be comfortable from the get-go.

job.title: Senior Data Engineer
job.abstract: Come and join a team of passionate technologists that like to solve problems! Fantastic opportunity to build upon your tech skills
job.content:
Servian, is an award-winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital and Cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has on us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career that will have a greater impact.

Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields. You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. Our Perth office is in the early stages of an exciting journey, foreseeing some of the largest headcount growth within the next 12 - 18 months across the Servian business globally.

If you have a passion for learning new things, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like-minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process!

 

We focus on:

  • Cloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, GCP), HashiCorp
  • Data & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering and Advanced Analytics
  • Digital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile Development
  • Customer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer Insights
  • Artificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep Learning
  • Cyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture Analysis

 

You will be involved in:

  • Development of end to end data pipelines. We are particularly interested in Google Cloud,  Azure, AWS or Snowflake experience.
  • Advising on data architecture, data models, data migration, integration and pipelines and data analysis and visualisation.
  • Implementing solutions for the establishment of data management capabilities including data models and structures, database and data storage infrastructure, master and metadata management, data quality, data integration, data warehousing, data transformation, data analysis and data governance.
  • Development and execution of Data migrations.
  • Supporting pre-sales activity to promote Servian, our capabilities and value to current and prospective clients.

 

What experience are we looking for?

  • A strong analytical thinker and problem solver with thought leadership and commercial awareness.
  • Experienced in building end to end data pipelines using on-premise or cloud based data platforms.
  • Experienced with hands-on delivery of solutions which include databases, advanced SQL and software development in languages such as Python, Scala, Java, TSQL, PL/SQL to name a few.
  • Knowledgeable in relational and big data architectures, data warehousing, data integration, data modelling, data optimisation and data analysis techniques.
  • Interested and knowledgeable in Big Data technologies and Apache ecosystem technologies such as Beam, Spark, Kafka, Hive, Airflow, NiFi, databases, integration, master data management, quality assurance, data wrangling and data governance technologies.
  • Knowledgeable in Cloud Data Warehouse services - Google BigQuery, Snowflake, AWS Redshift, Azure Synapse Analytics or Azure Databricks.
  • Experienced with public cloud platforms and cloud infrastructure, which is essential.
  • Exposed to ETL/ELT and governance tools (inc. Talend, Informatica, Matillion, FiveTran, IBM Datastage, Collibra)

 

Who are you?

  • Curious and eager to learn - You are a curious individual who is eager to develop their skills and progress their career at every opportunity in a consulting environment.
  • Team player - You thrive as a part of high performing teams and love sharing your knowledge with your peers and clients. We win together.
  • Proactive - You seize opportunities when you see them. Every day at Servian presents broad opportunities for personal, professional and business growth.
  • Passionate - You are excited by tech. Our team constantly innovate and implement new technologies and methodologies for themselves, our vendors and our clients.

 

Wellbeing & Benefits:

  • Access to a wide range of internal training sessions, across both technical and consulting skills.
  • Sponsored certifications across all our partner technology vendors. 
  • We provide employees with Life Insurance, Income Protection Insurance and access to an Employee Assistance Program. 
  • Generous Parental leave.
  • We are proud to have a sociable workplace that values diversity and celebrates achievement with multiple company-wide, social, and family events throughout the year. Due to Covid-19, all social events are currently virtual.

 

Inclusion & Diversity:

  • Servian recognises individual differences and welcomes people from a variety of life and work experiences. The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and to fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow. 
  • A natural curiosity, a respect for differences and a growth mindset are valued at Servian.

 

Why join Servian?

  • Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies.
  • A chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team.
  • Consultant-led events including Social clubs, Tech clubs (IoT, Chatbots, etc.), Gaming events, MeetUps, Tech Guilds and Cloud Vendor Hackathons.
  • Proactive career development through structured learning and development, multiple avenues for growth and an innovative reward and recognition structure.
  • Inclusion and diversity - The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow.
  • Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, and a progressive parental leave policy.

 

If you’re looking for the opportunity to challenge yourself and are excited by the thought of getting your hands dirty with the latest tech stacks/methodologies, then look no further...

APPLY NOW!

job.abstract: Swing from Mindtree vines to enhance your AZURE cloud skills and be a cloud evangelist with customers, partners and external social communities
job.content:
LTIMindtree is a global technology consulting and digital solutions company that enables enterprises across industries to reimagine business models, accelerate innovation, and maximize growth by harnessing digital technologies. As a digital transformation partner to more than 750 clients, LTIMindtree brings extensive domain and technology expertise to help drive superior competitive differentiation, customer experiences, and business outcomes in a converging world. Powered by nearly 90,000 talented and entrepreneurial professionals across more than 30 countries, LTIMindtree — a Larsen & Toubro Group company — combines the industry-acclaimed strengths of erstwhile Larsen and Toubro Infotech and Mindtree in solving the most complex business challenges and delivering transformation at scale. For more information, please visit www.ltimindtree.com.

 

 

Senior Cloud Engineer > Azure

Being a global technology services and digital transformation company, Mindtree has earned the AI and Machine Learning prime partner status of Microsoft Azure. This is a true validation of our deep knowledge, extensive experience and proven success in enabling customer adoption of AI and implementing Azure solutions for machine learning life cycle and AI-powered apps. Only partners that meet stringent criteria around customer success and staff skilling, as well as pass a third-party audit of their AI and machine learning technical practices, are able to earn the AI and Machine Learning prime partner status on Microsoft Azure's advanced specialization.

This new role will provide thought leadership for technical architecture, design, development and deployment as well as guide customers towards accelerated adoption of the Azure cloud data platform.

Working within various Australian government departments you will require: Baseline Security Clearance.

 

Roles & Responsibilities:

  • Experience in Data warehousing and BI domain with ability collect requirements and translating them into Design & Technical specifications
  • Experience in handling the structured and unstructured data
  • Architect/engineer end-to-end data migration solutions
  • Support IaaS and data migrations and PaaS implementation
  • Deliver clear vision for system architecture topology, component design, networking and security of proposed solutions through modelling and using tools like Visio
  • Implement end-to-end DevOps automated processes and pipelines via Azure DevOps, Implement CI/CD, Infrastructure as Code (IaC) .
  • Analyze customers’ data estate, including common workloads, use patterns and business priorities and needs and arrive at solution architecture, design and implementation approach.
  • Apply modern data platform architectures and data engineering best practices to build, implement, and optimize analytical data solutions including data lake, data warehouse, data lakehouse etc. with streaming and batch data processing and visualizations.
  • Identify opportunities for improvements and enhancements based on stakeholder feedback and help incorporate them into the overall technical strategy.
  • Anticipate, identify, and remove technical blockers through regular technical reviews and check ins to accelerate solution implementations.
  • Ensure that solution exhibits high levels of performance, security, scalability, maintainability, and evolvability upon deployment. Apply governance to identify, communicate, and minimize business and technical risks.

 

Technical Skills:

  • Strong communication and experience in managing various stakeholder relationships to get consensus on complex technical solutions.
  • Knowledge of Microsoft Well Architected Framework and Cloud Adoption Framework.
  • Strong Database development/management skills, with RDBMS (e.g. SQL Server, Oracle) as well as NoSQL database systems (e.g. MongoDb).
  • Knowledge and skills in other public cloud platforms like AWS and GCP.
  • Experience in open-source analytical data technologies such as Spark, Hadoop, HDFS, Hive, Kafka etc.
  • Programming skills in SQL, PySpark, Python, .Net, JavaScript etc.
  • Deep understanding of agile development methodologies like Scrum and Kanban.
  • Understanding of large program and project management processes and best practices.

 

Desired:

  • Hands-on experience in any of the following Technologies: Azure App Services, Azure Functions, Kubernetes/AKS/OpenShift, Azure storage, Service Bus, Azure SQL Database, Redis Cache, Azure Search, Azure Monitor, Application Insights, Traffic Manager, Key Vault, Cosmos DB, Azure DevOps, API Management, ARM templates, and general cloud governance and security mechanisms are required

 

LTI Mindtree Minds Enjoy:

  • Flexible working arrangements - work here there or anywhere!
  • Working on the most innovative project works!
  • Personal development to enhance your career!
  • Rewarding curiosity and collaboration!

 

LTI Mindtree minds are distinguished by their superior talent and mental agility marked by extreme ownership of transformative technologies in the digital age!

job.title: Senior Data Engineer
job.abstract: Play a key function in designing and implementing robust, secure and scalable corporate data solutions using AWS cloud technology
job.content:
Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principals that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named 2022 Top 10 Best Place to Work In Tech. We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

The Role

This role will report into the Data & Reporting Lead for Enterprise Applications and play a key function in designing and implementing robust, secure and scalable corporate data solutions using AWS cloud technology coupled with our tailored ELT tools for our internal partners (Finance, Sales Operations, Commercial Excellence, Marketing& HR) across the APAC region.

Key Responsibilities

  • Work in close collaboration with our partners and technical teams to architect, design, implement, test and handle leading data and analytics solutions.
  • Continuously supply to the improvement of SEEK’s data standards and guidelines.
  • Ensure all solutions conform to SEEK’s existing design patterns, architecture & data governance practices
  • Engage with partners to translate data requirements into technical specifications and recommend appropriate solutions
  • Proactively recommend technologies and practices that will allow SEEK to maintain its innovative platform while minimizing cost and improving performance
  • Provide partners with sophisticated support when solving issues
  • Facilitate technical design workshops and playbacks

The Team

The Enterprise Applications – Data team is a growing team of senior data specialists (Data Engineering & Business Intelligence (BI)) that support internal partners across the APAC region in designing and implementing corporate data solutions. You would be joining a fast paced, high-performance team of highly confident, intelligent and self-motivated individuals that value meritocracy and work in a collaborative and agile way to ensure the right outcomes for SEEK. The team manages the Corporate Data Hub (CDH) and currently pushes the boundaries when it comes to concepts such as Data Lakehousing.

    Qualifications

    Crucial Qualifications, Skills and Experience

    • Outstanding technical skills across cloud technologies (AWS), data modelling (Kimball/Data Vault 2.0), Programming (Python/SQL), Distributed Computing (Hadoop, Spark), Containerization (Docker), Orchestration (Airflow) & Infrastructure-as-Code (Cloudformation)
    • Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
    • A strong appreciation and experience with Data Management & Data Governance standard methodologies
    • A firm grasp of Data Warehousing & Data Lake concepts
    • Strong architectural capabilities when it comes to designing and implementing data solutions
    • Data analytics and diagnostics savvy, able to investigate root cause of identified data anomalies
    • Self-starter with the ability to work under stress, independently and manage multiple projects and task demands effectively

    Other Qualifications, Skills and Experience

    • Good communication & partner engagement skills
    • Successful record of delivering sophisticated data solutions in highly technical, fast-paced & ambiguous environments
    • Exposure to Kafka Streaming is a bonus

    Additional Information

    Permanent Perks
    At SEEK we offer:

    • Annual Performance Bonus Plan
    • Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and working from home depending on your role
    • Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
    • Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
    • SEEK are committed to operating sustainably, a certified carbon neutral business operation, with the target of 100% renewable energy by 2025, and net zero by 2030
    • The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
    • Free income protection insurance
    • Access to a wide range of discounts on things such as health insurance, fitness, food, travel, accommodation plus many more
    • Frequent events including sports days, family and friends’ day, hackathon, and trivia
    • Free kick-start breakfast every morning and fresh fruit available all day in our offices
    • Casual dress – every day

    Here at SEEK we pride ourselves on harbouring a flexible and inclusive working environment. Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

    For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

    At SEEK, the health and safety of our people is our highest priority. For this reason, SEEK has a policy requiring all new employees to be fully vaccinated for COVID-19, unless a formal medical exemption applies. On this basis, as part of the application process you will be asked to confirm that you have read and understood this policy and would like to continue with the hiring process.  Further details about this policy will be shared during the hiring process, as required.

job.title: Platform Engineer – Azure
job.abstract: Join an award-winning consultancy and work with the world’s largest organisations.
job.content:
Platform Engineer – Azure 

 

  • Hybrid workplace model
  • Melbourne location
  • Join a 30-year-old award winning growing tech consultancy
  • Permanent opportunity

 

About Us

We’re an innovative tech consultancy - a team of problem solvers. Since 1993 we’ve been finding better ways to solve complex technology problems for some of the world’s leading organisations and delivered solutions that millions of people use every day.

We bring together experts from diverse backgrounds and experiences in a collaborative and open culture to deliver outstanding outcomes for our clients, and a stimulating and rewarding environment for our people.

Our platform engineers design, build and maintain the delivery infrastructure, systems and processes underpinning technology transformation engagements and lead the adoption of modern platforms and ways of working.

 

As part of our continued growth we’re looking for versatile and experienced Platform Engineers to join us at our new location in Melbourne, Australia.

 

About the Role

We’re looking for hands-on platform engineers with deep understanding of the Azure ecosystem to join delivery teams working on some of the most exciting digital programmes around, with clients in a range of industries.

As an Azure expert, you'll work in small product teams alongside developers, architects, designers, analysts, and product owners to deliver automation, tooling, and cloud infrastructure.

We encourage continuous learning, so as well as the opportunity to work with some of the brightest and best in the industry, and evaluate the latest technologies, we’ll reward you for obtaining Azure certifications.

 

About You

You’ll have the expertise and confidence to lead the definition and support of the Azure delivery platform in complex engagements, typically working in multi-disciplinary teams on client site. You’ll have:

  • Commercial experience across designing, deploying and managing cloud environments in Azure.
  • Experience of containers and container orchestration using Docker, Kubernetes, and AKS.
  • Experience with infrastructure-as-code tools like Terraform, ARM Templates, Helm, or Pulumi.
  • Experience of pipeline build/deploy tools such as Azure DevOps, TFS, or Jenkins.
  • In-depth automation and scripting using tools such as PowerShell, AZ CLI, Python, Bash, Ruby, or Groovy.
  • Detailed knowledge of configuration management technologies like DSC, Puppet, Chef, SaltStack, or Ansible.
  • Thorough knowledge of logging and monitoring tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, Azure Monitor, Azure Log Analytics, Azure App Insights, New Relic, or Datadog.
  • Knowledge of cloud platform design patterns and best practices.
  • Knowledge of common database and caching technologies, such as Azure SQL, CosmosDB, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, MySQL/MariaDB, Memcache, or Redis.
  • Some knowledge of common programming languages used in modern web application development, such as C#, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, Go, or PHP.
  • Exposure to iterative/agile development methodologies and experience of enabling team delivery through technology.
  • As a bonus, experience of other cloud platforms and technologies.

 

If you don’t feel you match with all the above, we’re still interested! We have opportunities across a wide range of skill sets and levels in tech. More than anything, we’re excited about people who love technology and learning how to make it work. We’d really like to hear from you, and hopefully find you your dream job at BJSS.

 

Some of the Perks

  • A collaborative and inspiring environment working alongside some of the best tech people in the industry
  • Hybrid working – you can vary your working location to allow you to collaborate better, feed your creativity, and take the time and space to focus when you need it
  • Training opportunities and incentives – we support professional certifications across engineering and non-engineering roles
  • $400 new hire tech budget – kit out your home office to make sure you’re comfortable with hybrid working
  • Giving back – the ability to get involved nationally and regionally with partnerships to get people from different backgrounds into tech
  • An industry-leading referral scheme

 

BJSS is an award-winning technology and engineering consultancy for business.

 

As the winner of a Queen’s Award for Enterprise, we work with the world’s largest organisations, delivering the IT solutions that millions of people use every day.

 

http://www.bjss.com

https://www.bjss.com/joinus/

World's Best Management Consulting Firms (2022) by Forbes/Statista

job.title: Data Operations Engineer
job.abstract: Improve data maturity, contribute to uplifting enterprise data capability through the significant change program occurring in the agency.
job.content:
• Data Operations Engineer
  • $120 - $140 per hour (inc. super)
  • 24 + 12 month contract
  • Ability to obtain your Baseline security clearance
  • Civic, ACT
  • Data management, governance, quality, architecture, enterprise modelling, security and integration

Our client, a climate-focussed Federal Government department, requires a Data Operations Engineer for a long 24 + 12 month contract.

The Data Operations Engineer is responsible for the integrity of the production data utilised by employees by designing, creating and administering steps required to resolve or escalate issues that may prevent successful completion of scheduled production processes and data transfer, ensuring changes to the production environment have been reviewed and authorised.

This will be based onsite in Canberra, ACT, with flexible working arrangements available.

Duties

  • Improve data maturity, contribute to uplifting enterprise data capability through the significant change program occurring in the agency.
  • Supporting standards and modelling that improve data architecture.
  • Reduce regulatory burden, support self-service approaches, improve efficiency and encourage compliance with our schemes.
  • Consult on, design, build and/or roll out strategic initiatives that result in improvements to internal processes, data collection, client compliance, and communication related to scheme operations
  • Inspire front line teams to go beyond the standard “call of duty” to find creative solutions for our product issues.
  • Investigate and understand data anomalies.
  • Design web-based tools for business process management and automation.
  • Support the data requirements of the different business areas and processes including data management, governance, quality, architecture, enterprise modelling, security and integration.

Selection Criteria

  • Ability to scope and define data sets needed for specific use cases and identifying data gaps.
  • Ability to translate scientific insights into product decisions and work streams.
  • Knowledge and application of DMBOK data management frameworks and principals. 
  • Familiarity with star schemas and data vault modelling.
  • Experience using enterprise data modelling tools (LucidChart, EA Sparx, ERWin, ER Studio, etc).
  • Capability to create Conceptual, Logical and Physical data models for a range of technological solutions, databases and pipelines at an enterprise level in accordance with prescribed data modelling standards.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, with Attribute Based Access Control and deployments for Power BI.
  • Familiarity with DataOps and/or DevOps Repos & Pipelines, using Github, CI/CD and attribute-based Access Control and deployments for Power BI.
  • Demonstrated in-depth knowledge of data base infrastructure and cloud data solutions, preferably Azure suite (D365, SQL, Analysis Services, Power BI, Purview, Dataverse, Gen II data lake, Synapse, Data Factory).

To apply for this long Data Operations Engineer contract, please click the Apply to the Job button to send your CV to Andy at the Recruitment Hive. Please note this RFQ closes on the 10th of February and our Job ID is 7585

job.title: Cloud Data Engineer
job.abstract: Join our Customer & Data Enablement team to drive our Data Strategy to build cloud-based data assets like Marketing, Customer & Partner communications
job.content:
• Join the Better Big Bank to transform our MarTech and Data Analytics platforms
  • One of Australia's Biggest Banks - A top 100 ASX listed Company
  • Benefits includes flexible working, learning programs & discounts on banking

About us

With more than 160 years of history, we are proud of our position in the community with more satisfied customers than any other Australian bank.  Every day, we work hard to bring our company purpose to life, feeding into the success of our customers and communities and not off it. 

We're more than just a bank with banking products. We change the lives of customers and communities. Commercial actions with heart!

Our time is now. We are challenging the status quo and we're excited about our future!

About the role

We are transforming, moving to a cloud first model, modernising and simplifying and you can be part of that!  Join our Customer & Data Enablement team to enable the transition of our marketing analytics technology across to our team. You’ll join a fun, engaged and helpful team.

You will get the opportunity to work with the newest technologies (such as Acoustic, AWS & GCP), mentor others to see them improve their skills, whilst also having access to learning and development platforms plus the opportunity to get certified in cloud technologies.

We offer a hybrid and flexible ways of working. This role can be based anywhere in Australia near one of our locations.

Our community is a place to thrive in if you enjoy working in a changing environment and thinking of creative solutions.

You will be responsible for the development, testing and maintenance of the Bank’s Marketing Tech Stack to meet the organisation’s data requirements. It includes but not limited to automating and loading structured and unstructured data from internal or external, on-premises or cloud-based source systems to build and maintain digital marketing systems.

You will work closely with Digital Marketing teams, Technical Business Analysts and Product Specialists to deliver high performing end to end solutions for various Initiatives and platforms and proactively manage health and vitality of our MarTech assets.

In this role, you’ll get to:

  • Develop and maintain cloud data platforms required to service Marketing Automation and customer communications.  Work with stakeholders to understand their requirements, and continue to evolve functionality and resiliency
  • Focus on customers’ needs to drive behaviours and outcomes
  • Develop and maintain optimal data pipelines for a wide variety of data sources, structured or unstructured
  • Work with Practice Architects to understand C&DE Data Cloud Architecture Strategy
  • Work through a task, initiative, or project to ensure completion to achieve successful outcomes

About you

You will have experience working with Cloud Technologies and modern marketing automation suites and be experienced in writing code and scripts.  You’ll be experienced in working with Cloud providers and SAAS vendors.

To be successful in the role you will have:

  • Cloud based Data Platforms (AWS/GCP) and MarTech (Acoustic) experience would be ideal
  • Experience around handling structured and unstructured data
  • Experience with deployment of configuration code and/or data workloads using CI/CD tooling (ideally Gitlab, Terraform and Ansible)
  • Experience with streaming data pipelines and/or batch-oriented data processing
  • Working knowledge of Cloud Data Warehouses/Lakes, Information Governance Suites (Lineage, Glossary, Reference Data etc)
  • Exposure in advanced analytics and machine learning workloads

Why us?

There's so much more to a career with Bendigo and Adelaide Bank than just banking. 

Working with us opens the door to a whole lot more than a fee free account. Get real benefits, work life balance and flexibility. We offer various leave benefits as well as banking benefits which can you give cash back in your pocket, shopping discounts, novated leasing options and we can support financially if you wish to complete further studies.

Bring your brilliant mind and we’ll help you take your learning to the next level with on the job training and external development opportunities - we want you to shine. After all, YOU are the difference that makes us the better big bank.

At Bendigo and Adelaide Bank we believe a diverse workforce supported by an inclusive culture is central to our success and we actively encourage applications from those who bring diversity of thought to our business. We support candidate requests for adjustment to accommodate an illness, injury or disability to equitably participate in the selection process.

Be quick to apply! Applications will be reviewed as they are received and may close before the listed closing date.

job.abstract: A Solution Architect expertise in architectural design patterns and in-depth understanding of Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.
job.content:
A Solution Architect expertise in architectural design patterns and in-depth understanding of Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.

Job Title: Lead Solution Architect

Contract: Initial contract through 30 Aug 2023 with possible extensions

Location: Brisbane CBD

Our client is undertaking a significant multi-year digital transformation initiative to modernise its business systems, enable online service delivery and support a mobile workforce by implementing new Microsoft based systems and decommissioning legacy systems The initiative is being delivered using a lean agile methodology.

Job Summary

Our client is seeking an experienced Solution Architect to assist in the system continued development and application design for the existing Program Deliverables. The focus of this role will be to continue the development and maintenance of the systems solution architecture.

The Solution Architect will have a leadership role in the Program delivery. They will work with Program and Product management, other stakeholders, change and governance teams and lead the multidisciplinary development team to deliver a solution that meets the business requirements. The development team consists of D365 Functional and Technical and DevSecOps Consultants, testing resources, data resources and technical analysts amongst others. The Solution Architect will also engage collaboratively with the corporate Information Technology Services and other business areas also developing solutions in parallel.

They will need to have expertise in architectural design patterns and your in-depth understanding of Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.

Key Responsibilities

  • Lead and mentor technical teams in designing and developing complex solutions using Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365, while adhering to architectural design
  • Provide technical guidance and leadership to development teams and stakeholders, ensuring that solutions are designed and implemented to meet business requirements and are scalable, secure, and maintainable.
  • Create and maintain technical documentation, including architecture diagrams, design documents, and project plans.
  • Establish end-to-end architecture, design patterns and coding standards so that work is done to the highest possible quality and govern through code reviews
  • Ensure all work is thoroughly tested through manual/automated tests, including functional, non- functional, performance and resilience
  • Mentor Technical resource so that they become more effective in their role
  • Evaluate emerging technologies, frameworks and libraries to ensure coding standards and practices are aligned to industry standards
  • Present newly development functionality to stakeholders through Software demonstrations
  • Ensure that solutions are delivered on-time, within budget, and to the highest quality

Main requirements

  • Minimum 10 years experience producing Solution Architecture designs for medium and large sized business applications
  • Extensive experience with Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and
  • Demonstrated experience with:
    • implementing platform replacement of one or more of core business or business supporting applications
    • developing architecture documents in a format that technical and non-technical audiences can understand
    • developing architecture in a large portfolio with dependency adjacent projects in various states of delivery
    • working with technology and business stakeholders and supporting their respective standards, patterns and strategies
    • ensuring solutions are compliant with security and technology standards
    • leading and contributing to the development of architectural methods, processes, standards
    • reviewing architecture designs in a peer or governance format and providing feedback based on quality, risks and alternative options
    • an Microsoft application landscape including Microsoft Dynamics 365 Customer Service, Dataverse and PowerApps
  • architectural design patterns and best practices, including microservices, event-driven architecture, and serverless computing.
  • leading and mentoring technical teams in large-scale digital transformation
  • Proven high level negotiation, consultation facilitation and effective written and oral communications skills in a complex Agile program/project environment working with Product Managers, Product Owners and Delivery Teams.
  • Demonstrated experience in an Agile program/project environment managing Agile software requirements analysis activities, driving backlog refinements and ensuring user story Definition of Ready and Definition of Done requirements are met

Tech skills:

Enterprise grade DevOps

CI/CD Experience with Azure DevOps Pipelines

Infrastructure as code

Azure Resource Manager (ARM) / Bicep Templates

job.content:
• Opportunity to work on innovative projects
  • Be supported with benefits that fit your life, not just your career
  • Can be located in Canberra, ACT, Macquarie Park, NSW, Murarrie, QLD or Mawson Lakes, SA

Raytheon Australia is the nation’s leading provider of whole-of-life capabilities for the Australian Defence Force. With an in-country history spanning two decades, we have become a trusted capability partner for Australia’s defence.

At Raytheon Australia, we draw the brightest minds and give them work that excites them while continuously developing an environment for learning to maintain a highly-skilled, world-class workforce. The principles of trust, respect, collaboration, innovation, accountability, and a belief in the importance of health, safety and wellness underscore everything we do. Our diverse workforce delivers new and different perspectives, experiences and knowledge – and we believe that upholding the values of inclusiveness and diversity help us attract and retain the best talent in the Australian defence industry.

About the Role

The Data Engineer, Business Intelligence performs the critical roles of data ingestion and data management to facilitate reporting and analytics. This includes the complex problem solving and stakeholder engagement required to design and implement sustainable and efficient data solutions.

The role will be required to build and maintain close relationships with internal and external stakeholders to deliver system and process improvements.

Key Responsibilities

  • Acquire and prepare data and also manage the data platform residing in the data visualisation product.
  • Manage data ingestion processes / logic to ensure stable and reliable ingestion and transformation workflows.
  • Manage data bases, automations, and extract, transform, and load (ETL) processes.
  • Control holistic data architecture across all data sources.
  • Maintain data infrastructure such as databases and cloud repositories.
  • Facilitate the delivery of effective and timely business intelligence and analytics.
  • Enhance the understanding of the data environment available for business intelligence through data mapping.

Skills, Experience & Qualifications

  • 5 years prior relevant experience depending on tertiary qualifications.
  • Advance knowledge of extraction, transformation, and upload of data from multiple sources.
  • Experience using: Power BI, Azure Automation runbooks, SQL database staging tables, Custom Python code, .NET, MS Power Platform, MS Azure – Logic Apps and API calls, and ISE.
  • Practical knowledge of project management is desirable.
  • Desirable to have experience with customer liaison at a senior level, using Azure Purview and DevOps.
  • Must be an Australian Citizen and/or and the ability to obtain and maintain an Australian Government (Defence) Security Clearance – eligibility can be found at http://www.defence.gov.au/agsva

Be empowered to contribute to highly complex engineering projects that builds strength to our sovereign defence capability. 

With us, you’ll have the support of a talented team and a company that invests in your future. These are just some of the reasons why our people say we do great work and it’s great to #workhere. 

Click the "Apply" button below or contact us at careers@raytheon.com.au

job.title: Technical Lead Insights - Hawthorn East
job.abstract: The Technical Lead designs engineering solutions and ensures all parts incorporated with quality.
job.content:
We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

About the team

As the way we shop continues to evolve, our Digital team keeps us at the cutting edge. Driven by our innovative, inclusive and forward-thinking culture, we're constantly looking at ways to reinvent the shopping experience for our customers and build the next generation of digital retailing.

The Insights Team within the broader Coles Technology Team focuses on building data collection and analytics capabilities to uncover customer, product, and operational insights. Providing data driven support to our users and enabling Coles to be a data driven organisation.

About the role

We are embarking on engineering, enablement, operations, and delivery of key data initiatives, building them using market leading cloud technologies including Azure DevOps, Azure Data Factory, and Databricks.

The Technical Lead designs engineering solutions and ensures all parts of the technical design are correctly incorporated to provide technical support and technical quality control throughout all stages of the project.

You will mentor and guide teams to achieving great outcomes and maturing their capabilities, as well as overseeing all aspects of project deliverables including architecture and design to ensure all parts technical design are strategically aligned.

In addition, you will gather technical requirements and provide effort estimates and delivery timelines, as well as develop and deliver projects within the agreed timeframes and budgets. The role will also provide weekly status reports to management and other stakeholders.

You'll also:

• Resolve technical issues and ensure all parts of the technical design are correctly incorporated
• Provide technical support and technical quality control throughout all stages of the projects
• Oversee all aspects of project deliverables including architecture and design to ensure quality and strategic alignment
• Gather technical requirement and provide effort estimate and delivery timelines
• Design, develop, and deliver projects with high quality within the agreed timeframes and budgets


About you and your skills

We are looking for a dedicated and experienced Technical Lead with experience in managing the end-to-end project delivery and leading data solutions within both on-premises and cloud-based environment.

You will have previous experience in a similar role, offering ongoing support to functional and technical stakeholders working in a large, complex and data driven organisation.

You'll also need:

• Solid hands-on experience in Python and SQL essential
• Previously worked in at least one of these cloud technologies: Azure or AWS
• Proficiency in data pipelining, distributed data processing, software engineering components and data modelling concepts
• Exposure to CI/CD pipelines using a tech stack of Git and Azure
• Exposure to Data Factory and Databrick highly regarded but not essential
 

Take your next step into something bigger, apply now

With us it's not about the discounts (although you do get those), it's about joining a team where your wellbeing and professional development is invested in and celebrating your contributions is the norm. And because everyone leads unique lives, we offer flexible work including work from home, additional leave and parental leave entitlements.

We're continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that's just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We're happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. Find out more in the ‘Our Recruitment Process' section [link removed] of our careers site.

Safer together

We're committed to providing a safe environment for our team members and our customers. As part of that commitment, you will need to be vaccinated against COVID-19 before joining the team at Coles, unless you're medically exempt. You'll also need to disclose your COVID-19 vaccination status as part of your application (and possibly provide further evidence of your vaccination status). Thanks for applying, and for your understanding.

job.title: Data Engineering Analyst
job.abstract: Support Evolution through the analysis, interpretation and pipelining of data - to identify potential areas for delivering value
job.content:
About us

Evolution Mining was founded in late 2011 and has operations across Australia and in Ontario, Canada.

We currently operate five wholly owned operations across NSW, QLD, WA and Canada with a leadership team that continually focuses on embedding a values driven culture aligned with our company vision to create a premier, global gold company.

Our Group operations are based in Liverpool St. (Sydney CBD) providing support across all sites in several key areas including IT ensuring Evolution are positioned as a leader in effective optimisation of Information Technology.

About the role

This opportunity will allow the successful applicant to be professionally challenged and develop your skills within a fast-paced growth focused team and company. The role provides timely and effective support to the business and specifically the IT team in the analysis, interpretation and pipelining of data, supporting Evolution in identifying potential areas for delivering value by leveraging data.

You will understand the strategic direction of Evolution Mining and how insights from data can support strategy, enabling timely and accurate data-driven decisions across all aspects of the operation and performance via troubleshooting, provision of technical advice and delivery of improvement projects. Typical responsibilities with the role will include but not limited to:

  • Proactively gathering and conducting requirements analysis and documentation across stakeholders to improve processes and meet operational needs, including with our site-based teams.
  • Develop and design new data and analytic solutions, designing, implementing, and supporting analytics solutions including self-service in PowerBI
  • Test, and remain up to date with latest developments in relation to information systems and related technologies (automation, machine learning, predictive analytics, mixed reality, natural language processing etc.) and identify opportunities to leverage these developments for Evolution's gain.
  • Support change to the data and analytics infrastructure environment, working in a continuous improvement manner, focussed on outcomes and usability of data.
  • Commit to maintaining health, safety and security standards and principles, both within own workplace and through the identification of potential risks throughout Evolution.
  • Demonstrate behaviours aligned with the Evolution Mining values (Safety, Excellence, Accountability, Respect).
  • Develop ETL/ELT pipelines using Azure Data Factory and Databricks.
  • Develop Azure Data Factory objectives - ADF Pipeline, configuration, triggers, parameters, variables, Integration's services runtime.
  • Contribute strong understanding and technical skills across Azure.
  • Develop and maintain data models to support business objectives.
  • Monitor and troubleshoot data pipeline performance issues.

About you

Reporting to the Data Manager, to succeed in this role, you will tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Mathematics, IT or another relevant discipline combined with 3 years + proven experience in experience in Relational Database Systems development and integration; experience working with Business Intelligence / Data warehousing systems and applications (PowerBI and Qlik preferred) and one of the following programming languages: Python, Scala, R, C/C++, PowerShell, SQL

It is important that you have/ or can demonstrate:

  • Strong analytical skills with the ability to think logically and ‘join the dots' ideally in Mining/Heavy Industry that has both corporate functions and onsite operations, utilising data lakes and warehouses, preferably in a real time data environment.
  • Detail orientated with strong proficiency to build relationships combined with strong analytical and problem-solving capability, with the ability to multi-task.
  • Able to work at pace and manage multiple priorities simultaneously (utilising Agile Scrum methodologies) and be adaptive and responsive to change
  • Energetic, ambitious and results orientated.

What we offer

At Evolution we offer a range of employee benefits, that we review on a regular basis, ensuring we are listening to what our employees want. If successful, you can expect to receive the following:

  • Competitive salary package
  • Future opportunities to work in different business units, interstate and overseas
  • Short term incentive bonus
  • Complimentary life insurance and income protection
  • Referral bonuses available

This is a significant opportunity to further develop your professional development and attracts a highly competitive remuneration package including short term incentive. The role is based in Sydney CBD, with hybrid working with a requirement to travel to investor related functions as required.

Evolution recognises that climate change is one of the most pressing problems facing all of us and that we need to take serious action if we are to have a future business, clean and productive environment and healthy society. Evolution supports the Paris Agreement and is committed to be net zero by 2050, and an interim target of reducing our emissions by 30% by 2030.

We are an equal opportunity employer with a commitment to providing safe and inclusive work environments which allow our employees to be themselves. We support our employees' work-life integration and provide a stimulating environment to foster development and career growth.

We encourage candidates from diverse backgrounds to apply.

As part of the application process, Evolution will be collecting your personal information to assess your suitability for the role.

bullets: Opportunity to join a growing global mining organisation
A diverse and inclusive workplace culture
Industry competitive remuneration package + bonuses + benefits

job.abstract: Provide technical leadership for the implementation of data technical solutions that include Cloudera Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau
job.content:
Bluefin Resources are working with a prestigious federal government enterprise to recruit a Data Lead with strong technical expertise on Cloudera Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau for an initial 10 month contract with further extensions.

Job Details:

An opportunity to become part of a strategic initiative at a federal government enterprise to uplift the data management practice by rolling out advanced data technology solutions.

POSITION PRIMARY PURPOSE

Provide technical leadership for implementation of data technology solutions, including but not limited to Cloudera Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau that meet business requirements and align with the enterprise architecture and standards.

POSITION OBJECTIVES

  • Working closely with the architects and various IT teams, provide technical leadership to implement Cloudera Data Platform on the Azure Cloud; Tableau and other data and analytical solutions for the enterprise.
  • Perform systems analysis, produce detailed designs, architecture documents and seek approvals for the new systems ensuring compliance with the relevant IT standards.
  • Evaluate and undertake impact analysis on design options and assess associated risks.
  • Ensure that the designs balances functional, service quality and systems management requirements.
  • Work with the program teams and other related teams in IT, Business and Enterprise Data Office to ensure the requirements are well understood; and solutions are implemented as designed and intended.
  • Enhance the availability, security and performance of the solutions by creating compliant processes, security measures, standards and best practices.
  • Provide input to project planning, scheduling, estimation, status reporting and risk and issue resolution.
  • Support the systems through problem resolution, debugging and system enhancements, especially around implementation and warranty period.
  • Provide advice, guidance and assistance to less experienced colleagues as required.

QUALIFICATIONS, ACCREDITATIONS AND KNOWLEDGE

  • Degree qualifications, accreditations or certifications relevant to BI Technology.
  • Knowledge of BI Technology including Cloudera (Hadoop) Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau. Knowledge of Power BI, RStudio, Python, ETL Tools is desirable but not mandatory.
  • Knowledge of Azure architecture and design standards.
  • Advanced Knowledge of the System Development Life Cycle.
  • Understanding of industry trends, technologies and best practices.

EXPERIENCE

  • Proven experience in the following technologies: Azure Cloud, Cloudera Data Platform and Tableau is a must have. RStudio, Python and ETL experience is desirable.
  • Experience in authentication and access control principles and implementation.
  • Experience in defining and implementing information architectures and systems.
  • Experience in migrating and implementing BI Solutions in the Cloud.
  • Experience using Microsoft tools: Visio, Azure Dev Ops and Visual Studio.
  • Experience in writing and reviewing technical documentation.

On Offer - This is an initial 10 month contract with a high chance of extensions. Flexible working options available for the right candidate.

You will work with a great and well-established team and be part of something meaningful and rewarding where you will make a real difference!
