job.title: Senior Azure Engineer
job.abstract: Intuit Technologies’ Microsoft Cloud and Development Practice
job.content:
About the job

We are currently searching for an experienced Senior Azure Engineer to join our team. 

 

The Role

The Senior Azure Engineer is a key member of Intuit Technologies’ Microsoft Cloud and Development Practice. They are responsible for designing, implementing, and managing Azure-based solutions for clients. The Senior Azure Engineer acts as a subject matter expert on Azure-based solutions and provides guidance to clients using best practices, such as the Microsoft Well Architected Framework and Azure Landing Zone Architecture.

Key Responsibilities will include:

  • Acting as a key subject matter expert on Azure-based solutions 
  • Provide guidance to clients about best practice 
  • Design, implement and support Azure-based solutions including 
    • Networking (including Express Route, VPN, Virtual Networks and Private Endpoints),
    • Platform services (i.e. SQL, Storage, App Services, Kubernetes)
    • Infrastructure services (Virtual Machines, Azure Virtual Desktop) 
    • Security (Azure Defender for Cloud, Sentinel, Azure Policies, Azure AD Security features such as PIM and Conditional Access).
  • Understand security standards such as Essentials 8, NIST and ISO 27001. 

 

The Person

To be successful in this role, you will need to have: 

  • Strong understanding of Azure services, including
    • Networking (including Express Route, VPN, Virtual Networks and Private Endpoints),
    • Platform services (i.e. SQL, Storage, App Services, Kubernetes)
    • Infrastructure services (Virtual Machines, Azure Virtual Desktop) 
    • Security (Azure Defender for Cloud, Sentinel, Azure Policies, Azure AD Security features such as PIM and Conditional Access).
  • Experience with Azure Resource Manager (ARM) or Bicep templates, Azure DevOps, and PowerShell
  • Understanding of and ability to design solutions in line with the Azure Landing Zone Architecture
  • Understanding of Essential 8 security requirements and experience implementing them
  • Strong communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively with client development teams
  • Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills
  • Strong consulting and documentation skills, with the ability to help customers work through their requirements and document these within a design document

 

Intuit Technologies

We are a people-focused business! When you partner with Intuit Technologies you gain access to our extensive capabilities to design and deliver bespoke technology solutions. Our goal is to help our clients turn their ICT investment into a business strength. We provide extensive services, including professional consultancy, procurement and logistics, expert project services and project management, managed services, and resourcing. 

People choose Intuit Technologies because they are choosing an established company that has been in business for over 25 years and with a team of over 130 strong (and growing). We deploy our breadth of knowledge across a variety of industries and are a people-focused business as we recognise our people are our most significant differentiator. 

 

Attitude comes before everything else. 

We are passionate about our work, our environment, and our brand. People join us because they want to be here, around our people. We hire the best, work hard, and aim to deliver excellence in everything that we do. We believe that leadership is not just a management role, but a role for everyone. We seek people who are not afraid to make an incredible difference.

 

 If this aligns with your values and you feel you have the skills and experience to match the above criteria for this exciting and rewarding role, please apply.

 

DISCLAIMER - We'll keep your resume on file for future job opportunities if you are unsuccessful for this position. If you would prefer that we do not keep your resume on file please email hr@itechnologies.com.au.

job.title: Manager - Digital & Tech Risk Advisory
job.abstract: Deloitte is looking for strategically minded consultants to join our dynamic and fast-growing team
job.content:
Company description:

Deloitte Services Pty Ltd



Job description:

Description:
Deloitte Risk Advisory's Digital and Technology Risk team is looking for top performing, strategically minded consultants to join our dynamic and fast-growing team. We aim to help enable our clients to:

1. Better understand and embrace the risk associated with their current IT and Digital evolution.
2. Design, implement and govern smarter, data driven, lean digital process and control environments harnessing cutting edge cloud and robotic solutions
3. Gain assurance that their digital environments will help them achieve their business objectives and meet and manage their risk and regulatory requirements.

The nature of engagements we deliver are broad and can relate to nearly all aspects of technology operations and transformation from risk assessments, process and control design, governance and reporting to regulatory compliance and assurance and are delivered across a range of industries including Financial Services, Public Sector, Consumer, Energy and Resources. This means we require individuals that are passionate and inquisitive about all different types of emerging technology and are keen help find smarter and safer ways of enabling effective adoption of them.

What will your typical day look like?

We are looking for a top performing Digital and Technology Risk professional to join this dynamic and fast-growing team to help us meet the current market demand for digital and technology risk management. As a member of our team the types of work you will be involved in include:
• Support clients in leading and supporting technology delivery and operations and in responding to risk, audit, and regulatory challenge
• Support the assessment, design, development and delivery of process, risk and control management capabilities working with stakeholders across Business, Technology, Digital, Security, Risk, Audit, and Assurance functions
• Help lead the execution of client engagements through structured problem solving, effective time management and providing junior staff with the support and guidance needed to deliver high quality outcomes
• Build authentic and trusted relationships with our clients and the broader Deloitte firm.
• Mentor and coach staff throughout the stages of their career

Enough about us, let's talk about you.

You are someone with:
• 5+ years of technology risk management experience in a consulting/professional services environment
• 1-2 years of experience in leading/mentoring teams and performance management
• Hands on technology risk management methods, governance, and assurance
• Worked within risk, control, or assurance BAU functions or on large scale digital transformation or technology change management programs
• Experience in utilising data to inform technology risk management decisions and reporting
• Ability to think creatively, generate innovative ideas, question the status quo, and deliver effectively against challenging objectives.
• Experience in growing a Digital and Technology Risk practise through effective business development is a must
• Strong communication skills, both written and verbal
• Proficient with MS PowerPoint, Excel, and other relevant software

The Star Entertainment Group is looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join our Architecture and Engineering team within our Information Technology Group.

As the Senior Data Engineer, you will be accountable for assisting with the maintenance of the data platforms (CDW, ACE, and MDM) and related data integration platforms (Informatica, Striim) from an operational and strategic point of view. You will be responsible for assisting with the maintenance and development of the roadmap and strategy for the data platforms and data integration platforms.

Reporting to the Data Engineer Manager, the key to success in this role involves taking responsibility for all stages in the design and implementation of Data Platform and Data Integration Platform development work, as well as developing, documenting, and maintaining platform-based standards and ensuring compliance.

Your key priorities will involve:

  • Develop, document, and maintain platform-based standards, advise on their application and implementation, and ensures compliance

Our benefits

  • Both parental and secondary carers leave available to all employees
  • 30% Discounts across award winning restaurants and accommodation
  • Lifestyle discounts including gym memberships and dry-cleaning services

  • Groupwide Diversity and Inclusion strategy for LGBTQI, Gender, Culture and Indigenous

To be successful in this role you will have:

  • Hands-on experience developing solutions using Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Blob Storage, SQL Server, Azure SQL DW
  • Demonstrated experience implementing solution designs and end to end development

About us

The Star Entertainment Group’s vision is to be Australia’s leading integrated resort company. Attracting 18 million guests each year, The Star Entertainment Group’s properties across Sydney, Brisbane and the Gold Coast are world class tourist destinations that offer visitors a diverse selection of award-winning restaurants, bars, cafes, accommodation, and entertainment options.

job.title: Enterprise Data Architect
job.abstract: We’re seeking Enterprise Data Architect for 6 contract role–based in MEL with possible extn. #JoinASAP
job.content:
NTT is a leading global IT solutions and services organisation that brings together people, data and things to create a better and more sustainable future. In today’s ‘iNTTerconnected’ world, connections matter more now than ever. By bringing together talented people, world-class technology partners and emerging innovators, we help our clients solve some of the world’s most significant technological, business and societal challenges. With people at the heart of our success, NTT is committed to attracting and growing the best talent and providing an environment where everyone feels they can belong and their contribution matters.

 

Want to be part of the team?

You will join one of the world's largest teams of data scientists, data engineers, and experts in machine learning and AI. In just about every industry, you will be solving big problems using the latest tech. We believe a mix of data, analytics, automation, and responsible AI can do almost anything—spark digital metamorphoses, widen the range of what humans can do, and breathe life into intelligent products and services.

 

Your day at NTT

  • Leading and delivering advisory and consulting engagements in data strategy and architecture and governance
  • Assuming the role of a trusted advisor for our clients across various facets of data and analytics strategy.
  • Creating and curating the data and analytics initiatives roadmap including migrating off on-premise data and analytics platform into cloud.
  • Provide thought leadership on how clients can best leverage and utilise data to enhance business value and create new opportunities.
  • Assuming the role of the subject matter expert in cloud architecture patterns and building and expanding a data platform
  • Building consensus among customer’s solution architects and other technical stakeholders on appropriate architecture patterns
  • Assessing the maturity, capability, and architecture of client organisations and developing strategies and roadmaps to support their implementation.
  • Assisting clients in defining and implementing data architecture building blocks and architecture patterns across the data landscape.
  • Designing analytics frameworks, data architectures to support transformation and data platform modernisation
  • Support and mentor other team members through peer review’s knowledge sharing sessions and relevant training

 

 

What would make you a good fit for this role?

  • Experience of advising customers in adoption of modern cloud-based data and analytics platforms, data governance frameworks, associated practices and processes
  • Highly developed stakeholder management skills with a proven ability to establish strong working relationships at an executive level, across multiple clients
  • Excellent written and oral communication skills with the ability to explain and present data governance concepts to a business or technical audience
  • Hands on experience developing data-centric/data-driven transformation strategies in complex technology landscapes
  • Good understanding of key data governance concepts such as data architecture, data modelling, data quality, master data, metadata management, data lineage, privacy and security etc
  • Indepth understanding of a modern data platform and its end-to-end components such as data lakes, data pipelines, data warehousing, business intelligence, data science etc
  • Familiarity with data and management tooling such as Azure cloud platform, Databricks, SAP Hana, Oracle EDW, PowerBI etc
  • Knowledge and subject matter expertise of data focused best practices and emerging trends

 

Mandatory Non-Technical Skills/ Experience:

  • Excellent written and communication skills
  • Ability to work autonomously or with cross-functional teams or squads
  • Ability to identify pain-points from both technical and non-technical customer stakeholders
  • A pro-active approach to solving problems and the ability to readily engage with stakeholders
  • Has worked on agile based projects
  • Able to work within a team of like-minded, dedicated and passionate technologists
  • Must have at least 10 years of experience in leading or contributing to large and complex data platform modernisation initiatives

 

Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us. Apply today.

 

Career at NTT means:

  • Being part of a global pioneer – where you gain exposure to our Fortune 500 clients and world-leading global technology partners and work with a network of over 40,000 smart and diverse colleagues across 57 countries, delivering services in over 200 countries.
  • Being at the forefront of cutting-edge technology – backed with a 150-year heritage of using technology for good. With 40% of the world’s internet traffic running on our network and where Emoji were first invented, you can be proud of the group’s many new ‘firsts’.
  • Making a difference – by doing meaningful work that helps to shape the future for our clients, and across industries and communities around the world.
  • Being your best self – in a progressive ‘Connected Working’ environment that promotes flexibility, connection, and wellbeing. Where diversity and different perspectives are embraced to ensure equal opportunities for all.
  • Having ongoing opportunities to own and develop your career – with a personal and professional development plan and access to the broadest learning offerings in the industry.

 

 

 



Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us. Apply today.

For more information about this or other opportunities, please contact Neha Jhingan . Please quote our job reference number 580170.

About us

NTT Ltd. is a leading global technology services company. Working with organizations around the world, we achieve business outcomes through intelligent technology solutions. For us, intelligent means data driven, connected, digital and secure. As a global ICT provider, we employ more than 40,000 people in a diverse and dynamic workplace that spans 57 countries, trading in 73 countries and delivering services in over 200 countries and regions

NTT is proud to be an equal opportunity employer with a global culture that embraces diversity. We are committed to providing an environment free of unfair discrimination and harassment. We do not discriminate based on age, race, color, sex, religion, national origin, disability, pregnancy, marital status, sexual orientation, gender reassignment, veteran status, or other protected category.

Raytheon Australia is trusted by the Australian Defence Force to deliver some of the nation’s most complex technology and engineering projects to keep our defence on the leading edge.

The principles of trust, respect, collaboration, innovation, accountability, and a belief in the importance of health, safety and wellness underscore everything we do. 

Our diverse workforce delivers new and different perspectives, experiences and knowledge – and we believe that upholding the values of inclusiveness and diversity help us attract and retain the best talent in the Australian defence industry.

About the Role

The Data Engineer, Business Intelligence performs the critical roles of data ingestion and data management to facilitate reporting and analytics. This includes the complex problem solving and stakeholder engagement required to design and implement sustainable and efficient data solutions.

The role will be required to build and maintain close relationships with internal and external stakeholders to deliver system and process improvements.

job.content:
About Hollard

Hollard Insurance is part of the Hollard Group of Companies and a top 5 General Insurer in Australia and New Zealand. We underwrite a broad range of general insurance products, including motor, home, contents, business, and pet. Hollard’s unrelenting focus on diversity and inclusion, collaborative partnerships, and delivering great customer outcomes is at the heart of its business model, driven by its purpose of “Using our expertise, integrity and humanity to go further, together" 

The Role

Hollard is developing its Data Management capability and establishing a team that has the exciting task of establishing the data foundations for the company. You will be surrounded by data professionals that strive for excellency and data best practices to realise business value. You will have the opportunity to apply your knowledge in a green field and drive change.

Reporting to the Head of Data Management the key focus areas will be: 

  • Provide significant input into the strategical, technical and data engineering direction of the Hollard’s Data team and Data Platform.
  • Establish and enforce data engineering standards and frameworks to enable the implementation of a robust data platform. These include metadata framework, code versioning and management, reconciliation framework, platform monitoring, CD/CI pipelines, platform monitoring, environment management principles, etc.
  • Supervise internal and external engineering teams to build products and/or infrastructure required to support scalable data products, providing effective guidance for analysis, design, programming, and testing skills.
  • Engage with data modellers to verify that conceptual views of the data are translated into efficient data models considering definition of keys, indexes, table partitioning, virtualisation, etc.

Knowledge acquired awareness and/or expertise

  • Bachelor’s or master’s degree in computer/data science technical or related field.
  • Demonstrable Azure experience is required (3+ years)
  • Related certifications are preferable (e.g., Azure Data Fundamentals, Azure Data Engineer Associate). Snowflake knowledge is desirable.
  • Demonstrable experience delivering data projects in the data engineering space including data lakes, data warehouses, MDMs, data integration, data marts, ODS, BI & Analytics, content management, enterprise archives, and/or data management platforms

Working at Hollard

At Hollard you will be part of a supportive, valued and committed team. You will enjoy a challenging and rewarding work environment, career progression opportunities and great staff benefits and corporate discounts. We also offer many benefits to support your professional development and wellbeing including:

  • Professional and technical development opportunities
  • Flexible start and finish times, working from home, and other flexible work options to suit your lifestyle
  • Competitive remuneration and annual incentives program
  • 18 weeks gender neutral paid parental

  • Generous employee insurance discounts

  • Wellbeing benefits e.g. vaccinations, health insurance discounts, mental wellness training professional memberships, EAP,

Hollard is unapologetically committed to creating a workplace that values your diversity with a true sense of inclusion.  We actively seek to hire for your different lived experiences (including as relate to disability, ethnicity, faith, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, gender diversity, sexual orientation, age, neurodiversity).  These enhance cognitive diversity and psychological safety in our workplace for everyone. 

Hollard proudly promotes flexible work including remote work, non-traditional work patterns, and work-family balance. 

Even if you don’t meet all our selection criteria, we encourage you to apply.

Please note that a full background check will be completed on the successful applicant.

job.title: Analytics Engineer - Snowflake
job.abstract: Provide stakeholders with well-defined, transformed, tested and documented data assets, and build data-driven decision making into the organisation.
job.content:
• Be a part of Australia's independent national broadcaster
  • Permanent, full-time role

The ABC strives for diversity and inclusion in the workplace, and to promote a culture of opportunity. Through its services the ABC seeks to represent, connect and engage with all of the Australian community. In line with our focus on diversity, applications are strongly encouraged from Indigenous Australians, people from a range of cultural and linguistic backgrounds, people with disability and LGBTIQA+ individuals. The ABC also aims to achieve a gender-balanced workforce.

For more information about working at the ABC, please feel free to explore our careers page at https://www.abc.net.au/careers/

About the ABC

The ABC is the nation's most trusted and independent source of Australian conversations, culture, and stories. With over 4,000 employees from diverse backgrounds across over 50 locations around Australia and overseas, we are proud to create, curate and deliver high-quality content that informs, educates and entertains Australian communities.

About the Role

Our close-knit, Enterprise Data & Analytics team is seeking an Analytics Engineer to provide stakeholders with well-defined, transformed, tested and documented data assets, enabling ABC to maximise value from its data and build data-driven decision making into the organisation. As part of a small team, you will contribute significantly to the design, implementation, and support of enterprise data & analytics solutions. This highly specialised role will provide you the opportunity to:

  • Perform data profiling techniques to validate datasets, understand data quality characteristics and document any data quality issues, providing recommendations for their treatment.
  • In collaboration with the Data Architect and Enterprise Data & Analytics team, outline solution design for data and analytics requests, including but not limited to; data acquisition and transformation patterns, data models, source-to-target mapping, and reporting specifications.
  • Lead the data modelling capability by applying best practice techniques to model source data into integrated, reusable and well documented data assets that enable analytics.
  • Write SQL scripts, stored procedures, and views to transform source data to target model supporting dashboards and self-service reporting.
  • Lead data testing activities, ensuring data is validated and reconciled to specified data harnesses.
  • Develop enterprise data domain knowledge to further leverage and enhance analytics solutions and undertake root cause analysis to resolve data challenges.
  • Ensure enterprise data assets are discoverable and understood consistently, through the collection and management of technical and business metadata.
  • Proactively identify opportunities for enhancements and refinements of Data Governance and Data Management practices, processes and standards; and take appropriate action as required.
  • Increase data literacy and drive an uplift in data culture through undertaking data and analytics training and support as required across the ABC.
  • Provide operational BAU support of existing enterprise data & analytics solutions.

About You

If you are a natural problem solver and a keen communicator that enjoys proactively seeking solutions, we'd love to hear from you! You will be able to demonstrate extensive experience in the following:

  • Specialised knowledge in data modelling and experience in implementing most complex data models and data transformations within a data warehouse.
  • Significant experience in using on-premise or cloud-based Data Integration, Data Warehouse and Analytics and reporting technologies such as AWS, SQL Server, Azure, Talend, Snowflake, Power BI, and Tableau.
  • Creating data assets, including scoping, designing, developing, testing and operational support.
  • Significant knowledge and understanding of the principles of information lifecycle management (ILM); data ingestion, data modelling, lineage, SQL databases, master data management (MDM), data quality management (DQM), and data retention rules.

You're willing to learn and be a valued member of a team, open to upskilling to cover for other positions when needed. You will also have:

  • A good reputation for excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with strong attention to detail, and highly developed communication and interpersonal skills in a large and complex organisation.
  • Significant hands-on experience of end-to-end data project delivery across stakeholder engagement, scoping, requirements gathering, analysis, design, testing, BAU transition and support.
  • Some experience or interest in learning ETL tools to maintain data pipelines.
  • Awareness of visualisation tools, dashboard design and dashboard development principles.

For further details on the role and requirements, please refer to the full position description: 50012778 ANALYTICS ENGINEER.pdf

For further information on this position please contact on Alison Burgis, Manager, Enterprise Data & Analytics at Burgis.Alison@abc.net.au. We are unable to accept email applications, please ensure that you submit your application via the online portal.

We respectfully request that Recruitment Agencies do not submit applications for this position.

The ABC has a vaccination policy that requires employees to meet vaccination requirements for those working in some high-risk environments or circumstances. Some roles will require adherence to this policy as an inherent requirement of performing the role.

Applications Close: 11:55 pm, Sunday 12th March.

job.title: Microsoft BI Consultant
job.abstract: Leverage your expert skills and enterprise experience with MSBI, Power BI, Tableau, SQL Server + Azure data tools (Data Factory, Data Bricks etc.)
job.content:
As some with significant professional work experience in Business Intelligence (BI) and Analytics and an expert with SQL Server, Microsoft BI (MSBI) - SSIS / SSRS / SSAS, Power BI... and ideally experience in Azure data tools, you understand the value of data to help solve business problems.
You will also have a passion for data visualisation whether it's developing models, prototypes, reports or dashboards.

You’re happy to roll up your sleeves and see projects through from end-to-end including mapping business processes, conduct requirements analysis and documentation. Most importantly you understand that your role is all about helping our clients source, transform and interpret data into actionable metrics to optimise their business.

Our team of broadly experienced Consultants, work on a diverse portfolio of client, projects, and innovation initiatives - some of which will make you the envy of your peers.
  

Applicants MUST hold Australian Citizenship, Permanent Residency (PR), or other permanent work rights.



Required skills and experience:
  • Previous experience in a similar role as a Microsoft BI / Analytics Specialist
  • Advanced skills in SQL Server
  • Significant, commercial, hands-on experience across the Microsoft BI stack (SSIS, SSRS, SSAS)
  • An expert in Power BI
  • Experience working in a complex enterprise data warehouse environment
  • Solid Agile environment experience
  • Knowledge and experience of DWH, BI, and analytics best practice
  • Ability to develop requirements into actionable business analytics strategies, roadmaps, and BI solutions
  • Able to quickly build strong relationships with decision-makers, and become their trusted advisor
  • Knowledge of Azure data tools; Databricks, Data Factory, Data Lake etc. Python and R would be beneficial, but are not essential
  
Working at DWS offers you:
  • Ongoing professional and career development
  • Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses
  • An active social club that host regular, subsidised events
  • Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, Apple products and much more 

About Us: 
Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCL Technologies. With offices across Australia, we have over 800 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation.


Applicants must hold Australian Citizenship, Permanent Residency (PR), or other permanent work rights.



Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now!
www.dws.com.au

No agencies please – our in-house talent acquisition team have this covered.

This role is open to candidates who aren't the finished article but have a hunger for learning and career progression or an senior engineer looking to work on the latest tech and be required to take the lead in shaping an advanced analytics capability and help create the data solutions that bring the analytical edge to the business.

job.title: ETL Engineer - Dataiku
job.abstract: Build ETL flows on Dataiku using your Python & SQL skills.
job.content:
As a Data Engineer you will be responsible for building ETL flows on Dataiku as well as the creation of tools (python-based) on Dataiku to allow the business to use a self-service ETL platform. You will leverage your strong python skills to build and use workflow orchestration processes on Dataiku, prior experience with other workflow orchestration tools such as Apache Airflow would be beneficial. These processes will require modern development standards such as Test-Driven Development, use of microservices and consideration of data governance/lineage. 

 The role will involve the creation and management of CI/CD pipelines so prior experience with GIT and version management is required. Also, use of Big Data tools, particularly the Apache stack (Impala, Hive, Spark) for ingesting data to and from Data Warehouses and Data Lakes. Prior experience with cloud services is required, particularly AWS, part of the role will involve interacting with S3 buckets and so knowledge of the CLI/bash scripting and general file management best practices. Is necessary Given that much of the role involves integrations with Dataiku, mastery of this platform will be a core function. 

 To be successful in this role you will have: 

  • Experience with python including libraries such as pandas and pyspark as well as testing frameworks, linting and use of object-oriented functionality such as classes 
  • Experience with SQL, particularly on large datasets
  • Experience with the CLI/bash scripting language
  • Experience with Big Data and knowledge of data management techniques eg partitioning, file compression 
  • Experience with Big Data technologies such as Apache Spark, Impala and Hive 
  • Experience with cloud platforms, preferably AWS but including Azure and GCP
  • Management of CI/CD processes (eg Jenkins, Bamboo, CircleCI, TeamCity) and use of Git version management such as Bitbucket, GitHub, Gitlab etc
  • Understanding od DevOps concepts and when to apply them to data transformation (or DataOps) 
  • Familiarity with agile methodology, particularly the use of Jira and Confluence, particularly when working across several large projects
  • Good communication and stakeholder management skills

 If this sounds like the right opportunity to further your career, please apply via the portal.

About the Corporate Operations Group

The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, and the Macquarie Group Foundation. We deliver service excellence to ensure Macquarie is open for business, deliver on transformational change, invest in our people and have deep relationships with our customers.

At Macquarie, we support a hybrid working model.

Our commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion 

The diversity of our people is one of our greatest strengths. An inclusive and equitable environment enables us to deliver innovative and sustainable outcomes for our people, clients, shareholders and communities. From day one, you'll be encouraged to be yourself and supported to perform at your best. If our purpose of ‘empowering people to innovate and invest for a better future’ is as inspiring to you as it is to us, please apply. With the right technology, support and resources, our people can work in a range of flexible ways.

We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We encourage candidates to speak with a member of our recruitment team if you require adjustments to our recruitment process to support you, and the type of working arrangements that would help you thrive.

job.title: Data Analyst AND Data Engineer required for large program of work Defence
job.content:
On behalf of my clients in the Defence sector, I am currently sourcing an experienced Data Analyst AND a Data Engineer for a large program of work in the Defence space.

All candidates must be NV1 or above cleared and my clients are able to consider candidates who are happy be office based in Canberra, Melbourne or Sydney.

The roles are both being offered as 12 month day rate contracts with view of extension way beyond this.

I have detailed the role descriptions and requirements for each below.

If you are interested in being considered and have the experience required please Apply Now with a copy of your updated resume together with a cover letter as to how your skills / experience align and I will be in contact to discuss further. Alternatively please send an email for the attention of Sarah to jobs@tenacitycx.com.au

 

DATA ANALYST - ROLE OVERVIEW

The Data Analyst & Modeller is responsible for designing data assets and ensuring they meet the needs of our customers and the business.  A major part of the role will be working to understand current and future use cases, requirements and translating those requirements into logical data models. The data modeller designs, implements, and documents data architecture and data modelling solutions, which include the use of relational, dimensional, and NoSQL databases. These solutions support enterprise information management, business intelligence, machine learning, data science, and other business interests.

Key Skills / Experience Required:

  • Experience with a range of vendors and tools, and on premise and cloud infrastructure or services, including: Microsoft Azure, Tableau, Cognos, Power BI and UX Design.
  • Experience with Agile delivery methodologies.
  • Modelling experience for analytical/OLAP systems - preferably Cloud Native Database(s) including Terradata, Oracle, SQL Server, DB2
  • Excellent interpersonal, oral and written communication skills with extensive experience explaining and presenting complex technical concepts to both Business and Technology focussed senior stakeholders.
  • Proven ability to develop and manage enduring client relationships, engendering a sense of trust and respect.
  • Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills with an ability to build credibility with senior leaders and internal working teams.
  • Experience working with Department of Defence, professional services or similar Federal Government department experience required.

Additional Notes:

  • NOT a visualisation or statistical modelling or machine learning role. Similarly PowerBI and Python are not important as this stage.   
  • Experience in Data Warehousing and Database Modelling, such as dimension tables and ERD. 
  • Experience in building Data Models, Star Schema for large data sets highly advantageous.

 

DATA ENGINEER - ROLE OVERVIEW:

The Data Engineer is the designer, builder and manager of the information or data management pipelines, preparing data for analytical or operational use. You have an aptitude for translating business problems into data & infrastructure/resource requirements and solutions. You will design, construct, test and maintain data pipelines to pull together information from different source systems, pipelines which integrate, consolidate, cleanse and monitor the data. You will actively ensure the stability and scalability of our clients’ systems and data platforms. You will strive to bring the best of DevOps practices to the world of data by embracing the emerging practice of DataOps.  

RESPONSIBILITES:

  • Drive a technical roadmap for the team, covering non-functional requirements such as scalability, reliability and observability
  • Assess new and existing data sources on their applicability to address the business issue and translate the outcomes of the analytical solutions we design in the context of business impacts and benefits.
  • Design, construct, install, test and maintain highly scalable, resilient, recoverable data management systems by bringing a software engineering mindset and applying DataOps principles 
  • Automate the build deployment of data pipelines using and DevOps and CI/CD patterns, including defining what tests are required and can be automated at each stage of the lifecycle of a data pipeline.
  • Understand, explain and evangelize buzz words such as serverless, cloud native and PaaS and how they impact the design of Data Pipelines
  • Be comfortable with code or tool-based data pipelines and understand the pro and cons of each.
  • Work closely with Data Scientists to extract and manipulate data from a variety of sources and subsequently cleanse, standardize, scale, bin, categorize, tokenize, stem and transform it in order to get the data into a state suitable for further analysis. 
  • Select and configure analytics toolsets considering the clients’ business issue and analytic maturity.

KEY SKILLS / EXPERIENCE REQUIRED:

  • Knowledge of architecting and engineering cloud-based data solutions with the following products 
  • Teradata – Priority Technologies
  • Oracle Data Integrator (ODI) – Priority Technologies
  • Informatica – Highly Desirable 
  • Snowflake
  • Cloud platforms with a focus on Paas or Serverless:
  • AWS: Redshift/RDS, S3, EC2, Lambda, step, EMR, Glue, DynamoDB, Athena, Kinesis, Cloudwatch, SQS, SNS, fargate
  • OR Azure: Blob storage, Synapse, Data Factory, Functions, CosmosDB, Databricks, log analytics, Event hub, Azure Kubernetes Service
  • Big Data technologies such as Hadoop, Spark Streaming, Flink, Hudi, Storm, NiFi, HBase, Hive, Zepplin, Kafka, Ranger, Ambari.
  • Programming languages such as Java, Node, C#, Go, Python, Scala, SAS, R. – Priority Technologies
  • ETL tool experience – Highly Desirable 
  • Experience with DevOps principles and tools, including:
  • Continuous Integration/Delivery tools such as Jenkins, AWS code, Azure DevOps or other similar industry tools
  • Experience with SQL-based technologies (e.g. PostgreSQL and MySQL) and NoSQL technologies (e.g. Cassandra and MongoDB)
  • Experience of Data lake and Data warehousing solutions and architectures and low-level design principles
  • Data modelling tools (e.g. ERWin, Enterprise Architect and Visio) 
  • High-level understanding of statistical analysis and modelling, predictive analytics, text analytics and other machine learning applications and how to extract insight from data.
  • A sound understanding of digital and cognitive technologies and analytics, information management and business process-based solutions. 
  • A disciplined approach to problem solving and an ability to critically assess 

Additional Notes

Data Engineers: 

  • ETL Experience and ETL development, especially with Oracle ODI, but Informatica and DataStage are also good equivalent tools.
  • SSIS ET is desirable, but priority will be for any of the listed three.

job.title: ETL Engineer - Dataiku
job.abstract: Build ETL flows on Dataiku using your Python & SQL skills.
job.content:
As a Data Engineer you will be responsible for building ETL flows on Dataiku as well as the creation of tools (python-based) on Dataiku to allow the business to use a self-service ETL platform. You will leverage your strong python skills to build and use workflow orchestration processes on Dataiku, prior experience with other workflow orchestration tools such as Apache Airflow would be beneficial. These processes will require modern development standards such as Test-Driven Development, use of microservices and consideration of data governance/lineage. 

You will be involved in the creation and management of CI/CD pipelines so prior experience with GIT and version management is required. Also, use of Big Data tools, particularly the Apache stack (Impala, Hive, Spark) for ingesting data to and from Data Warehouses and Data Lakes. Prior experience with cloud services is required, particularly AWS, part of the role will involve interacting with S3 buckets and so knowledge of the CLI/bash scripting and general file management best practices. Is necessary Given that much of the role involves integrations with Dataiku, mastery of this platform will be a core function. 

 To be successful in this role you will have: 

  • Experience with python including libraries such as pandas and pyspark as well as testing frameworks, linting and use of object-oriented functionality such as classes 
  • Experience with SQL, particularly on large datasets
  • Experience with the CLI/bash scripting language
  • Experience with Big Data and knowledge of data management techniques eg partitioning, file compression 
  • Experience with Big Data technologies such as Apache Spark, Impala and Hive 
  • Experience with cloud platforms, preferably AWS but including Azure and GCP
  • Management of CI/CD processes (eg Jenkins, Bamboo, CircleCI, TeamCity) and use of Git version management such as Bitbucket, GitHub, Gitlab etc
  • Understanding of DevOps concepts and when to apply them to data transformation (or DataOps) 
  • Familiarity with agile methodology, particularly the use of Jira and Confluence, particularly when working across several large projects
  • Good communication and stakeholder management skills

 If this sounds like the right opportunity to further your career, please apply via the portal.

About the Corporate Operations Group

The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, and the Macquarie Group Foundation. We deliver service excellence to ensure Macquarie is open for business, deliver on transformational change, invest in our people and have deep relationships with our customers.

At Macquarie, we support a hybrid working model.

Our commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion 

The diversity of our people is one of our greatest strengths. An inclusive and equitable environment enables us to deliver innovative and sustainable outcomes for our people, clients, shareholders and communities. From day one, you'll be encouraged to be yourself and supported to perform at your best. If our purpose of ‘empowering people to innovate and invest for a better future’ is as inspiring to you as it is to us, please apply. With the right technology, support and resources, our people can work in a range of flexible ways.

We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We encourage candidates to speak with a member of our recruitment team if you require adjustments to our recruitment process to support you, and the type of working arrangements that would help you thrive.

job.title: Sitecore Developer
job.abstract: Sitecore Developers required at all skill and experience levels to work a range of modern web and software technologies. Work from home friendly!
job.content:
SiteCore Developer 

Reporting to: Head of Software Engineering
Full-time, Canberra or remote

At Annex we understand developers want to specialise but also want some variety in their work. We believe our SiteCore Developer role hits that sweet spot.

In this role you will develop engaging web experiences as part of a multi-disciplinary team, developing frontends using SiteCore, javascript based single page apps (SPAs) and other approaches as required. You will work on a range of products and teams, and have an opportunity to be part of and contribute to our great culture and modern development practices.

Qualities and skills we’re looking for 

Essential  

  • 3+ years of experience using SiteCore
  • Team player
  • Great problem solving and verbal communication skills
  • Great organisation and time management skills
  • Ability to build javascript applications using frameworks such as Vue.js, React or Angular
  • Flexible outlook and willing to work on solutions containing Drupal, AEM, SiteCore and other CMS’s
  • Experience writing appropriate unit tests as part of development workflow
  • Experience debugging, refactoring and optimising code
  • Experience with GIT version control
  • Australian Citizen, with ability to get an Australian government security clearance

Desirable

  • Sitecore Developer Certification (version 8+)
  • Experience working in a multi-disciplinary agile development team
  • Experience developing accessible and performant applications
  • Understanding of javascript fundamentals such as code structure, objects, data types, error handling, the browser and DOM
  • Familiar with integration - including event based integration patterns
  • Familiar with data layer - including modeling and databases
  • Experience with TDD, BDD or similar
  • Experience applying DevOps practices such as CI/CD and automated testing
  • Experience with Drupal/GovCMS or other CMS platforms
  • Experience with cloud platforms such as Azure, AWS or Platform.sh
  • Experience working with or for Government clients

A bit about us

Annex is a modern digital consultancy - kicking goals and growing quickly. We’ve brought together a unique mix of talent that’s resulted in great culture and great work.

Through our expertise and collaborative agile approach we help our clients design and deliver digital products and services.

Our principles

Trust. Transparency. Collaboration.  

Annex is built on trust, if you’re a part of the team, it means we trust and empower you to do your job. We value open communication and transparency and strive to build a safe place for our team to develop their skills and have pathways for progression.

Flexible working

Annex offers flexible working options, which allows you to work from home, in the office as well as on client sites when required. During COVID 19 restrictions Annex operated entirely as a remote office.

Central location 

Annex maintains an office in Canberra, which is available for use, depending on availability and any social distancing restrictions at the time. 

Hours

Full-time position, although part-time or flexible working considered.

Great kit

We use Mac OS and you’ll be provided modern equipment and software to help you do your job. Our daily tools Slack, Jira, and Confluence. Our design team uses a range of design software and adapts as required. 

Support and Benefits

You will have access to our Employee Assistance Program as well as ongoing perks via PerkBox. You will also be provided with ongoing training and development and access to industry events and conferences.


 

If this sounds like the job for you, we’d love to hear from you!

job.title: Senior Automation Tester
job.abstract: A new & exciting role for a Senior Automation Tester!
job.content:
About the business

Does working on world-leading technologies and providing solutions for high profile Government Agencies excite you? 

We are IDEMIA – a global leader in Augmented Identity. We provide a trusted environment enabling citizens and consumers alike to perform their daily critical activities (such as pay, connect and travel), in the physical as well as digital space. With close to 15,000 employees around the world, IDEMIA serves clients in 180 countries.   

In Australia and New Zealand, IDEMIA’s Public Security & Identity Business Unit supports several blue chip security customers that operate critical infrastructure and systems of national significance, underpinned by IDEMIA’s biometrics, digital security and cloud services. With a large pipeline of work coming through, we are looking for multiple talents to join our growing team.

 

You will be joining a highly motivated and collaborative team and a company that offers:

  • Exposure to niche technologies products and solutions powered by modern tech
  • Work-life balance
  • Diverse & Inclusive Culture
  • Health and Group Life Insurance
  • Long service rewards
  • Learning & development
  • Extended annual leave based on tenure up to 5 weeks per year
  • Treated as a person not just a number
  • Birthday Leave

About the role

Senior Automation Tester is responsible for setting up Test automation framework, automation of functional and non-functional test cases, test execution and reporting.

  • Establish Test Automation Framework and test setup based on the applications to be automated and further design, script, execute and report test results based on the planned test executions.
  • Collaborate and work with various project stakeholders to understand the applications, requirements and manual test cases for each Sprint and automate.
  • Automation of existing manual test cases for Desktop (On Premises) solution and moving forward towards the automation of the cloud solution test cases.
  • Post setup of framework and automation, regular maintenance/updates of the automated test case for every sprint based on the new functionalities/changes and ensure they are executable for Regression Testing.
  • Keen to understand the existing automation solution and capable to troubleshoot and suggest suitable solution for framework issues and also to build new automation solution in future for applications hosted in cloud.
  • Implementation of CI/CD processes/pipelines.
  • Test automation using SOAP UI, Selenium, Cucumber, JMeter, JIRA Xray/Testlink, Jenkins and automation programming languages such as Java, Java Script or C#.
  • Setup and configuration of JMeter. 
  • Support manual testing, regression testing and other testing activities when required, based on priority.
  • Defect analysis and logging

Skills and experience:

Preferred:

  • 10+ yrs. of experience in Functional Test Automation, setup framework across desktop and cloud solutions, design, script, execute and report
  • Good exposure in functional automation, Performance Testing, Test execution and reporting. 
  • Strong automation experience across various automation frameworks, approaches and techniques.
  • Setting up new automation framework, understanding the existing framework and fix the ongoing issues that arises due to changes in application, platform and test environment.
  • Automation of Desktop application and cloud based solution.
  • Experience in API testing – SOAP UI, Postman.
  • Experience in Log management tools.
  • Hands on experience in automation of Regression test cases, execution, test data creation and reporting.
  • Knowledge of DevOps tools 
  • Great written and oral communication skills;

Optional:

  • Experience in Federal Government projects.
  • Experience in using TestLink.
  • Automation experience in Microsoft Azure based solution.

General:

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
  • Self-motivated with attention to details.
  • Good interpersonal skills.
  • Ability to work within distributed team composed of people from multiple countries and time zones (France)
  • Highlight the challenges/blockers (clearly) on time and to report the automation status regularly, based on the agreed plan.
  • Collaborates well within testing team and also with other streams and ensure the required inputs are obtained and automation outcomes are achieved.
  • Ability to work within a highly specialized team environment.

NOTE: To apply for any of these roles, you must be an Australian Citizen and preferably be holding AGSVA Baseline or higher security clearance.

For further information please contact Laura - laura.carvalho@idemia.com

job.content:
• Leading solution provider, Microsoft Gold Partner
  • Great opportunity to own end-to-end Cloud Solutions for your clients.
  • Excellent work culture, with Hybrid WFH if you're in Sydney and opportunity to work remotely if any other regions.
  • Need Australian Citizenship or PR for at least 5 years

Benefits

  • Competitive salary package
  • Flexible work environment
  • Career progression and fantastic company culture

About the Company

This leading solution provider is a Microsoft Gold Partner and going through an exceptional growth due to an expanding client portfolio and current successes. They are the partner of choice for clients requiring the highest levels of security, availability and customer service in the Microsoft space. Their mission is to create client value through thought leadership, service excellence and solution innovation. They empower enterprise-wide innovation through end-to-end solutions where compliance and robustness are non-negotiables.

About the role

The business is heavily and solely invested in Azure and will need a Microsoft specialist, with a strong technical background. A Servant leader who has led technical teams towards building out and managing Azure cloud-based products.

A big bonus would be for you to have experience across on-prem to Azure migrations, Azure DevOps and some level of pre-sales experience. Having multi-cloud experience and knowledge of the latest stack of Cloud product is a plus.

You will be part o the overarching architecture team with daily responsibility including:

  • Drive and further develop the Cloud DevOps Architecture practice
  • Day to Day Product ownership of the Azure (and multicloud) Saas and PaaS offering
  • Involvement in RFP response, supporting the Presales and Sales teams as required
  • Transforming the way your practice operates, working to further embed DevOps into the culture of the whole business
  • Work closely with peers to workforce plan, drive initiatives and outcomes. You will be directly working with other teams in the managed and professional services practices
  • Own end-to-end clients' solutions from requirements to implementation

Culture

With a customer centric culture based on collaboration, can do attitude, respect, communication and teamwork, this leading Australian technology partner offers career progression aligned with the evolving technology landscape, training and exciting innovative projects, plus great perks such as:

  • Paid day off on your birthday
  • Paid parental leave
  • Employee Assistance Program
  • Employee discounts on home loans, insurance, private health insurance and retail products through our client base

Skills & experience

  • Five or more years of architecture, design implementation and/or support of distributed applications designed to run in the cloud or across hybrid cloud and on-premises environments;
  • Deep understanding and proven experience with modern DevOps practices, including automation, continuous delivery, continuous deployment, and continuous integration methodologies. (Azure DevOps experience highly regarded);
  • Multiple certifications in Azure and Microsoft products; minimum AZ-301: Microsoft Azure Architect Design certification;
  • Experience or familiarity of DevOps concepts and cultural elements
  • Australian Citizenship or PR for more than 5 years is a must

How to apply

Click APPLY, send Luca an email with your CV at lucam@thenetworkit.com or simply call her on 0468 961 185 for a confidential conversation.

job.content:

​

In this role you will have the opportunity to execute the onboarding of clients onto Perpetual Digital's platform product suite including systems integration, overall performance, and client experience.

  • Capture and define technical requirements for new digital products from product, business and client stakeholders.

Job Details:

An opportunity to become part of a strategic initiative at a federal government enterprise to uplift the data management practice by rolling out advanced BI technology solutions.

POSITION PRIMARY PURPOSE

Provide technical leadership for implementation of BI technology solutions, including but not limited to Cloudera Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau that meet business requirements and align with the enterprise architecture and standards.

POSITION OBJECTIVES

  • Working closely with the architects and various IT teams, provide technical leadership to implement Cloudera Data Platform on the Azure Cloud; Tableau and other data and analytical solutions for the enterprise.

  • Provide input to project planning, scheduling, estimation, status reporting and risk and issue resolution.
  • Support the systems through problem resolution, debugging and system enhancements, especially around implementation and warranty period.
  • Provide advice, guidance and assistance to less experienced colleagues as required.

QUALIFICATIONS, ACCREDITATIONS AND KNOWLEDGE

  • Degree qualifications, accreditations or certifications relevant to BI Technology.
  • Knowledge of BI Technology including Cloudera (Hadoop) Data Platform, Azure Cloud and Tableau. Knowledge of Power BI, RStudio, Python, ETL Tools is desirable but not mandatory.

  • Advanced Knowledge of the System Development Life Cycle.
  • Understanding of industry trends, technologies and best practices.

EXPERIENCE

  • Proven experience in the following technologies: Azure Cloud, Cloudera Data Platform and Tableau is a must have. RStudio, Python and ETL experience is desirable.
  • Experience in authentication and access control principles and implementation.
  • Experience in defining and implementing information architectures and systems.
  • Experience in migrating and implementing BI Solutions in the Cloud.
  • Experience using Microsoft tools: Visio, Azure Dev Ops and Visual Studio.
  • Experience in writing and reviewing technical documentation.

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Do you have a passion for innovation, problem solving, and using data to create powerful new insights in a dynamic and fast growth team?
job.content:
Do you have a passion for innovation, problem solving, and using data to create powerful new insights?

If you’re interested in changing lives, and helping others, whilst being part of a dynamic, fast growth team….

Then this could be the opportunity for you!

Hi, we’re Global Proptech Solutions- and we’re on a mission to transform the way the world invests in real estate.

Doing so will help to serve our purpose of improving the lives of others and will help us to change the world by creating a more abundant society.

And that's where you come in!

Right now, we're looking for a Data Engineer to be the supportive force that empowers the team to do their best work. but...

This job is NOT for just anyone.

We are looking for an experienced “A” player who has a proven track record of excellence, and loves to think outside of the box!

Your Rewards:

  • Culture of Freedom and Responsibility
  • Fast growth company, with an amazing team culture
  • Do work that matters
  • Unlimited Paid Annual Leave
  • Work from anywhere
  • Generous salary, plus Super
  • Access to leading technology platforms to support your remote working
  • WFH Boost Grant

Your Role:

At Global Proptech Solutions (GPS), we owe our success to our insatiable curiosity and our relentless work ethic in pursuit of our mission to transform the way the world invests in real estate.

We are a rapidly growing proptech startup looking for a Data Engineer to help drive the creation of the next generation of property solutions in Data Science & Artificial Intelligence.

You will be looking to carve out a career as a Data Engineer to drive innovation in a stable and fast growing startup to change the way people invest in properties globally .

You will embrace new technologies, big data, systems, and productivity tools.

You will thrive in a dynamic environment, and bring structure to an environment that is always changing, whilst staying flexible enough to go with the flow.

You will actively seek ways to improve systems (people, process and application) to increase efficiency and outcomes.

You will be solution focussed, always looking for the answer, and overcoming any roadblocks.

You must have a high ownership mentality, deep comfort with autonomy, confidence in your thought process and willingness to adapt to new information, a hunger for finding the truth, and a desire to help others grow.

This role will likely change and evolve as the company grows, but will always seek to serve our mission to transform the way the world invests.

From day one, you will have an impact on the efficiency and effectiveness of our daily operations, and a lasting influence on our company, and in turn, our clients.

Responsibilities Include (but not limited to):

  • Drive and deliver innovation.
  • Implement requests for ingestion, creation, and preparation of data sources;
  • Deliver data pipelines and data sets for analysis and machine learning, with activities including data staging, ETL, data quality, and archiving;
  • Profile source data and validate fit-for-purpose;
  • Optimize data pipelines from performance and scalability perspectives;
  • Monitor and maintain data pipelines and data storage systems;
  • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand and implement data requirements.
  • Ensure project delivery within timelines and budget requirements;
  • Stay up-to-date with the latest industry trends and technologies in data engineering.

Skills & Qualifications:

  • Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field
  • Proficiency in Python programming language;
  • Proven experience in SQL and NoSQL databases;
  • Proven experience in business intelligence/data visualization platforms e.g. Tableau, Power BI etc.;
  • Experience with cloud environments e.g. AWS, Azure or GCP;
  • Proficiency in exploring and manipulating large datasets through applications or programming interfaces;
  • Knowledge and skills in one or more of the big data frameworks i.e. Spark, Hive, Hadoop and Flink;
  • Strong understanding of data modeling, ETL, and data warehousing concepts;
  • Excellent problem-solving and debugging skills;
  • Proven experience in data warehouses e.g.Snowflake, DataBricks, Redshift, Bigquery etc. is a plus.

The Culture:

We believe that finding the right fit is the most important thing, so before you apply, we thought it would be good to give you some insight into our culture.

We operate a high performance team culture, and practice a philosophy of Freedom and Responsibility.

Put simply, we trust you to operate with integrity, and in line with our values. We also trust that you will do whatever it takes to uphold your professional and personal responsibilities.

Outside of that, we recognise our best work often happens when we have the freedom to manage our time and to support our own personal needs.

We have unapologetically high standards, and strive for excellence in everything we do.

We don’t accept excuses, only solutions.

Extreme ownership results in outstanding performance, and mutual respect.

We believe in relentless, pragmatic, optimism and look for the positives in every situation.

We also believe in having a hell of a lot of fun, and making sure that we are all living our best lives along the way.

Why would you?

Yes, we are a Property Investment Strategy & Acquisition Services company, but we are equally a PropTech company with a strong commitment to transform the way the world invests in property.

Data is our fuel, AI is our building material and wisdom is our guide to build world class solutions.

Dashdot provides a platform for data scientists, developers and business specialists to work closely together using the latest technology.

Some of the tools you will be using daily include AWS, Azure, GCP, Snowflake, Databricks, and Tableau.

At Dashdot we are tech agnostic, what matters is the solution.

If a tech can do it, we’ll use it… and it goes without saying … we like playing with the latest tech!

Interested? You know you are!

Click Apply Now and let's get to know each other!

  • Undertake problem diagnoses, correction and escalated support of Microsoft and associated technologies across the organisation
  • Promote business continuity by supporting existing systems/solution to ensure maximum uptime of applications and platforms on a day to day basis
  • Undertake rigorous monitoring, review and analysis as required to ensure validity, efficiency and consistency of software and infrastructure systems
  • Maintain an effective testing environment and test changes to production servers in a controlled environment
  • Advise and perform operational support of the applications/platforms and ensure change and release management, compliance, auditing controls are in place for cloud environments
  • Undertake continuous improvement to ensure standards, process' and tools, automation, scaling and recovery process are in place and aligned with Industry best practice
  • Development of policies procedures and other documentation required to support the systems environment

Key Skills Required:

  • Experience with complex Data Centre, IaaS, PaaS and SaaS, cloud computing and/or emerging technologies
  • Advanced knowledge of Office 365,SQL Server, IIS, Active Directory and other key server technology
  • Strong working knowledge of network protocols including TCP/IP, SDWAN & wide area network technologies
  • ITIL experience in a hybrid cloud environment
  • Architecture and design experience within Data Centre & Cloud related technologies
  • Public and Private Cloud domain experience
  • Proven experience in Cloud Services, including engineering and operational management
  • Proven ability to lead transformations in complex environments
  • Excellent communication and Stakeholder engagement skills
  • Strong customer service focus
  • Working knowledge of scripting language

Please Note: All resumes MUST be submitted in Word format.

If you are interested in hearing more about this position, don't hesitate to contact Sumeet Kaur.

job.abstract: This is an exciting opportunity to join a large-scale data and analytics project working with new Azure products!
job.content:
Our client is seeking an experienced Test Analyst for a long-term contract. This role offers attractive daily rates and flexible working arrangements.

  • Muti-Year Project working with new Azure products!
  • Long Term Contract Available; and
  • Attractive Daily Rate - In line with current Market Rates.

The Test Analyst (Business Intelligence) will contribute to validating data and reporting solutions within the new Enterprise Data & Analytics Service (EDAS) Microsoft Azure platform.

You need

  • Solid BI / Data Warehouse Experience;
  • Cloud Experience (preferably Azure);
  • Experience working with Reporting Tools - Power BI ideal; and
  • Python experience (desirable).

This role will support the Test Manager and form part of the EDAS delivery team with the role focusing on ensuring quality outcomes for both data specific requirements and reporting functionality.

This new role will enable the successful applicant to work on modern data and analytics solutions using technologies within the Azure space. It will also provide the applicant opportunities to work and integrate with a variety of enterprise applications with different technologies and architecture.

Key Accountabilities

  • Work with the Test Manager and delivery team to create test plans to ensure appropriate test coverage in line with the test strategy;
  • Create test scripts in accordance with the test plan for execution through the test framework;
  • Work with Business Analysts, Data Analysts and Data Modellers to understand data platform and reporting requirements and translate these into test plans and test cases;
  • Work with Business Analysts and business teams to support user acceptance testing and coordinate defect resolution;
  • Execute testing across the solution to ensure high quality data products. Includes, system integration testing, functionality testing, performance testing, security testing, regression testing, smoke testing and production verification testing;
  • Ensure test results are suitably captured for auditing and release management purposes;
  • Utilise a wide range of Azure technologies such as Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Azure Logic Apps, Azure Functions, Azure APIs and Azure DevOps to complement the test methodologies and frameworks; and
  • Participate in team design and planning sessions as part of the agile sprint process and proactively provide updates and communicate risks or impediments.

Technical Skills Required

  • Experience in testing data warehouse solutions on Azure;
  • Experience in the creation of SQL scripts to validate report and business / presentation layer data;
  • Experience in working with APIs for data ingestion and sharing in a testing capacity;
  • Experience in verifying data in Power BI or a similar product;
  • Experience in functional and usability testing of Power BI or similar product;
  • Experience in testing user level security requirements;
  • An understanding of metadata driven testing methodologies and frameworks;
  • An understanding of modern data warehouse solutions including ETL / ELT processes and Data Lakehouse; and
  • Experience of python or a similar language is advantageous.

For more information please call Tyler Dewar at u&u on 0455 668 294, quoting reference number 30729. Alternatively, to submit an application please click the apply button.

job.title: Data Architect
job.abstract: DATA ARCHITECT | DATA MODELLING | AZURE | ROAD-MAP CREATION | FUTURE PROOFING | DOCUMENTATION | DATA STRATEGY | GROWTH OPPORTUNITY | HYBRID |
job.content:
Davidson Technology have teamed up with an iconic Australian Financial services organisation to help them find them a Data Architect to join the team!

This is a full-time permanent opportunity that does not come around often. Have the chance to join a progressive and values driven organisation who gives back to the community at every chance they get.

Joining a newly formed team, the room for growth both personal and career is a major factor in this role, working alongside their Integration Architect and Strategic Digital Leader you will have a major impact on the organisations future and how they utilise their data.

Key facts about this opportunity:

You will be providing strategic architecture services and own the development of Enterprise data modelling and associated solution architectures and inform development of technology strategies and architecture roadmaps for the data & integration domain, ensuring solutions are current and aligned with business needs and technology developments.

As the Data Architect, you will work collaboratively to prioritise technology needs, considering the wider data and privacy governance landscape, enterprise architecture, business/ product/ architectural strategies and principles to establishing tailored architectural (data) modelling and technology solutions.

The skill set we need:

  • Previous Experience in an Azure Environment
  • High level of stakeholder management and communication skill
  • Experience working both independently and as part of a small team of Solution Architects / Designers / Engineers.
  • Business results orientation and organisational awareness
  • Strong teamwork and collaboration skillset.
  • Pragmatic and risk/time/cost solution focus
  • Interpersonal and relationship development skills
  • Influencing and storytelling skillset with strong verbal, written and presentation skills with an ability to communicate in both technical and business language, ability to translate complex technical language into business impacts and requirements.
  • Strong understanding of and ability to articulate the business value of specific architectures.
  • Proven ability to plan and prioritise in a high-pressure environment.
  • Previous experience within a financial or highly regulated environment will be looked on favourably.

It is expected that the data architect demonstrates:

  • Courage and resilience in the face of ambiguity ('staying the course'), while showing flexibility and an openness to change.
  • An ability to challenge stakeholders where necessary to achieve optimal outcomes, whilst building a rapport to create a shared vision and journey.
  • Solid problem-solving with an emerging ability to cut-through complexity, and an ability to think creatively at a tactical level with a keen attention to detail.
  • A drive to succeed, self-motivated and able to work independently with limited direction.
  • Holds strong moral values and a want to give back to the community.

You will need to be an Australian Citizen or hold Australian Permanent Residency to be eligible for this role.

If this sounds like the right opportunity for you, please apply today!





Please apply by upload your current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). If you would like to have a confidential discussion, please contact David Chisholm on +61 3 9929 9500, quoting reference JN -022023-31964. Want to know more about Davidson? job.title: Solution Architect
job.abstract: Looking for an established Solution Architect
job.content:
• 6 month contract

The Solution Architect will have a leadership role in the Program delivery. They will work with Program and Product management, other stakeholders, change and governance teams and lead the multidisciplinary development team to deliver a solution that meets the business requirements. The development team consists of D365 Functional and Technical and DevSecOps Consultants, testing resources, data resources and technical analysts amongst others. 

They will need to have expertise in architectural design patterns and your in-depth understanding of Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.

Key Responsibilities:

  • Lead and mentor technical teams in designing and developing complex solutions using Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365, while adhering to architectural design patterns.
  • Provide technical guidance and leadership to development teams and stakeholders, ensuring that solutions are designed and implemented to meet business requirements and are scalable, secure, and maintainable.
  • Create and maintain technical documentation, including architecture diagrams, design documents, and project plans.
  • Establish end-to-end architecture, design patterns and coding standards so that work is done to the highest possible quality and govern through code reviews
  • Ensure all work is thoroughly tested through manual/automated tests, including functional, non- functional, performance and resilience
  • Mentor Technical resource so that they become more effective in their role
  • Evaluate emerging technologies, frameworks and libraries to ensure coding standards and practices are aligned to industry standards
  • Present newly development functionality to stakeholders through Software demonstrations
  • Ensure that solutions are delivered on-time, within budget, and to the highest quality standards.
  • Participate in the development of proposals and project estimates.
  • Work collaboratively with clients and internal teams to understand business requirements and develop technical solutions to meet those needs.

Key Skills Essential:

    • Extensive experience with Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.

    • Demonstrated experience with:

o implementing platform replacement of one or more of core business or business supporting applications

o developing architecture documents in a format that technical and non-technical audiences can understand

o developing architecture in a large portfolio with dependency adjacent projects in various states of delivery

o working with technology and business stakeholders and supporting their respective standards, patterns and strategies

o ensuring solutions are compliant with security and technology standards
o leading and contributing to the development of architectural methods, processes, standards

o reviewing architecture designs in a peer or governance format and providing feedback based on quality, risks and alternative options

o an Microsoft application landscape including Microsoft Dynamics 365 Customer Service, Dataverse and PowerApps

o architectural design patterns and best practices, including microservices, event-driven architecture, and serverless computing.

o leading and mentoring technical teams in large-scale digital transformation initiatives.

o Proven high level negotiation, consultation facilitation and effective written and oral communications skills in a complex Agile program/project environment working with Product Managers, Product Owners and Delivery Teams.

o Demonstrated experience in an Agile program/project environment managing Agile software requirements analysis activities, driving backlog refinements and ensuring user story Definition of Ready and Definition of Done requirements are met
