Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCLTech. With offices across Australia, we have over 800 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation

Who We Are Looking For:
Already possessing many years of C# / .NET Development experience, this role will push you to utilise your existing C# / .NET skills and apply them to the design, development and implementation of new complex systems. Interaction with the business and customers will be part of your daily life, understanding the needs and requirements of users and tailoring systems to these specifications will be a key part of your role. 

Specific experience must include:

  • Exposure to open source technologies (MongoDB / NoSQL) would be a bonus
  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills

Working at DWS offers you:

job.abstract: Worked directly in an MSP as either a TAM, consultant or an Engineer who is ready to step up into client-facing TAM role for First Focus? Apply now
job.content:
Benefits:

First Focus’ values are based around keeping everyone informed, aligned, supported, and rewarding performance. Some examples of this include: 

  • A competitive salary package
  • All employees have free access to Uprise, including 1:1 coaching sessions from qualified psychologists or counsellors
  • First Focus understands the importance of flexibility for a satisfying work-life balance, which is why we offer hybrid working arrangements
  • ‘Never Stop Growing’ is deeply imbedded in our DNA - we offer 1 paid study day every month and support employees towards certifications and qualifications - we will not only pay for the exam but will also give you a pay rise for achieving certs (conditions apply, of course)
  • Staff are encouraged to take advantage of our weekly internal training sessions and library
  • Opportunities for personal and professional development with our FastTrack mentor program
  • We have our very own MAD (making a difference) Council, focusing on equality, charity, and the environment
  • Option of a Tesla company car as part of your ongoing employment package (conditions apply)
  • $40/month towards your mobile phone and data plan under our BYOD policy, and if you want to bring your own laptop to work, we'll double that
  • Complimentary membership with Women in Technology (WiT)
  • Regular social events and a great team culture!

About us:

First Focus is Australia's #1 ranked Managed Service Provider, with almost 280 staff across Australia, New Zealand and the Philippines. We have grown consistently and profitably for over 15 years and we're continuing to win new clients and evolve our solutions.  Life at First Focus is all about helping our customers use technology. We simplify, we succeed as a team, and when something isn't right, we call it out. We listen to each other, and to our customers. We make changes (often very quickly) and we don't tolerate office politics.

About the opportunity:

We are seeking another Technical Account Manager to join our national Client Services Team. This opportunity will appeal to experienced TAMs, Level 3 or Level 4 Service Desk Support Engineers looking to become more client facing, or even to a Junior TAM looking to join a high performing Team and grow from training and strong, dynamic leadership.

About You:

  • Ideally you have previously worked with in a Managed Service Provider (MSP) on a Service Desk or client facing in a TAM role.
  • You will have a strong technical background (Office 365, cloud, Azure, Windows, networking) with relevant IT Certifications and proven track record or solving technical problems.
  • You will have previous experience in identifying technical issues and spotting opportunities to better support our values customers.
  • You will be a relationship builder - more of a farmer than a hunter in your sales experience.
  • An in-depth understanding of SLAs / ITIL, ticketing system and time based billing.
  • Commercial acumen, analytical skills and client-facing experience required.
  • Additional experience in writing proposals, quoting and invoicing is a definite advantage but not essential.

Tasks & responsibilities of the role:

  • Develop and maintain strong relationships with your Clients (SMBs up to 500 seats).
  • Take technical ownership of client environments, ensuring they are robust, well managed and meet the Client's needs.
  • Design technical solutions, develop and present proposals for up-sell opportunities.
  • Monitor and improve client satisfaction.
  • Identify opportunities to improve your customer's environments through problem analysis and management.
  • Administration, good recording keeping and ability to operate in a time based billing environment.

First Focus welcomes applications from Neurodiverse candidates. We recommend & appreciate disclosure along with the application so that a copy of our Neurodiversity Statement can be provided outlining the flexible options we can offer to best showcase your skills.

job.abstract: Engage with Stakeholders across Multiple Industry Sectors. 80-90% Dev. Doc Requirements, Translate into Tech Specs, Develop, Test, Train Deploy.
job.content:
Senior Data Analytics Developer – 12 Months Fixed Term then Possibly Permanent

 – B4HANA / SAP SAC / Azure Data Bricks / Azure Data Lake Gen2 / Power BI -

About the role

This is a 12 month fixed term opportunity to join the corporate IT team as a Senior Data Analytics Developer based out of our head office in North Sydney.

 

In this role you will engage with stakeholders across the business, document their requirements, translate into technical requirements, develop, test, train and deploy.

 

The Opportunity

The interesting part is to understand what the business is trying to achieve and suggesting the best data analysis solution. It’s the industry sectors that you’ll get exposure to such as NSW Rail or TfNSW, People & Culture and leaders from across the business.

 

Most of the data and core processes reside in SAP (SAP FI) however some data is non SAP. In this role it will be vital to assess the business needs and provide the right solution using B4HANA, Azure Data Bricks, Azure Data Lake Gen2, SAP Analytics Cloud and Power BI as the visualisation tools.

 

We use ServiceNow, Trello, agile methodology and usually 2 week sprints. This is a growing data analytics practice with approximately 80-90% development activities. You will also manage tickets and submit change approvals to the advisory board.

 

Key responsibilities

  • Analyse business requirements and priorities, liaise with stakeholders, design reporting solutions
  • Design, configure, test and implement SAP BI Objects
  • Support and troubleshoot SAP BW applications and BI solutions and manage BAU tickets
  • Provide estimates for projects and enhancements and develop and maintain technical documentation

About you

  • Substantial experience in a similar role designing, implementing, testing, supporting and maintaining SAP BW and various BI tools such as SAP SAC and PowerBI
  • SAP Business Warehouse and administration, SAP Business Objects tools including AfO
  • Preferable skills include SAP modules such as PS, Logistics, PM, CS and HR

About Us

UGL Pty Limited is a leading provider of end-to-end engineering, construction and maintenance services. We are active across rail and transport, communications and technology systems, oil and gas, power, renewables and resources, water and defence markets. UGL partners with some of the world’s largest blue-chip companies and government agencies, private enterprises and public institutions. We are a member of the CIMIC Group of companies.

As a diversified services organisation, UGL appreciates the diversity and richness of its people, and seeks to create inclusive environments that promote your talent and skills. 

Please note that relevant screening checks will be conducted as part of the recruitment process. These may include a national criminal history check and for you to undergo pre-employment medical assessment including drug and alcohol screen.

Ref: 252329

job.title: D365 Functional Consultant
job.abstract: 6 Months Contract looking for Dynamics 365 Functional Consultant.
job.content:
About the Company
Davidsons Technology are currently partnering with a large Queensland State Government department undertaking a significant multi-year digital transformation initiative to modernise its business systems, enable online service delivery and support a mobile workforce by implementing new Microsoft based systems and decommissioning legacy systems The initiative is being delivered using a lean agile methodology.

We are seeking an experienced D365 Functional Consultant for a initial 6 months contract with potential to extend to assist in the continued development and application design for the existing Program Deliverables.

About the Role
In your new role will be responsible for working closely with clients to gather and analyse business requirements, design and configure D365 solutions, run requirements workshops, and deliver solutions that meet client needs. You will also collaborate with technical teams and stakeholders to ensure successful project delivery. The ideal candidate will have a strong business analysis background, excellent communication skills, experience in agile methodologies, and knowledge of the Power Platform.

Your key responsibilities will include:

  • Work with clients to understand their business processes and gather business requirements for D365 solutions.
  • Lead requirements workshops, document and analyse business processes, and translate business requirements into functional requirements.
  • Design and configure D365 solutions using industry best practices and proven patterns.
  • Acting as the translation point between functional and technical teams so that solutions can be developed
  • Effectively managing large work streams to stay within scope, meet or exceed project schedule and remain within the approved budget
  • Collaborate with technical teams to ensure successful delivery of solutions that meet business requirements.
  • Provide guidance and support to stakeholders and end-users in the use of D365 solutions.
  • Utilise agile methodologies to manage project delivery and effectively prioritise tasks.
  • Stay up-to-date with the latest D365 and Power Platform features and updates.
  • Help create an innovative, creative and fun team culture, capable of developing advanced technologies.

About You

  • Minimum of 5 years of experience in business analysis, requirements gathering, and D365 functional configuration.
  • Experience with Azure Integration, Azure Data, Power Platform, and D365.
  • Proven experience in agile methodologies and leading requirements workshops.
  • Knowledge of the Power Platform and its associated tools, including Power Apps and Power Automate.
  • Strong communication and interpersonal skills.
  • Ability to work collaboratively with technical teams, stakeholders, and end-users.
  • Experience in large-scale digital transformation projects

The Benefits
This opportunity offers you a contract till end of August 2023 and potentially to extend, and an hourly rate of $100 - $115 per hour + Superannuation (negotiable).

The client offers flexible working conditions split between work from home and their Brisbane CBD based office.

Next Steps
To apply, click the link and upload your current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx).

If you would like to have a confidential discussion, please contact our Brisbane Technology team on QLDGov_Technology@davidsonwp.com quoting ref no 32109

Applications close 5:00 pm Friday 24th January.

job.content:
Ingenia Communities is a leading Australian property group that owns, operates and develops a fast-growing portfolio of living and lifestyle communities (land lease communities) and holiday parks across key urban and coastal markets. We employ over 1300 people across 120 parks and communities, with offices in the 3 eastern seaboard states.

About the Role

This is a newly created BI Data Analyst role that will work on a range of high-profile data initiatives as part of the larger Ingenia IT function. This opportunity will see you exposed to a range of business units and stakeholders as you will be a key member of the Business Intelligence team!

As the subject matter expert in understanding underlying data structures used to manage Ingenia information, you will identify, strategize, and then build a range of replicable analytics and Power BI dashboard reporting to help Ingenia inform critical strategic decisions.

We are looking for an experienced, collaborative, and driven professional with a good understanding of technical components, and the ability to work independently and across business functions

Key Accountabilities

  • Building complex database queries to extract relevant data for analysis.
  • Work with technical and non-technical stakeholders when gathering requirements.
  • Draw correlations between data sets, analyse and provide insights and trend statistics.
  • Manager vendors in tandem with the BI Data Engineer and broader IT team.
  • Develop and maintain documentation regarding business requirements, reports, processes and change management tasks.

About You

  • Experience in Power BI (DAX) and presenting complex data in easy-to-understand formats essential.
  • Good knowledge and experience with SAAS environments, data architecture, and Microsoft products (SQL, Power BI, Azure Data services)
  • An understanding and data governance, data quality and master data management.
  • Technical acumen across core SQL, Data Warehousing (Snowflake), Advanced Analytics and Data Visualization desired.
  • SharePoint Experience
  • JIRA Experience
  • CRM Experience
  • Experience in reporting, database queries and API logic
  • Tertiary qualifications preferably in a quantitative subject e.g., computer science, engineering, mathematics, finance, or economics.
  • Demonstrated ability to work independently and pragmatically with a structured (yet flexible) approach to solve problems and find outcomes that truly provide value to the customer

Benefits

You might not have heard about Ingenia before, and we tend to fly under the radar. Once you look into our dynamic, fast growing (ASX 200) business with a culture of creating communities you'll be surprised by all the opportunities you'll find. Our team is dynamic and friendly, and you'll enjoy fantastic discounted rates at our holiday parks across the east coast. We offer an attractive salary, flexible work arrangements and many other fab benefits.

job.abstract: Excellent opportunity for a Microsoft Dynamics 365 FO/AX professionals
job.content:
About the Company
This IT Services and IT Consulting company is an Australian company that has core competencies in banking and financial services. They work with leading and local companies across the APAC region. Their highly skilled, talented IT specialists are experts in their fields, and employees are placed in key value-adding roles with our customers on strategic projects to strengthen their core teams. The company is fiercely proud and supportive of the talented people they bring on board to join their company. They endeavour to find you challenging and fulfilling work that converts passion into action. They actively support and drive skills development to enable growth opportunities.
  • Competitive Salary 
  • Flexible Work Arrangements 
  • Generous Benefits 
  • Opportunities for Growth 
  • Collaborative Culture
 
An opportunity has arisen for the MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager role.  The opportunity also exists for a candidate with strong retail project delivery background and with knowledge of Dynamics 365 FO/AX to be provided on-the-job training to be upskilled to get you to the correct level.
 
About the Retail Implementation Manager (MS D365 FO/AX) role:
In the MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager role, you will be responsible for delivering all phases of the project life cycle including analysing, designing, modelling, testing, training, pre and post Go live support, and deploying suitable and appropriate solutions.
 
 
Key responsibilities:
  • Demonstrate capabilities in evaluating retail processes and recommending improvements.
  • Understand how to build and maintain positive client and peer relationships.
  • Excellent customer-facing skills, able to communicate at all levels of an organization, from C-Suite, SME, and End users.
  • Demonstrate strong analytical, communication (written and verbal) and problem-solving skills.
  • Comfortable in settings from smaller Discovery/Workshop environments all the way to the Board Room.
  • Prepared for some domestic and international travel as required.
  • Ability to collaborate effectively with a larger team throughout an enterprise transformation.
  • High degree of initiative and personal responsibility.
To succeed in a MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager role, you must have successfully completed a post-secondary degree/diploma in Business, Computer Science, or a related discipline and at least 3+ years of experience with a full life-cycle implementation of D365. Preferably: D365FO/ Dynamics AX Retail experience
 
Key requirements:
You must have experience and strong working knowledge across some or all of the Retail, Commerce, and Supporting modules and Microsoft products:
  • Order to cash
  • Inventory, products, variants, attributes
  • Catalogues, assortments, pricing, and discounts
  • Online/Brick & Mortar channel configuration
  • POS Architecture and configuration
  • Payment processing
  • Loyalty
  • Distributed Order Management (DOM) and Intelligent Order Management (IOM)
  • Data migration, data management, and FastTrack go-live assessment.
  • Security framework. roles and best practices
  • Understanding the integration options and underlying technologies available
  • Preferably has experience with Power Platform, Logic Apps, Power Automate
  • Preferably has experience with Azure Data Lake Storage, Dataverse, Dual Write
  • Preferably has experience in Using Lifecycle Services to design and plan a project.
  • Using Azure DevOps, test case planning, and acceptance testing framework
  • Proven experience leading requirement gathering and discovery with users and stakeholders.
  • Participation in the FIT/GAP process and ability to write complete functional design specifications.
  • Solid experience in designing and writing technical specification documents.
  • Demonstrated knowledge and experience in ERP implementation principles, practices, and methodologies.
Preferred Certifications:
  • MB-300: Microsoft Dynamics 365: Core Finance and Operations
  • MB-340: Microsoft Dynamics 365 Commerce Functional Consultant
 
If you are driven, determined, and want to take the next step in your career, this is the role for you. Great career progression opportunities await the right person in this exciting MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager job.
 
Apply today or email camille@staffx.com.au or call her at +61 3 7042 5305 to discuss this new opportunity!

  • Understand how to build and maintain positive client and peer relationships.
  • Excellent customer-facing skills, able to communicate at all levels of an organization, from C-Suite, SME, and End users.
  • Demonstrate strong analytical, communication (written and verbal) and problem-solving skills.
  • Comfortable in settings from smaller Discovery/Workshop environments all the way to the Board Room.
  • Prepared for some domestic and international travel as required.
  • Ability to collaborate effectively with a larger team throughout an enterprise transformation.
  • High degree of initiative and personal responsibility.

To succeed in a MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager role, you must have successfully completed a post-secondary degree/diploma in Business, Computer Science, or a related discipline and at least 3+ years of experience with a full life-cycle implementation of D365. Preferably: D365FO/ Dynamics AX Retail experience
 
Key requirements:
You must have experience and strong working knowledge across some or all of the Retail, Commerce, and Supporting modules and Microsoft products:
 

  • Order to cash
  • Inventory, products, variants, attributes
  • Catalogues, assortments, pricing, and discounts
  • Online/Brick & Mortar channel configuration
  • POS Architecture and configuration
  • Payment processing
  • Loyalty
  • Distributed Order Management (DOM) and Intelligent Order Management (IOM)
  • Data migration, data management, and FastTrack go-live assessment.
  • Security framework. roles and best practices
  • Understanding the integration options and underlying technologies available
  • Preferably has experience with Power Platform, Logic Apps, Power Automate
  • Preferably has experience with Azure Data Lake Storage, Dataverse, Dual Write
  • Preferably has experience in Using Lifecycle Services to design and plan a project.
  • Using Azure DevOps, test case planning, and acceptance testing framework
  • Proven experience leading requirement gathering and discovery with users and stakeholders.
  • Participation in the FIT/GAP process and ability to write complete functional design specifications.
  • Solid experience in designing and writing technical specification documents.
  • Demonstrated knowledge and experience in ERP implementation principles, practices, and methodologies.

Preferred Certifications:
 

  • MB-300: Microsoft Dynamics 365: Core Finance and Operations
  • MB-340: Microsoft Dynamics 365 Commerce Functional Consultant

 
If you are driven, determined, and want to take the next step in your career, this is the role for you. Great career progression opportunities await the right person in this exciting MS D365 FO/AX Retail Implementation Manager job.
 
Apply today or email camille@staffx.com.au or call her at +61 3 7042 5305 to discuss this new opportunity!

job.title: Data Analyst -
job.abstract: We are looking for Data Analyst to join our team for a contract role in Mel to work with government clients & provide their expertise with SQL skills.
job.content:
NTT is a leading global IT solutions and services organisation that brings together people, data and things to create a better and more sustainable future. In today’s ‘iNTTerconnected’ world, connections matter more now than ever. By bringing together talented people, world-class technology partners and emerging innovators, we help our clients solve some of the world’s most significant technological, business, and societal challenges. With people at the heart of our success, NTT is committed to attracting and growing the best talent and providing an environment where everyone feels they can belong and their contribution matters.

 

 

Want to be part of the team?

You will join one of the world's largest teams of data scientists, data engineers, and experts in machine learning and AI. In just about every industry, you will be solving big problems using the latest tech. We believe a mix of data, analytics, automation, and responsible AI can do almost anything—spark digital metamorphoses, widen the range of what humans can do, and breathe life into intelligent products and services.

 

 

We are looking for a Data Analyst to work for one of our client for a contract role for the next 4+ months.

You will be responsible for performing analysis of data flows across related systems, and system specific data models with a focus on decommissioning systems that are no longer required.

This role is based in Melbourne (Hybrid) Start date: ASAP #4+months contract #contracttillJuneend2023

 

Key Deliverables:

1.        Data specifications

2.        Data Models

3.        Data Dictionaries

4.        Data Flows with data sets

5.        Scripts where applicable

6.        Business signoff artefacts

7.        Data Migration Reconciliation Plans

8.        Analysis and Handover packs

 

What would make you a good fit for this role?

  • Experience capturing detailed knowledge of the data/information processes (source systems, raw entities and attributes, data models and data dictionaries).
  • Ability to analyse large datasets and establish accurate data profiles (data profiling)
  • Experience with Microsoft SQL Server and Advanced skills in SQL scripting.
  • Knowledge of Azure Data Factory
  • Experience in showcasing of system solution and assisting with User Acceptance Testing.
  • Excellent verbal communication skills with the ability to:
    a. Lead workshops and work directly with solution stakeholders.
    b. Ability to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team and provide leadership in your area of expertise.
    c. Negotiate, and resolve problem, challenging opinions where necessary to achieve quality solutions.

 

 

Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us. Apply today.

 

 

Career at NTT means:

· Being part of a global pioneer – where you gain exposure to our Fortune 500 clients and world-leading global technology partners and work with a network of over 40,000 smart and diverse colleagues across 57 countries, delivering services in over 200 countries.

· Being at the forefront of cutting-edge technology – backed with a 150-year heritage of using technology for good. With 40% of the world’s internet traffic running on our network and where Emoji were first invented, you can be proud of the group’s many new ‘firsts’.

· Making a difference – by doing meaningful work that helps to shape the future for our clients, and across industries and communities around the world.

· Being your best self – in a progressive ‘Connected Working’ environment that promotes flexibility, connection, and wellbeing. Where diversity and different perspectives are embraced to ensure equal opportunities for all.

· Having ongoing opportunities to own and develop your career – with a personal and professional development plan and access to the broadest learning offerings in the industry.

 



Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us. Apply today.

For more information about this or other opportunities, please contact Neha Jhingan . Please quote our job reference number 581208.

About us

NTT Ltd. is a leading global technology services company. Working with organizations around the world, we achieve business outcomes through intelligent technology solutions. For us, intelligent means data driven, connected, digital and secure. As a global ICT provider, we employ more than 40,000 people in a diverse and dynamic workplace that spans 57 countries, trading in 73 countries and delivering services in over 200 countries and regions

NTT is proud to be an equal opportunity employer with a global culture that embraces diversity. We are committed to providing an environment free of unfair discrimination and harassment. We do not discriminate based on age, race, color, sex, religion, national origin, disability, pregnancy, marital status, sexual orientation, gender reassignment, veteran status, or other protected category.

job.title: EL 1 Director, Data Analytics
job.abstract: We are looking for a Data Analytics specialist to fill a key vacancy in our SADA team.
job.content:
About the EL 1 Director, Data Analytics, SADA in the ANAO

This is your opportunity to undertake work that you can’t do anywhere else. The EL 1 Director, Data Analytics is a unique position within the Australian Public Service. You will work side-by-side with experienced leaders and play a pivotal role in ensuring accountability and transparency in the Australian Government sector.


About the role

The Systems Assurance and Data Analytics Group (SADA) provides support and services to the ANAO’s financial statements, performance statement, and performance audit groups, and Corporate Management Group. SADA comprises of approximately 35 staff who work in teams specialising in either IT systems and controls assurance or in data analytics. Within SADA, the Data Analytics Team consists of approximately 10 staff, with backgrounds encompassing professions such as research, data analytics, engineering, economics, information technology, finance and accounting.


The opportunity

The ANAO undertakes audits of a variety of government programs, and in doing so conducts assurance and data analytics activities that examine data, complex IT systems, and cyber security risks. The Data Analytics Team provides data analytic support to the audit and assurance activities of the ANAO, ensuring ANAO remains responsive to technology and data changes in the Australian Public Sector, specifically in analysing how government uses technology and data to support program implementation and manage risk. The Data Analytics Team is responsible for the delivery of both business-as-usual data analytics support to audits, and projects aimed at using data analytics to help achieve the strategic objectives of the ANAO.

The Director (Data Analytics) is a leader that supports the Senior Director Data Analytics to deliver the above functions of the Data Analytics Team. Your day-to-day work would likely involve tasks along the lines of the below:

  • Lead and manage a team responsible for undertaking data analytics and data support tasks for audits/projects managed by SADA, the Performance Audit Services Group (PASG), the Financial Statements Audit Services Group (FSASG), Performance Statements Audit Service Group (PSASG), and other business groups;
  • Demonstrate technical expertise in data analytics and audit methodologies and provide a high level of professional and technical advice on a range of data analytics and audit issues;
  • Undertake and manage data analytics projects and produce and supervise the production of data analytics deliverables;
  • Raise awareness across the organisation of data related issues for different types of audits and projects;
  • Manage client relationships including maintaining a high level of engagement and communication with audit or business teams;
  • Assist in the formulation of business and operational plans for the SADA Group; and
  • Mentor, coach, guide and support the professional development of junior staff.


Desirable skills

Given the nature of the work within the Data Analytics Team, the following skills and experience would be highly regarded:

  • Previous audit experience is not essential, however willingness to lean to apply data analytics skills in the audit context is important;
  • Experience working with a wide range of data-formats or data sources from various IT/business information systems; and
  • Experience working with data-related technologies in the Azure cloud, such as but not limited to: SQL, Azure Data Factory, and Azure Devops.

This role may be offered on an ongoing basis in Canberra. If you are found suitable but do not receive a job offer, we’ll add you to a list of people we can contact about similar jobs that become available. This is called a merit pool.


About you

The successful candidate will have the following:

  • Tertiary qualifications in a discipline that requires the use of programming languages for the analysis of complex information, interpretation, and written reporting of findings;
  • Strong research, conceptual and analytical skills, including the ability to think strategically, investigate and develop innovative solutions;
  • A strong background and proven success in the delivery of data analytics services to achieve business objectives and experience using data analysis and visualisation languages/tools such as Python and Power BI;
  • Advanced project management knowledge and skills including planning, leading and managing innovative and complex data or research projects;
  • Demonstrated capability to communicate complex technical information effectively to a non-technical audience;
  • Excellent stakeholder engagement and strong representational skills in particular expertise in consultation, liaison, and negotiation with senior stakeholders;
  • Demonstrated leadership, interpersonal and people management skills including the ability to manage, lead, mentor and develop team members with diverse skills and backgrounds.

 

Benefits

The ANAO is proud to offer a modern, activity-based work environment and a strong focus on ongoing training and development to grow and invest in your career.

You will be offered quality in-house training and on-the-job mentoring as well as support for you to undertake your professional studies.

We also offer generous salaries with additional 15.4% superannuation, flex time for APS level staff, an Employee Assistance Program for staff and their families and a range of different leave options.


Interested?

For more information about the roles and how to apply, please refer to our ANAO Careers webpage, and submitting your application via our online recruitment system by: 11:30pm (AEST) on Sunday 19 March 2023

job.title: Solution Architect
job.abstract: BroadReach are recruiting multi-domain Solution Architects, data/information specialists, integration specialists and Azure specialists.
job.content:
About us

BroadReach Consulting is a West Australian company providing information, integration, solution and enterprise architecture services to a range of clients over the last 16 years. We have a proven track record of delivering high quality, practical and cost-effective Strategic Advisory, Architecture and Digital Transformation services.

Qualifications & experience

  • Solution design: Ability to design and deliver end-to-end solutions that meet business requirements and align with the overall technology strategy. A deep understanding of solution design and delivery methods and techniques such as TOGAF and Agile Practices.
  • 5+ years’ hands-on experience of successfully solutioning and delivering solutions and evidence of continued learning and development in your chosen field of expertise.
  • Strong technical background with a deep understanding of various technologies, such as cloud computing (Azure, AWS), data and analytical functions, software design and development methods and practices.
  • Proven and demonstrable experience in architecting solutions with cloud-native service and platforms such as Azure and AWS.
  • An understanding and practical application of the TOGAF 9.x architectural method and framework and modelling languages such as Archimate 3.x.
  • Architecture methodology: Knowledge of architecture frameworks, such as TOGAF, and ability to apply these frameworks to ensure solution design is consistent, scalable, and secure.
  • Outstanding interpersonal, written and verbal presentation and communication skills. Strong ability to present and seek feedback and direction of complex ICT topics to a non-ICT audiences such as senior executives through to operational team members.
  • Stakeholder management: Experience in engaging with stakeholders, including business leaders, technical teams, and vendors, to gather requirements and build consensus on solution design.
  • Proven and demonstrable experience in understanding, and then working on business and technical solutions to complex problems.

Tasks & responsibilities

  • Leads the development of architectures for complex solutions ensuring consistency with agreed requirements, constraints, and dependencies.
  • Applies a whole-of-system understanding to problem identification and solutioning, including understanding the business context, problem identification, benefits, risks and requirements mapping, people and process change, data/information analysis, application and technical solution identification.
  • Provides technical guidance and governance on solution development and integration. Evaluates requests for changes and deviations from specifications and recommends action
  • Manages trade-offs and balances functional, service quality and systems management requirements within a significant area of the organisation. Communicates proposed decisions to stakeholders.
  • Coordinates and manages the target architecture across multiple projects or initiatives. Maintains a stable, viable architecture and ensures consistency of design and adherence to appropriate standards across multiple projects or initiatives.
  • Contributes to the creation and development of technology roadmaps, including documenting target architectures and strategies, and ensuring alignment with, and enablement of, business strategy.
  • Communicates technical concepts, business and system requirements, effectively (in non-technical language) and engage widely with business sponsors, user groups and stakeholders to address concerns and advise about required changes to operating models, services, organisation design, and processes.
  • Where necessary, manages solution design and delivery, using various delivery models such as Waterfall, Agile, DevOps, SDLC).

Benefits

  • BroadReach offer you the flexibility to work with us as a permanent member of our consulting team or as a contractor. We offer above-market rates to secure the best team of like-minded, experienced professionals.
  • We offer training and development opportunities, peer-2-peer coaching and support, as well as opportunities to develop new skills and progress your career in interesting roles.
  • We believe in fostering creative freedom which enables people to choose how best to perform their roles and provide our clients with an outstanding experience.

job.title: Junior / Graduate Data Analyst
job.abstract: Blue Crystal Solutions along with Royal Flying Doctors Service are excited to present an opportunity for a Graduate Analyst.
job.content:
The Opportunity

Blue Crystal Solutions in partnership with the Royal Flying Doctors Service (Central Operations) are excited to present an opportunity for a Junior / Graduate Data Analyst.  The successful candidate will be looking to play a critical role in ensuring that technology enables and supports a scalable, maintainable, and reliable technology environment.  You will work in close partnership with wider data teams, data stewards, technical and business stakeholders to analyse, refine and report on data to address business needs and enable effective decision making.

This role will be based on-site at Royal Flying Doctors Service (Central Operations) Head Office for an initial 12-month period. 

What you’ll be doing

Working within a dedicated team, expect to:

  • Work with state-of-the-art data processing frameworks, technologies, and platforms
  • Improve data quality through testing, tooling and continuously evaluating performance.
  • Work with other software engineers, data analysts, data scientists, and decision-makers, such as product owners, to build solutions and gain novel insights.
  • Act as the bridge between our back end and analysts and work on data cataloguing/management and build/maintain crucial data pipelines.
  • Contribute to a digital health technology elevation with RFDS.  Opportunities to extend into ML, AI, Digital Twins etc.

What we’re looking for

The successful candidate will have solid foundations of the below requirements, with the ability to be coached and trained to increase their skills:

Key Knowledge and Experience: 

  • Exposure to data engineering, data warehouse and data migration projects.
  • Exposure in designing and developing SQL stored procedures, views and data models in a MS-SQL or Oracle database environment.
  • Experience in critical Data systems (Oracle / SQL Server / Redshift / Snowflake / Postgres)
  • Experience in ETL and structured query language (TSQL, PLSQL) 

Qualifications, Experience, and Desired Capabilities:

  • Tertiary qualification, in Information Technology, Data Analytics, Mathematics or a related discipline. (Desirable only)
  • At least 1-2 years’ experience in technology industry. (Desirable only)
  • A strong understanding of Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Science and Cloud Computing.
  • Excellent communication skills and the ability to win over clients at all business levels.
  • Ability to work in a team environment and collaborate on multiple tasks.
  • Excellent writing skills, with the ability to clearly define how we will help solve problems.
  • Proven ability to work independently to meet tight deadline.
  • Ability to effectively manage multiple stakeholders and competing deadlines.

 

Nice to have:

  • Exposure in designing, developing and supporting various data technologies. Including - Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, MS SQL Server, Azure Synapse, Power BI, Python, Oracle DB, Postgres, MySQL etc.
  • Working knowledge of Unix/Linux Shell Scripting. 
  • HTML, CSS, JavaScript.

 

The offer

At Blue Crystal Solutions, we offer rewarding opportunities for proactive technology professionals, blending a social environment of highly skilled and dynamic people. We place a high importance on regular staff social events to drive a collaborative and inclusive culture. 

Key rewards and benefits for our people:

  • Competitive salary 
  • Exposure to multiple technologies, continuous learning, and professional development
  • Work in an agile environment focused on ensuring customer success.

 

The Organisations: 

Royal Flying Doctors Service (Central Operations)

 

As a not-for-profit organisation, every day we assist around 100 patients in South Australia and the Northern Territory, be it an aeromedical evacuation, a GP and Community Health Nurse clinic, a telehealth call, a mental health or oral health clinic, or a child's immunisation. From our four aeromedical bases at Darwin, Alice Springs, Port Augusta, and Adelaide, and our health services staffed by Remote Area Nurses in Marree, Andamooka, and Marla, RFDS Central Operations assists over 50,000 patients every year - that's one patient every 20 minutes!

 

RFDS Central Operations has been in existence since 1939 and is a key player in the delivery of 24/7 emergency aeromedical and essential primary health care services to people living, working, and travelling in rural and remote South and Central Australia.

 

Interested in knowing more about RFDS, visit: https://www.flyingdoctor.org.au/sant/about/

 

Blue Crystal Solutions

 

As a proud South Australian Company, Blue Crystal Solutions is a trusted and respected leader in cloud, infrastructure, database, and application services throughout Australia. Our depth of knowledge in these fields enables us to deliver unrivalled value to our customers. 

 

For more information about Blue Crystal Solutions, see our website: http://www.bluecrystal.com.au

 

Eligibility Criteria

Permanent Australian residency is essential.

If you feel your skills and experience match the above criteria, please send your resume to info@bluecrystal.com.au

For more information or clarification on the role, please contact info@bluecrystal.com.au

job.title: Data Developer & Application Support
job.abstract: Fantastic opportunity for a Data Developer to join our IT Team!
job.content:
Data Developer & Application Support  
  
About Us 
  
For over 60 years, Cancer Council Queensland’s pioneering work has helped save thousands of lives and has improved the quality of life for people living with cancer. Our mission is to lead Queenslanders in a partnership against cancer. 
  
Cancer Council Queensland raises funds that are dedicated to improving the quality of life for people living with cancer through research to support prevention and early detection. 
  
We are dynamic, outcome-focused, responsive to community needs, and committed to voluntarism and the pursuit of excellence.  
  
Cancer Council Queensland employees and volunteers lead Queenslanders in a partnership against cancer by employing high-performing employees who live our values of being responsible, inclusive, equitable, and collaborative. 
  
Working at Cancer Council Queensland 
  
Our greatest asset is our diverse team of talented, savvy people. Our awesome employees and volunteers tell us that Cancer Council Queensland is a meaningful, rewarding and fun place to work. 
  
We provide a positive and supportive working environment where you will be a valued team member. We love to recognise and reward our team of superstars with employee benefits such as extra paid days off.   
  
About the role  
  
As a Data Developer within the Applications team, you will be responsible for supporting business stakeholders by providing them with accurate data solutions. The role will be responsible for delivering datasets and reports which are accurate, relevant and of good quality. This output is to be delivered in accordance with business requirements and our data governance principles, to which you will be active member in guiding and implementing. You will also seek out new opportunities for data analysis and business improvement using your technical data skills and knowledge. 
  
This role is a Permanent, Full-time role (37.5 hours per week).  
    
About you  
  
Your Contribution   
  • Work within the Microsoft Azure technology stack to deliver data insights and data extracts to business stakeholders through designing and building advanced queries that consume and aggregate Cancer Council Queensland’s enterprise data sources. 
  • Assist in identifying business opportunities and improvements for stakeholders using data insights and technical solutions delivered by the Applications team. 
  • Build and maintain Cancer Council Queensland’s suite of business intelligence reports ensuring that they meet business requirements and that they present data in a format that is easy to understand and interpret. 
  • Build strong working relationships with stakeholders to gain a deep understanding their data needs, and promote practices and solutions that enable reporting self-service and ease of use. 
  • Assist in the design, support and development of ETL and ELT data pipelines, data lake, warehousing and unification assets. 
  • Deliver training and guidance to users in all aspects of BI reporting. 
  • Reduce the complexity of handling and managing datasets at CCQ. Reduce Excel and flat file use, and centrally control and purge requested files.  
  • Work within, and in alignment with the defined IT strategic priorities and goals.  
  • Work in accordance with all data governance and data security policies ensuring that users are also aware of such policies.  
Qualifications, Experience, Knowledge and Skills  
 
Essential Skills:   
  • Advanced skills with data querying (SQL) and report authoring. 
  • Demonstrated experience working with data in both a business and technical context. 
  • Knowledge of databases, data integration, data warehousing and data analytics. 
  • Experience with data visualisation tools (Power BI). 
  • Experience programming applications (C#, Python or similar) 
  • Completed or completing tertiary qualifications in relevant IT field. 
  • Strong organisational and time management skills and ability to manage multiple tasks. 
  • Ability to maintain effective working relationships and communicate with people from all levels. 
  • Excellent written and oral communication skills. 
  • Good problem-solving abilities. 
Desirable Skills:  
  • Certifications and/or training in Microsoft Power BI. 
  • Certifications and/or training in data warehousing techniques. 
  • Certifications and/or training in Microsoft Azure Data Factory, SSIS or SSAS. 
  • Experience working with cloud-based API data sources.     
Benefits  
  
Cancer Council Queensland has a collaborative, energetic, and supportive team culture, contributing to meaningful work with a tangible impact. By celebrating and fostering our individual strengths, we take on more challenging work. In turn, we lead more balanced, exciting and fulfilling lives. Our growing Non-for-Profit organisation offers employees:     
  • Flexible work arrangements (Flexible Work Hours and Work from Home options) 
  • ATO-Approved Salary Packaging up to the value of $18,549 per Fringe Benefit Tax year 
  • Recognition and Rewards Program  
  • Two paid Wellbeing days per year  
  • One paid ‘Thank you’ day at the end of the year  
  • Professional Development Allowance  
  • Corporate social events (such as bring your dog to work day) 
  • Team events, employee connectivity and Healthy Workplace Activities  
  • Cancer Council Retail shop discount    
Meet Our People

People (Employment) Team 
Cancer Council Queensland

job.title: Application Architect
job.abstract: BE THE DIFFERENCEAt AIA we don’t simply believe in being ‘the best’. We believe in better – because there’s no limit to how far ‘better�
job.content:
BE THE DIFFERENCE

At AIA we don’t simply believe in being ‘the best’. We believe in better – because there’s no limit to how far ‘better’ can take us. Everything we do is driven by our purpose to make a difference by helping people embrace Healthier, Longer, Better Lives. And every one of our people has an important part role to play. If you want to make a difference by helping shape a healthier, better-protected Australia, read on.

The Opportunity:

AIA Australia is currently undergoing a large technology, data and business transformation program resulting in refreshing the technology blueprint and the introduction of contemporary ways of working with the aim of creating a simpler, faster more connected organisation.

In this exciting role as an Application Architect, you will take a lead role in coordinating technical skill sets and facilitating, planning and managing in close consultation with the project manager the estimates, delivery schedules while enhancing, and overseeing the technical implementation across Data & Analytics technology portfolio (on-prem and cloud data stack).

Ensure that technical delivery aligns with IT strategy and architectural principles and that best practice coding standards are applied to meet all requirements (e.g. functional, security, business continuity, operations, user experience, performance and accessibility).

This role will report to the Technology Portfolio anager and can be based in Sydney or Melbourne.

To do this successfully you will:

  • Design major aspects of the architecture of an application, including components for on-prem Datawarehouse application and on Azure cloud platform  
  • Take full responsibility for defining a technical solution based on detailed Business Requirements and aligned to the solution architecture data models across the technology portfolio
  • Create and build logical data models, modern Data Pipelines and Data Streams that address relevant areas of complexity and provide a fully considered and detailed solution design across the technology portfolio
  • Lead the data migration from legacy on-prem Datalake systems to Azure cloud solutions
  • Ensure a seamless integration of new and existing applications to eliminate potential problems and maintain data structure and integrity
  • Work collaboratively with the AIA business SME’s, Project Managers, Development Teams (local and offshore) and vendors to deliver required software solution across the technology portfolio
  • Mentor and support data engineers, data modellers in development of best engineering practice and upskilling engineers in Azure toolset

To be successful in this position you will have

  • Proven experience in developing, embedding and implementing data governance and architecture frameworks and processes
  • Experience in engaging, collaborating and influencing people across different business units and at all levels of financial service organisations.
  • The ability to be a strong team player who demonstrates flexibility and a pro-activeness to deliver to business outcomes
  • Experience in software design and architecture in the Data & Analytics domain
  • Knowledge of architectural patterns and software design patterns, with demonstrable experience applying the patterns to solution design
  • Experience in the Insurance or Financial Services industry preferred
  • Extensive experience of working in Agile (Scrum) and Waterfall/ Hybrid
  • Certifications like Microsoft Certified Azure Architect and Microsoft Certified Azure Data Engineer Associate [link removed]

Why choose AIA:
 

  • At AIA, we’ve made a promise to help people live healthier, longer, better lives. And it starts with our own people
  • AIA Australia is part of the larger regional Asia AIA Group, which is the largest public listed life insurance company in the Asia-Pacific region
  • Access our training and development to build on your current skills
  • Career development through internal mobility opportunities
  • Work for a business helping millions of Australians and make a difference to someone’s life everyday
  • Access additional leave days a year to recharge and refresh yourself
  • Enjoy wonderful Health and Wellbeing initiatives that support you
  • Work with supportive and inclusive working environment
  • Flexible working arrangement

At AIA Australia, we’re proud to help guide, support and protect the wellbeing of over 3.5 million Australians. Through life and health insurance, financial wellbeing and our total wellbeing ecosystem that includes AIA Vitality – the world’s leading science-backed wellbeing programme – we’ve started a movement to make Australia the healthiest, best protected nation in the world. As part of the AIA Group - the largest independent publicly listed pan-Asian life insurance group with a presence in 18 markets in Asia-Pacific – it is our ambition to engage one billion people to live Healthier, Longer, Better Lives by 2030.  Lots of companies like to say they’re different. What makes us truly different at AIA, is the difference we make in people’s lives.

AIA is different. Are you?

bullets: Join a high performing team that feels like a family
Help us redefine how people think about insurance
Join a progressive company, operating in 18 markets across Asia-Pacific

job.title: .Net Developer
job.abstract: Are you looking for a new role where your contribution matters? Come join us at SG fleet.
job.content:
WHO WE ARE
We are a financial services company that specialises in fleet management, vehicle leasing and salary packaging, with a presence across Australia, the UK and NZ. With 3 major brands, a total portfolio under management of $2.5 Billion and over 1100 employees, we work at the forefront of the fleet management and leasing industry. We believe that our people are the most important contributor to our continued success and are instrumental in making us a great place to work.


SOME OF OUR PERKS INCLUDE
  • We are a fun, friendly team where you're not just a number
  • Hybrid work from home, work from office
  • 2 “Wellness” days per annum (yes, in addition to your annual leave!)
  • We will give you ongoing training and development within your role
  • We also offer wide range of benefits including gym and education subsidies
  • And not to mention, a competitive remuneration package including a performance-based bonus plan
OUR CULTURE
When adding a new member to the SG Fleet Group family, we look for people who embody our values, allowing us to provide an unparalleled customer experience.  You will have the opportunity to thrive in a positive and fun atmosphere where everyone is valued and recognised for their efforts, whilst being a part of an amazing team.

We have a Cross-functional teams collaborating closely with customers and business
  • Teams are organised around a business area or function as opposed to a skillset
  • We follow the ‘2 Pizza’ rule to limit team size (should be able to feed the team with 2 pizzas)
  • Practice groups provide peer support, training, and collaboration opportunities
  • Team members are encouraged to broaden their skills beyond their main role resulting in more productive teams and more skilled and rounded team members
  • We do not operate in silos either technical or business vs IT

Modern technology platform
  • We’ve invested in a modern, hybrid cloud technology platform using a range of Azure PaaS service
  • We use up to date development tools wherever possible such as .Net 6, Visual Studio 2022 and SQL Server 2019
  • We support our teams with modern productivity tools like Jira, Confluence, Miro and Microsoft 365
  • We have a dedicated platforms team who’s mission is to let other teams focus on delivering great software rather than getting bogged in boilerplate and plumbing
  • We’re using solutions like Azure Data Lake, DataBricks, Power BI, Power Platform, Dynamics 365

AS A .NET DEVELOPER...
You will be responsible to deliver functional and valuable software solutions at SG Fleet using the Microsoft .Net technology stack. To enhance SG Fleet’s software development and delivery process, both directly and through mentoring other team members.

YOUR DAYS WILL INVOLVE…

The major responsibilities of this position include but are not limited to:
  • Develop innovative, efficient and scalable solutions using .NET technologies
  • Participate in systems and solution design and work with business users and business analysts to understand the requirements.
  • Communicate effectively with technical and business stakeholders. Clearly articulate accurate status of work.
  • Mentor and transfer technical skills to other developers in the team. Perform reviews on code produced by your peers.
  • Ensure established coding standards are adhered to; contribute to enhancing existing standards. Deliver to quality standards.
  • Ensure all activities are undertaken in accordance with agreed service levels and procedures, maximising delivery of functional software with the least impact.
  • Assess and report on risks that could impact on systems and data security and ensure appropriate mitigation practices are in place.

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT YOU
  • Up to date with new tools and technologies in the Microsoft space
  • Can explore new concepts and solve new problems with limited supervision
  • Experienced in working with modern cloud architectures, preferably in Azure
  • Is quick to understand business concepts and understands how to apply technology to provide business value
Essential
  • Solid practical experience in .Net development
  • Proficient with Microsoft software development technologies and tools i.e. .NET, MVC, WCF, Web API, Entity Framework, SQL, etc.)
  • Experience with .NET Core, Angular, GIT is an advantage.
Desirable
  • Strong experience in agile way of work and agile software development
  • Knowledge of Agile process tools and associated CI/CD tools (eg. JIRA, Confluence)
  • Knowledge of other Microsoft-related tools & products (eg. Azure, Dynamics, Visio 365, etc)

WHAT'S NEXT
We'd love to hear from you if you're ready to take on your next challenge at a company that embodies diversity and belonging while also offering work-life balance and career development.

We are a proud equal opportunity employer, and welcome everyone to our team. Resumes may be sent and interviews may take place prior to the closing date for applications. To give yourself the best chance of selection, please do not leave your application to the application 'close' date. As a pre-requisite to employment, the successful applicant will be required to complete pre-employment screening.

We're not so large that you're work is just part of the machine
Everyone can make a difference to our customers

job.title: Data Engineer
job.abstract: Permanent Opportunity - Data Engineer / Data Quality Specialist! Fortitude Valley / Hybrid Working, and exposure to new and innovative technology!
job.content:
A new Permanent Opportunity is currently available for a a Data Engineer / Data Quality Specialist to join this reputable Queensland Statutory Authority based in Fortitude Valley.

The Data Engineer Data Quality Specialist will be responsible for supporting the Data Analytics team in delivering data engineering services with a particular focus on supporting the soon to be introduced Data Quality Toolset.

Key responsibilities of the Data Engineer / Data Quality Specialist will be as follows;
  • Work as part of the Data & Analytics team as a Data Engineer providing technical guidance on Azure data management usage for ingestion of data into the Enterprise Data Warehouse
  • Design, build, execute, and maintain automated tests and data profiling runs. Responsible for formulation of rules-based and pattern-based tests, and writing code to discover, implement, execute, and manage those tests to ensure data products meet expectations.
  • Work Collaboratively and build relationships with stakeholders (working with Data Stewards to assist understanding in using the Data Quality toolset) to support and administer the Data Quality Toolset while making recommendations to improve data quality from findings from the Data Quality Tools.
  • Provide assessments of the integrity of data from multiple sources.
  • Become the Subject Matter Expert for the administration and use of the Atacama Data Quality product set.
  • Provide ITIL level 2 support for EDW and ingestion processes with a particular focus on supporting the Data Quality Toolset.
 To be considered for this exciting new role, you will be required to demonstrate the following technical competencies;
  • Ability to work with stakeholders to understand requirement specifications for the build of data quality profiling rules, along with movement and transformation of data between systems. Ability to plan work and meet deadlines working with teams or alone.
  • Data Analyst/Engineer with a passion for utilising commercial Data Quality products to perform data quality profiling and monitoring of data quality results over time.
  • Able to work independently as well as with other team members in an Agile environment who can deliver timely agile sprint outcomes.
  • Experienced Data Engineer problem solver who can work in cloud and on-premise environments to create a connected view of domain owned data across the organisation.
  • The role requires extensive use of the data movement products within Microsoft Azure and can develop / support data movement code and physical data model table building from technical specifications.
  • Competent with the development of ETL routines automated to ensure data currency at the required speed of refresh/availability.
  • Fluent in data programming languages/ETL and Scripting tools
  • Have proven experience with any or all of the following: data quality, data management, data governance, analytics, business intelligence, dashboards or reporting, data science, and/or data-intensive software development projects.
  • Aptitude for becoming familiar with new tools and technologies - Ataccama
Interested applicants are urged to contact Shameem Prinsloo at shameem.prinsloo@troocoo.com or contact 0411 516 678 to discuss this opportunity in further detail.

job.abstract:
We have an exciting opportunity for a Systems Administrator on a contract basis. HIRING IMMEDIATELY! 
Please APPLY NOW!
job.content:
Finite IT is currently seeking a System Administrator on a 6 month contract basis with possible extension for WA Government based in Perth CBD.

The work is required to provide backfill in our ICT Operations Infrastructure team working in a team of system administrators.

  • Manage and respond to Systems Administration and Application Support requests ensuring the provision of effective, efficient and timely support services.
  • Undertake daily monitoring and review the tuning of server and application platforms environment including storage, backup, security and patching and capacity management to ensure an efficient environment.
  • Work with vendors to support and administer systems and applications.
  • Receive and manage responses to incidents, service requests and problems arising from daily business activity.
  • Provide advice to management regarding current or emerging issues affecting the support services.
  • Monitors and tests server performance against SLAs and where required initiates remedial action.
  • Review and updates documentation relevant to the configuration of the server environment.
  • Oversee and support the restoration of server platforms following a disaster recovery event.
  • Provide expert technical review and advice of documentation including server design and deployment documents, arising from the DPRID's Right Size and Rationalise project.
  • Plan and/or assist in planning for service and application deployments and retirements within the legacy environment.
  • Supports the IS Operations response to cyber security events as part of the infrastructure team including reporting on activity and tracing events.



Our client operates primarily on a Windows server environment, with a significant investment in VMWare primarily using Dell hardware. There is a growing footprint in Azure as well as some legacy Debian Linux instances. Citrix supports a small number of legacy systems and an F5 is used for load balancing and VPN access to the Department's legacy environment.

Experience in and awareness of Oracle (OVM, DB, Oracle Linux etc), Objective, Hyper-V, Azure data factories, SAN, SolarWinds, Commvault, SharePoint Online, Microsoft DevOps, Tenable security suite, containerisation with Docker are desirable.

Working in this environment will afford plenty of challenges from the wide scope of tasks. It will require someone to be flexible as priorities will change and be able to demonstrate that they can work and contribute to a team environment.


If you are looking for your next challenge, PLEASE APPLY NOW! We will contact you to further discuss about the role.

• 12 MONTH CONTRACT

job.abstract: We are currently seeking an Application & O365 Developer to assist in the development and maintenance of applications and associated systems.
job.content:
Keolis Downer is the largest private provider of multimodal public transport in Australia, and the southern hemisphere. We support 250 million passenger journeys annually in Australia.

Adelaide Metro Rail carries 15 million passengers every year and services 89 stations. Our vision is to deliver sustainable, revitalised train services for the people of metropolitan Adelaide and its visitors. Keolis Downer brings a strong focus on safety and customer service through its Zero Harm and Think Like a Passenger values.

We are currently seeking an Application & O365 Developer to assist in the development and maintenance of applications and associated systems to meet the needs of Keolis Downer Adelaide’s internal business and rail operations business.  You will provide value to the business through the development of innovative and effective technology solutions. You will:

  • Coordinate and perform service requests, incidents and problems management as assigned from the Service Management process for all applications
  • Plan and manage deployment of application upgrades (as required)
  • Design with the Applications team application capacity planning, monitoring and tuning, forecast demand
  • Delivery of assigned project works/tasks on budget, to schedule, and within scope
  • Research, consult, analyse and evaluate program functional and technical requirements
  • Undertake system and user analysis to identify application and system improvements
  • Deliver software modifications including system analysis, design specification, development, test, deploy as required
  • Develop and deploy strategy, process and solution for the creation, maintenance and retention of corporate and/or operational information in a secure manner
  • Define solution monitoring and alerting requirements, including security mechanisms to mitigate and manage security risks
  • Perform assurance testing works as required, using appropriate testing methodology
  • Provide advice, guidance and expertise in developing proposals and strategies for software design activities such as financial evaluation and costing for recommending software purchases and upgrades

About you

  • Tertiary qualifications in Information Technology ; And/Or significant proven experience, relevant to this discipline
  • Experience in designing, customising and implementing complex and business critical applications
  • Project management skills – including the ability to define, estimate and plan work
  • Proven application, systems analysis and technical architecture skills
  • Excellent written and verbal communications skills to support efficient interactions with customers
  • Problem Solving skills, with proven experience in a systems approach to problem solving
  • Teamwork skills; able to effectively work and deliver results within a team environment
  • .NET application development; (.Net and .NET Core)
  • Azure Platform (Azure Data Factory, Azure Functions, Databases Postgres, Azure SQL, Azure Key Vault, Storage Accounts and Web App Design/Creation)
  • Experience in analysing and establishing business requirements and/or working with business analysts 
  • It is desirable that you have experience in on-prem/legacy applications, including IIS, ASPx Websites, Understanding of Active Directory and Good understanding of Azure Active Directory
  • Ideally you will have O365/M365 knowledge, Power BI and development for mobile platforms and scripting skills

This opportunity to join Keolis Downer in building the future of transport systems in Adelaide will be hands on in creating a world class public transport system for the Adelaide metro area, on par with our global mission.

What we offer

  • A highly supportive, team environment
  • Competitive remuneration
  • Employee Benefits which include an Employee Assistance program, reward and recognition programs and ongoing learning and development programs
  • Based at our state-of-the-art purpose built Dry Creek offices with parking available
  • Full time permanent position

The Keolis Downer culture is one of engagement and enablement – we want to hear your ideas and support you in implementing them. We are focused on developing our staff, identifying career pathways and creating opportunity across our global network.

Interested?  Click “apply now” or contact Susan Hutton at kda-recruitment@keolisdowner.com if you have any questions.

Closing date: 2 March 2023

(Note: Keolis Downer does not accept applications via email)

Keolis Downer is committed to achieving a diverse workforce and strongly encourages applications from women and indigenous Australians.

job.content:
Findex is building a workplace that is unrestrained by geography and hierarchy. A workplace that is connected through technology. A workplace that values your needs and allows you to be the best version of yourself.

With a focus on empowering you to work in a way that best meets your needs and those of your team and clients, your career growth isn’t limited by your location. With more than 100 offices throughout metropolitan, regional and rural Australasia, we provide you with opportunities to pursue your dreams, wake up every day in a place you love and surround yourself with people who inspire and challenge you.

We attract, retain and promote people who share a sense of purpose and belonging. And we come together to achieve amazing outcomes for our clients and communities. We share a sense of purpose and belonging that goes beyond the day to day. And we have a passion for creating opportunities for growth and sustainability that ripple throughout metropolitan and regional communities.

Write your next chapter with Findex where you can grow your career with us from anywhere and be empowered to work in a way that best meets your needs and those of your team and clients. 


What will you typical week look like?

  • Set up data pipeline through APIs and integrate developed portals with other platforms
  • Identify, create, manage, and maintain analytically rigorous data and automating collection processes
  • Analyse processes and systems to extract insights from both structured and unstructured
  • Deploy developed analytics solutions in Azure Dev Ops including database
  • Interacting with clients to gather requirements and identify scope

More about the perks

  • Full remote working set-up to work from wherever you want – work from home and/or office
  • Be rewarded with opportunities for development and promotion
  • Grow your career while living somewhere you love
  • Work around your family, lifestyle or personal commitments
  • Thrive in a team who come together to achieve amazing outcomes

Let’s talk about you!

You have the following skills and attributes…

  • Minimum 6+ years of relevant experience with end-to-end implementation of advanced analytics/ machine learning solutions
  • Experience working with structured or unstructured databases such as SQL server, Mango DB
  • Experience developing applications with Django frameworks
  • Experience in extracting data from various data sources (internal or external), in different types and integrate the extracted data
  • Develop, build, test, and validate algorithms and models
  • Translate unstructured problems into well-defined machine learning projects
  • Leads and manages a team of data scientists that is innovative, collaborative, and customer-focused

As well as experience in: 

  • Cloud service providers (Microsoft Azure and AWS) such as Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse, Azure Data lake, Azure Databrick, Key Vaults
  • Develop data pipeline for ETL process
  • DevOps and database/Azure deployment
  • Python programming and strong knowledge in Django framework is must, familiarity with Java or C++ is an asset.
  • Using business intelligence and visualisation tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau)
  • Strong knowledge about machine learning algorithms such as XG Boost, CNN and RNN, decision tree analysis and statistical methods.
  • Bonus points if you have experience on front end/backend development frameworks such as Vue.js, Django
  • Bonus points if you have experience on Graph QL

Let’s talk about our team

  • Knowledgeable and passionate about delivering quality service
  • Collaborative, friendly and supportive
  • Connected with stakeholders in the business both locally and nationally

More about Findex

job.title: BI Developer
job.abstract: We are looking for a BI Analyst who wants to be part of an exciting transformational period and dynamic team.
job.content:
Connect Hearing is a nationwide provider of hearing health care services. We exist to make a positive difference in our client's lives through better hearing. We are proud to be part of Sonova, the leading manufacturer of innovative hearing care solutions, present in over 100 countries across the world. Passionate about our purpose, we believe in giving back through our "Hear the World" foundation.

The main focus of the role is to design, develop, test, maintain, programme, query & document all applications relating to the BI stack to maintain and continuously improve data integrity, database structure, safeguard continuous data flows to the business & facilitate accurate reporting & decision making.

This role will be part of our hybrid model which includes work from home and our office based in North Sydney.

Day to day for you this would look like:

  • Investigate & interpret undocumented data structures across Connect’s applications including Simply Hearing, NOAH, Business Central, Navision, CH Website, Jet Database, BI database, all related servers.
  • Research, consult, analyse and evaluate systems & system program needs.
  • Identify & trace data anomalies, technology limitations and deficiencies in existing systems and associated processes, procedures and methods.
  • Write and maintain scripts & code to:
    • Transform data from source to target systems, & as part of a data migration program
    • Optimize reliability & efficiency of data pipeline
    • Create data-warehouses, marts, cubes & sets
    • Build segments, analytics & reports
  • Develop & perform quality assurance processes & protocols to assure data quality including testing, debugging,diagnosing and correcting errors and faults in scripts & applications programming language.
  • Ensure documentation of technical programs, Scripts, Applications settings, end user documentation and operational procedures 
  • Consult and advise with BI Analyst and functional experts providing advice, guidance and expertise in developing proposals and strategies for delivering reporting, targeting & analysis.
  • Consult & advise improvements to applications ecosystem improvements including architecture & costings

To be the best you can be in this role we are looking for:

  • Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in Information Technology / Data Science / Software Engineering / Computer engineering.
  • Significant experience in data science, database or data applications.
  • Azure: ADF (Azure Data Factory), Data Lake
  • Microsoft: SSIS/ETL
  • Strong Database skills: Stored procedures, queries etc.
  • Data Warehousing
  • Python (not essential)
  • Power BI (not essential)

What's on offer:

  • Competitive salary package (base salary plus bonus)
  • Employee Assistance Program
  • Online Wellbeing Centre
  • Opportunity to grow and develop in the role and future career growth
  • Be a part of a growing team with a company that is at the forefront of innovation in the hearing industry
  • A genuinely rewarding role with purpose and meaning

Sonova is an equal opportunity employer

We team up. We grow talent. We collaborate with people of diverse backgrounds to win with the best team in the market place. We guarantee every person equal treatment in regard to employment and opportunity for employment, regardless of a candidate’s ethnic or national origin, religion, sexual orientation or marital status, gender, genetic identity, age, disability or any other legally protected status.

For any enquiries, you can contact us at careers@connecthearing.com.au

To find out more about us, please visit our website at www.connecthearing.com.au
