job.title: Senior Data Architect
job.abstract: We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Architect to support the uplift of data collection, run analytics and develop optimisation capabilities.
job.content:
• 6 Months contract with potential extension.
  • Attractive Daily rates $1250 per day plus super
  • Immediate Start| Parramatta.
Easy authoring is seeking an experienced Senior Data Architect to support the uplift of data collection, run analytics and develop optimisation capabilities with a large Government body.

Key Accountabilities:
  • Work with business to understand the business requirement and facilitate the discussion with business stakeholder(s) for agreement and approval of business data requirements.
  • Provide data solutions to meet business requirements and obtain necessary sign-off and approvals.
  • Support the development and communication of the data architecture plans and policies to senior leaders, staff, partners, and stakeholders.
  • Lead the data management stream in providing direction, approach and work with project data modellers and SW suppliers to deliver the data and value models, business glossary and data quality deliverables.
  • Work in a team of Professional Services consultants, modeler, architects, and project managers who implement value models and business program optimisations.
  • Be involved, lead, or participate in business and technical sessions to document or review program documentation.
  • In addition to a business and technical background, the position requires strong problem-solving, analytical abilities and consulting skills with the ability to communicate effectively at various levels of business and project.
  • Delivered data architecture artefacts in multiple projects and has experience in dealing with multiple and complex data sources for both structured and unstructured data types.
Essential requirements:
  • Prior experience in delivering cloud-based (preferably Azure) data platforms.
  • End-to-end data architecture/ solution
  • Enterprise value models
  • Data Quality solutions
  • Data and analytics platforms
  • Enterprise management capability
  • Enterprise Information model.
  • Deep knowledge in understanding, analysing and communicating business and data requirements. Providing solutions, highlighting gaps and priorities to address the business outcomes.
  • Data architecture delivery in Azure-based data platform
  • Delivery of data management and data governance.
  • An understanding of Asset Investment Planning and Optimisation Systems
  • An understanding of Data bricks, Azure data factory, synapse, Collibra and Power BI.
  • Relationship Building: The ability to forge strong relationships with Business Users, Vendors including other partners and consultants
If this sounds like you, please submit your resume by clicking the 'Apply Now' button. For further information about this role, please contact Naresh at 0481 615 994 or email naresh.shankar@easyauthoring.com
  
About Easy Authoring:
Established in 2006, Easy Authoring helps job seekers find the right opportunity to match their skill set and aide career progression. We are the authorised suppliers to NSW, ACT, QLD and Federal government as well as multiple corporate organisations to provide contingent labour for various business functions including: ICT, Project Management, Change Management, Learning design along with a broad range of other business focused positions.

job.title: Senior Developer - Data Integrations
job.abstract: Want to be involved with the development in data integration using Azure tech stack? Apply now!
job.content:
Forever New Evolving

Forever New is Australia's fastest growing fashion clothing and accessories brand. With more than 300 stores and a vast online presence across the globe, we have developed a strong community of fashion-lovers, designers, innovators, experts and creatives who have taken us from Melbourne to the world.

Forever New Opportunity

We currently have an exciting opportunity for an Azure Integration Developer within the Technology team that is embarking on a key strategic initiative. This role will primarily be involved with development in data integration using Azure tech stack.

Skills & Experience 

Minimum 3 years of Software Development using Microsoft .NET technologies (C#, .NET Core) and Azure Integration iPaaS, with some or all the following,

  • Azure Logic apps, Function Apps
  • C# API development experience

Azure Functions –

  • Service Bus
  • Logic Apps, Function Apps
  • Azure Storage
  • Azure API Management
  • Good understanding of cloud technologies, especially Azure cloud
  • Hands on experience in designing RESTful\GraphQL Services using APIs
  • General understanding of Authentication, Security and Networking concepts, especially in cloud context.

Forever New Company Culture & Benefits

Here at Forever New, our people are at the heart of everything we do. Forever New HQ is a fast-paced retail environment rapidly expanding across the globe. By the same token, we're all about a healthy, flexible work-life balance. That's why, as part of the Forever New family, you'll enjoy plenty of exciting rewards and benefits.

The perks:

  • Generous 40% employee discount and periodic family and friends’ discounts
  • Loyalty and birthday leave
  • Monthly afternoon tea with an early finish Friday
  • Wellbeing and environmental incentives
  • Learning and development programs
  • Recognition program and service awards
  • Subsidized car parking
  • Thriving head office located in Richmond
  • Exposure to a global business based across 5 continents
  • Recruitment referral incentives

Whether we’re designing our latest fashion collection, expanding into a new international market, or providing expert styling advice to our loyal customers, these are a few of the rules we live by:

Think Customer  Respect for all  Keep it Simple  Take Responsibility  Act with Pace
